o overhaul their role and position. Not acting comes at a cost: if the government does not adjust, it will be exposed to the powers of the energetic society that may effectively obstruct government initiatives. We need a new partnership and a new division of roles. \r\n\r\nInnovation means scope for action and initiative, accepting the fact that mistakes will be made, and making certain that improvements are identified and implemented rapidly. Such innovation calls for a different type of government based on the notion of “radical incrementalism”. Digitalizing sustainable “achievements” of institutions and businesses can play a key role in this. Fast and continual feedback about behavior and its consequences are of great value to society.\r\n\r\nThe challenge is to do more with less – something for which there is no instant solution. New ideas will constantly be required and may be stimulated by a government that commits itself to clear objectives and makes use of new forms of social engagement. In all of this, urban communities will play a key role.\r\n','2011-09-16 09:00:00','2011-09-16 09:20:00','2011-08-23 13:45:35','2011-08-23 13:49:20',1,NULL),(255,'City Dashboard',1,'','2011-09-16 11:55:00','2011-09-16 12:15:00','2011-08-23 14:16:17','2011-08-23 14:16:17',1,NULL);
