ciety.\r\n\r\nTogether with Bas Verhart (Media Republic) she created PICNIC, the leading European event for the creative industries, an innovation platform hosted yearly in Amsterdam.\r\n\r\nIn 2007 Marleen Stikker  initiated the ICT Innovation Platform Creative Industries (IIPcreate) which aims to bring together science, industry and the creative sector to formulate a strategic research agenda.\r\nStikker is a member of the  Board of Directors at WPG Publishers, an independent publishing group. She continues to advocate her message of \"inclusion through technology\" around the world.','2011-08-24 12:30:05','2011-08-24 12:30:05'),(463,1046,'forename','Jane','2011-08-24 12:52:35','2011-08-24 12:52:35'),(464,1046,'surname','Tjon Tjauw Liem','2011-08-24 12:52:35','2011-08-24 12:52:35'),(465,1046,'bio',NULL,'2011-08-24 12:52:35','2011-08-24 12:52:35'),(466,582,'forename','Alexandra','2011-08-24 13:47:15','2011-08-24 13:47:15'),(467,582,'surname','Burton','2011-08-24 13:47:15','2011-08-24 13:47:15'),(468,582,'bio',NULL,'2011-08-24 13:47:15','2011-08-24 13:47:15'),(469,582,'bio','New York City transplant loving and living in Amsterdam. Consumer/event/guerilla marketing expert (in the making as the quest for knowledge never ceases) working at the best agency in the world, Edelman. ','2011-08-24 13:50:25','2011-08-24 13:50:25'),(470,1116,'forename','Jesse','2011-08-24 14:47:43','2011-08-24 14:47:43'),(471,1116,'surname','Hoosemans','2011-08-24 14:47:43','2011-08-24 14:47:43'),(472,1116,'bio','Programme Manager for digital media at Kenteq, Centre of Expertise on Vocational Education, Training and the Labour Market.','2011-08-24 14:47:43','2011-08-24 14:47:43'),(473,485,'forename','Yasmina','2011-08-24 15:56:52','2011-08-24 15:56:52'),(474,485,'surname','Haryono','2011-08-24 15:56:52','2011-08-24 15:56:52'),(475,485,'bio',NULL,'2011-08-24 15:56:52','2011-08-24 15:56:52'),(476,1044,'bio','Ilari Patrick Lindy is Senior ICT Policy Specialist at the ICT Sector Unit of the World Bank. Before joining to the Bank he worked as Senior Advisor at the Ministry for Foreign Affairs of Finland advising on policies and instruments related to science, technology (ICT) and innovation for development. He has previously served in various advisory and project management positions in Finnish government and in European Commission both in European and African continent. Ilari is interested in Open Innovation related instruments such as Living Labs and opportunities to foster global cooperation on ICT enabled innovation.\n','2011-08-24 16:36:08','2011-08-24 16:36:08'),(477,889,'forename','Frits','2011-08-24 17:47:28','2011-08-24 17:47:28'),(478,889,'surname','Nolet','2011-08-24 17:47:28','2011-08-24 17:47:28'),(479,889,'bio','Founding Board member at Stichting IPv6 Nederland','2011-08-24 17:47:28','2011-08-24 17:47:28'),(480,983,'forename','Chris','2011-08-24 20:53:10','2011-08-24 20:53:10'),(481,983,'surname','Pinchen','2011-08-24 20:53:10','2011-08-24 20:53:10'),(482,983,'bio',NULL,'2011-08-24 20:53:10','2011-08-24 20:53:10'),(483,1093,'forename','Bram','2011-08-25 05:25:00','2011-08-25 05:25:00'),(484,1093,'surname','Lievens','2011-08-25 05:25:00','2011-08-25 05:25:00'),(485,1093,'bio',NULL,'2011-08-25 05:25:00','2011-08-25 05:25:00'),(486,1124,'forename','Marnix','2011-08-25 08:24:06','2011-08-25 08:24:06'),(487,1124,'surname','Bras','2011-08-25 08:24:06','2011-08-25 08:24:06'),(488,1124,'bio','Interaction Designer online at Agis Zorgverzekeringen / part of Achmea health at Achmea Zorg','2011-08-25 08:24:06','2011-08-25 08:24:06'),(489,1113,'forename','Amanda','2011-08-25 12:15:14','2011-08-25 12:15:14'),(490,1113,'surname','Mooney','2011-08-25 12:15:14','2011-08-25 12:15:14'),(491,1113,'bio','Amanda leads Edelman’s Shanghai Digital practice and serves as a lead strategist for clients such as Hilton HHonors and Hay Group. She helps clients understand key trends and insights related to audience technographics and community cultures online, develop community management, content and social business strategies and engage key stakeholders. In addition to her role as manager for the Shanghai Digital practice, Amanda is a co-lead of Edelman’s global Millennial consultancy, 8095, and acts as a digital contributor for goodpurpose at Edelman.\r\n\r\nPrior to transitioning to Edelman China, Amanda helped to lead insights and strategy for Edelman Digital Chicago.\r\n \r\nOutside of work, Amanda volunteers with TechYizu to help organize events for the tech community in Shanghai. As a blogger and avid social network user, Amanda’s perspective on Millennials and the digital space is regularly featured on Ruby Pseudo Wants a Word, the Edelman Digital blog, We Are The Digital Kids and in Paper Magazine. She has been cited in articles for GigaOM, ReadWriteWeb, BusinessWeek, The Boston Globe, Newsweek , Mashable and TIME, and has served as a contributor for Adrants and ad:tech and a judge for WOMMA’s annual Wommy Awards.\r\n','2011-08-25 12:15:14','2011-08-25 12:15:14'),(492,1127,'forename','Joost','2011-08-25 12:31:37','2011-08-25 12:31:37'),(493,1127,'surname','Bakker','2011-08-25 12:31:37','2011-08-25 12:31:37'),(494,1127,'bio','Born into a dynasty of Dutch flower growers, Joost is a discipline-crossing creative who constantly draws on his ‘horti-culture’ to make artful commentary on the world’s wasteful ways. Working exclusively with the waste of human activity he has fashioned such extraordinary forms that the word \"rubbish\" has risen from the scrap heap.\r\n\r\nJoost has been commissioned to design furniture, vertical gardens and event spaces in his trademark style juxtaposing nature and industry. In March 2006, Joost set about constructing a new home for his family, employing a unique building system: a contemporary take on a great sustainable construction method using straw bales set into a 100% recyclable steel framework. In 2008, the same building principles were used to construct the first \"Greenhouse by Joost\", an exhibition and event space at Melbourne’s Federation Square which was open from November 2008 to January 2009 and attracted 1,000 visitors per day, global media attention from major publications and over 2.5 million viewers on YouTube. A permanent Greenhouse by Joost is currently located at St George’s Terrace in Perth, Western Australia. In 2010 it was named Restaurant of the Year in Perth and attracts 800 to 1,000 visitors per day.\r\n\r\nJoost is driven by a genuine passion for simply doing things better - and opening a public dialogue about sustainable design practices in the process.','2011-08-25 12:31:37','2011-08-25 12:31:37'),(495,574,'forename','Ronald','2011-08-25 12:32:45','2011-08-25 12:32:45'),(496,574,'surname','Lenz','2011-08-25 12:32:45','2011-08-25 12:32:45'),(497,574,'bio',NULL,'2011-08-25 12:32:45','2011-08-25 12:32:45'),(498,921,'forename','Tobias','2011-08-25 12:41:53','2011-08-25 12:41:53'),(499,921,'surname','Sievers','2011-08-25 12:41:53','2011-08-25 12:41:53'),(500,921,'bio','Entrepreneur in digital media, creative director with coffee-addiction, love to make & hate to admin','2011-08-25 12:41:53','2011-08-25 12:41:53'),(501,1137,'forename','Bart','2011-08-25 13:01:49','2011-08-25 13:01:49'),(502,1137,'surname','te Riele','2011-08-25 13:01:49','2011-08-25 13:01:49'),(503,1137,'bio','Creative director at Energize. Public and professional listener. Parttime thinker. (But also like to share what i\'ve learned by listening & thinking)','2011-08-25 13:01:49','2011-08-25 13:01:49'),(504,1123,'forename','Monique','2011-08-25 13:26:16','2011-08-25 13:26:16'),(505,1123,'surname','Panhéleux','2011-08-25 13:26:16','2011-08-25 13:26:16'),(506,1123,'bio','FDI Advisor at Invest in Western France in ICT: web 2.0, Internet, social & real networks! Located in #Nantes. I\'m also a #Greeter. Like 2 be on stage too !','2011-08-25 13:26:16','2011-08-25 13:26:16'),(507,1114,'forename','William','2011-08-25 13:30:08','2011-08-25 13:30:08'),(508,1114,'surname','McDonough','2011-08-25 13:30:08','2011-08-25 13:30:08'),(509,1114,'bio','William McDonough, co-founder, McDonough Braungart Design Chemistry. William McDonough, FAIA, Int. FRIBA, is a designer, thought leader, and co-creator, with Michael Braungart, of the Cradle to Cradle® approach to design. He advises top leaders in all sectors including venture capital, government policy, city and building design, product manufacturing, industrial systems, economic systems and new business models, energy and water systems, and material reutilization in biological or technical cycles. 1996, he became the only individual to receive the Presidential Award for Sustainable Development. In 2003, he received the Presidential Green Chemistry Challenge Award. In 2004, he received the U.S. National Design Award. He was named a “Hero of the Planet” by Time magazine with a citation that included this assessment: “His utopianism is grounded in a unified philosophy that—in demonstrable and practical ways—is changing the design of the world.\"','2011-08-25 13:30:08','2011-08-25 13:30:08'),(510,1081,'forename','Marc','2011-08-25 13:50:53','2011-08-25 13:50:53'),(511,1081,'surname','Runco','2011-08-25 13:50:53','2011-08-25 13:50:53'),(512,1081,'bio','Mark Runco earned his PhD in Cognitive Psychology from the Claremont Graduate School. He has taught for over 20 years and earned tenure first at the University of Hawaii, Hilo, and then at California State University. In 2008 he accepted the position of E. Paul Torrance Professor of Creativity and Gifted Education at the University of Georgia, Athens. He was Director of the Torrance Center from 2008-2010. \r\n\r\nAdditionally, Marc has been Editor of the Creativity Research Journal since 1989 and is a Past President of Division 10 (Psychology, Art, Creativity, and Aesthetics) of the American Psychological Association.  He co-edited the revision of the Encyclopedia of Creativity (2011)  and his textbook,  Creativity: Theories, themes, and issues (Academic Press) has been translated into six languages. His primary area of empirical research is Adivergent and creative thinking.','2011-08-25 13:50:53','2011-08-25 13:50:53'),(513,1082,'forename','Renato Valdés','2011-08-25 14:17:40','2011-08-25 14:17:40'),(514,1082,'surname','Olmos','2011-08-25 14:17:40','2011-08-25 14:17:40'),(515,1082,'bio','I\'m the co-founder & CEO of Cardcloud. I build, manage, talk and design. I run a fantastic team. I\'m a geek, dandy, ex-fat kid, and runner. I love hats.\r\n\r\nRenato Valdés Olmos (1985) is co-founder and CEO of Cardcloud, a service that allows users to create online business cards and exchange them by using mobile phones. Cardcloud is a fast-growing startup based out of Amsterdam funded by several angel investors.\r\n\r\nPrior to founding Cardcloud, Renato founded a hardware company called My Name is E and a profitable design agency called Postmachina.\r\n\r\nRenato holds a Master’s degree in Interaction Design, but now spends his time growing his team in Amsterdam, New York and San Francisco. \r\n\r\nAs a co-founder of Dutch entrepreneurial collective STIKK, Renato advises startups on product design, marketing and fundraising. Renato talks about his technology vision and is an expert in the fields of user interface design, marketing, PR and team building.','2011-08-25 14:17:40','2011-08-25 14:17:40'),(516,596,'forename','Fred','2011-08-25 14:40:17','2011-08-25 14:40:17'),(517,596,'surname','Rocha','2011-08-25 14:40:17','2011-08-25 14:40:17'),(518,596,'bio','Founder and CEO of FitMemes, the minds behind memeoirs.com. Food. Film. Music. Life.','2011-08-25 14:40:17','2011-08-25 14:40:17');
