INSERT INTO `documents` VALUES (1,'PICNIC Logos','2011/05/05/05_01_38_506_PICNIC_Logos.zip','PICNIC_Logos.zip','zip',2,0,'2011-05-05 12:01:38','2011-05-05 12:01:38',NULL,NULL),(2,'PICNIC 2011 Volunteer Application Form','2011/07/08/08_28_24_560_PICNIC_Festival_2011_Volunteer_Application.doc','PICNIC Festival 2011 Volunteer Application.doc','doc',36,0,'2011-07-08 15:28:24','2011-07-08 15:28:24',NULL,NULL),(3,'NPL Newsflash - Energy sector is hot amongst investors_7July2011','2011/07/12/04_51_57_576_NPL_Newsflash_Energy_sector_is_hot_amongst_inventors_7July11.PDF','NPL_Newsflash_Energy sector is hot amongst inventors_7July11.PDF','PDF',36,0,'2011-07-12 11:51:57','2011-07-12 11:51:57',NULL,NULL),(4,'PICNIC 11 Urban Futures Building the PICNIC City_15Apr2011','2011/07/12/05_04_23_891_PICNIC_11_Urban_Futures_Building_the_PICNIC_City.PDF','PICNIC 11 Urban Futures - Building the PICNIC City.PDF','PDF',36,0,'2011-07-12 12:04:23','2011-07-12 12:04:23',NULL,NULL),(5,'PICNIC Builds City at NDSM_29July11','2011/07/29/04_00_49_947_PICNIC_Builds_City_at_NDSM_29July2011.pdf','PICNIC Builds City at NDSM_29July2011.pdf','pdf',36,0,'2011-07-29 11:00:49','2011-07-29 11:00:49',NULL,NULL),(6,'PICNIC Festival 2011 Presentation','2011/08/09/08_48_58_364_PresPICNIC11_Small.pdf','PresPICNIC11_Small.pdf','pdf',36,0,'2011-08-09 15:48:58','2011-08-09 15:48:58',NULL,NULL),(7,'2011 Marketplace Participants','2011/08/11/09_06_45_231_Marketplace_Participants_PICNIC_11_11Aug.pdf','Marketplace Participants PICNIC 11_11Aug.pdf','pdf',36,1,'2011-08-11 16:06:45','2011-08-11 16:06:45',NULL,'MARKETPLACE Participants\nPICNIC Festival 2011\n\nDPI Animation\nDPI Animation House is a visual communication agency and 3D producer based in the Netherlands. We create computer illustrations, augmented reality applications, animations, educational programs, video productions, interactive presentations, websites, apps and other touch-technology based solutions. Our productions have won various awards at national and international animation festivals. 3D Animation has many faces and applications. DPI is the national market leader in the field of real estate and infrastructure projects, having been involved in more than 1,800 plans to date. These range from minor inner-city changes to comprehensive new housing developments and national projects involving high-speed railways, airports, shopping malls and harbors. www.dpi.nl www.dpinewmedia.nl\n\nDigifit B.V. = VirtuaGym\nDIGIFiT develops new wellness applications in the field of fitness and lifestyle, applying smart technology to motivate people to live healthier and more active lifestyles in an easy and fun way. DIGIFiT‟s fitness ecosystem VirtuaGym, comprising mobile apps, connected hardware and an online portal has over 700,000 users worldwide. DIGIFiT has now developed YourLifestyle™, a solution that allows third parties to use this rich and proven lifestyle portal solution, completely with their own branding and domain name. This allows them to offer participants a personalized training and nutrition plan through the automated system and/or the online coaching interface. http://www.miclub.nl/yourlifestyle\n\nStudio Überdutch\nWe are Studio Überdutch. We develop creative brand concepts with a strong focus on product and interior design and consumer interaction. Last March we started a new brand called “Swipespot” that offers tablet-related products for the corporate market. We used a very innovative, open approach by sharing every step in our design / development process and using our network‟s input to improve the product. This resulted in great exposure and enthusiastic reactions. In August 2011 we will deliver the first 50 Tablet Stands. The elegant design invites users to communicate interactively. A real Dutch Design product to improve corporate presentations. www.swipespot.nl\n\nSense Company\nSense Company awakens your senses! Sense Company is specialized in advising, developing and executing total experiences. Our motto is “Awakening your senses”. Our main focus is scent. The advantages of scent are highly underestimated: our nose has a direct influence on our wellbeing, emotions and judgments. Therefore scent is a very important marketing instrument. http://www.sense-company.nl\n\nMuzar.org\nWe create location- based and augmented reality experiences for creatives, brands, agencies, content owners and you! Visar helps to set up, host and publish your own location-based/AR services with ease and on multiple platforms (like Layar and QR codes). It offers power users unique tools to manage large data sets. Visar requires no technical background or programming skills: through its intuitive interface, anyone can learn to use it. It‟s web based, runs in the cloud and is offered as a service (SAAS) so it‟s easy to set up, scalable and highly reliable. www.visar.biz\n\nMoop.me\nMoop.me is developing an iPad Cash Register \"Cashier\" for pubs, clubs, restaurants & cafes. The choice used to be either a large glorified calculator or an expensive Windows-based touch-screen point of sale system. The iPad Cash Register is cheaper, more user friendly and beautifully designed. It also automatically backs up its data in the cloud, and makes it available through a web interface. www.getcashier.com http://moop.me/\n\nWhatser\nWhatser is your city, your collection of favorite spots. From restaurants to galleries, from coffee bars to pop-up stores, Whatser offers a collection that reflects your taste and preference, in the city where you live, work or simply love to hang out. To get more inspiration and inside information you follow other people‟s collections; the ones of friends, specialists or big shots, so that you always have suggestions to discover new places. Wherever you are and wherever you‟d like to go. www.whatser.com/\n\nStudioNUM\nNew Urban Media (NUM) is specialized in integrating network technology with urban development: locating and optimizing connections in urban areas. With project “CloudMrkt” NUM combines traditional urban planning research (density, demographics, infrastructure) and information technology. It is a process that translates both physical and digital flows efficiently and intuitively into a business application. This interface (desktop and mobile) uses real-time data mapping and social media functionality. Information from different companies and the region becomes visible and available. It gives you the ability to easily share knowledge and expertise and saves up to 20% in costs. Transparent, reliable, efficient, scalable and repeatable \"CloudMrkt\' unlocks local economic and sustainable opportunities. www.studionum.com/\n\nOAT Shoes\nOAT Shoes are shoes that bloom. That‟s right, when you wear these sneakers out, you can bury them in the ground and let the seeds in the tongue bloom into a colorful bouquet of wildflowers. Meanwhile, the shoes will decompose into compost in the ground. OAT was born out of a desire to create products that are not only good-looking. “We want to create products that connect people with their environment in an imaginative way. So in every product, there is a story for the buyers to share. Like the little seeds in our shoes.” www.oatshoes.com\n\nTreemagotchi\nTreemagotchi is a unique, award-winning and proven social media tool that makes sustainability and CSR concrete, easy and fun for large crowds of individuals - at home and in the workplace. How? You get your own personal digital tree that you can place on your Facebook profile or blog. Treemagotchi handpicks the best and most viable actions available online and sends you action reminders. If you perform an action regularly, your tree will automatically react, it will grow and flourish and you are in the race for prizes. However, if you don‟t take action, your tree will deteriorate… www.treemagotchi.nl\n\nTygron Serious Gaming\nTygron is a leading developer of Serious Games regarding spatial development and multi-actor situations in the Netherlands. We specialize in bringing complex multi-actor management challenges into a multiplayer Serious Game. We often rebuild a real-life situation in our virtual 3D-world. Therefore, stakeholders can experience the challenges of the future in a safe environment. Our customers vary from government institutions like Rijkswaterstaat and several Ministries and Municipalities to large companies like the Port of Rotterdam. They all choose Serious Gaming experiences where interests conflict and converge. We are pleased to show our experiences regarding urban challenges like livability, real estate and water problems. www.climategame.nl\n\nGreen map system\nData visualization is our medium for fostering inclusive participation in sustainable community development. We share adaptable mapmaking tools and universal Green Map Icons with 750 diverse teams in 55 countries. Hundreds of locally published Green Maps have connected millions of people to local social, cultural, ecological and green living sites. Our new social mapping platform at http://GreenMap.org has radically reduced financial, technical and financial barriers to public participation. Mobile apps and widgets offer residents, visitors, entrepreneurs and policymakers inspiring local models and global connections. We offer the PICNIC audience a great way to extend leadership capacity and impact urban sustainability initiatives. www.greenmap.org\n\nBureau BlauwGeel\nBureau BlauwGeel – Augmented Reality adventure in the city At PICNIC we will show Molecular City. Molecular City is an Augmented Reality adventure that you could experience with your smartphone during the Night of Art & Science in Groningen. More cities to come! Bureau BlauwGeel is a creative web agency. We help you with your online strategy and we make beautiful things to support that strategy. We do online campaigns, websites and mobile applications. Clients call us because our work evokes immersive experiences and because we deliver one-timeright. We dive into your issue and come up with innovative solutions. http://bureaublauwgeel.nl/\n\nPixelPixies\nGetting your message across is increasingly difficult nowadays. Serious Games offer you the possibility to let your target audience “experience” the message instead of reading, hearing or watching it. Using the immersion effect of games, players will learn and remember more. At PixelPixies we have been creating (serious) games since 2002. At PICNIC we will show our latest project “Villa Eeckhoorn” aimed at kids in primary school. The game makes them aware of the influence they have on the environment as a consumer. \"From Bangkok till New York, make a difference with your fork.\" www.pixelpixies.nl\n\nSnappCar\nSnappCar offers you the possibility to rent out your own car or rent someone else\'s car in an easy and fully reliable manner. All matters one can potentially worry about, like insurance, road assistance and payment are taken care of by this new service in the Dutch mobility market. Car owners can earn money by renting out their expensive and quickly depreciating asset, profiting from the occasions when they don‟t need to use the car themselves. Car renters who are looking for flexibility have the opportunity to rent at decent prices and select from a large range of brands and types. In addition, they can pick up their car close to their home as the car owner is living nearby. Car use is reinvented with a service offering convenience, reliability, affordability, efficiency and care for the environment. www.snappcar.nl\n\nBy-wire.net\nAccording to Marina Toeters, founder of by-wire.net, “If technicians and designers would join forces and start interdisciplinary projects with added benefits to society, the fashion and textile industries will become innovative once again and can take responsibility for environmental issues by implementing high-tech solutions in the commercial market.” By-wire.net loves to expand innovative fashion by sharing knowledge. As a freelance intermediary, Marina Toeters works for both fashion and technical companies. She creates concepts, brainstorm sessions, presentations and garments for technical companies that are looking for a new application for their materials or advises designers interested in material and process innovation. www.by-wire.net\n\nPur Sang Royal\nWe offer an innovative app for web-based and smart phone platforms, to help people find jobs and accommodation near their school. The goal of our application is to help people improve their mobility, thanks to a new algorithm that enables smarter use of data. The app includes: Shorter distances to accommodation, work and education (school), with focus on environment and time savings Traffic analysis for people travelling to their work, accommodation and education and to predict trends Platform to attract new housing and job projects www.pursangroyal.com\n\nGreenGraffiti\nYou hear a lot about new media. GreenGraffiti® is the new media. Creating messages by means of the most appropriate new sustainable methods, we use communication techniques that have a high impact on the audience but a low impact on the environment. Sustainable by its very nature, GreenGraffiti® is not simply about environmental box-ticking. We offset 100% of the water we use, and our processes are completely carbon neutral. So, it‟s an alternative communication method, but that‟s about as alternative as we get. We provide pragmatic, innovative communication solutions for pragmatic, innovative businesses and organizations. We help to increase visibility and raise profiles using methods that depart radically from traditional communications, and are socially responsible. www.greengraffiti.com\n\nSpringtime Holding\nSpringtime Holding is a group of 3 companies that are involved in mobility. Springtime industrial design is a design consultancy with over 15 years experience in mobility and brand development. Bikedispenser is world\'s most compact and fully automatic bicycle storage and rental system. LEEV Mobility is the latest company in the group, developing and marketing light electric vehicles. LEEV‟s first product - the Mantys Golf - is an electric vehicle for the golf course. The Mantys will have its global launch this summer. We welcome you to visit us at the PICNIC Marketplace to discuss your mobility needs and ideas! www.springtime.nl\n\nMediamatic\nMediamatic is an art space and design lab based in Amsterdam. Mediamatic Lab develops connections between the virtual and the real world. Our projects include social networks and installations that encourage interaction, collaboration and knowledge sharing. We work for NTR, INNL, Puma, Amsterdam Museum, DOEN Foundation, Renault, Jewish Historical Museum, Pakhuis De Zwijger, ANP, Stadsherstel, Women Inc. and about fifty other organizations. Examples of our products include the ikPod: our prize-winning multimedia guide, the offline “check in” for Facebook Places and the physical “Like” button. Our sister organization Mediamatic Foundation organizes exhibitions, workshops, dev camps and lectures on new media, art, culture and society. Projects include El Hema: an Arabic department store, and the Expired Food Club: a protest against the demonization of expired, but irresistibly good food. Combined we are Mediamatic, sharing ideas, facilities and talent. www.mediamatic.nl\n\nDrain Products Europe B.V.\nWith years of experience, Drain Products Europe BV is the specialist in water treatment and management, and a leader in introducing innovative new products. Many of the now common products used for water treatment and management have been developed by Drain Products Europe. To stay at the forefront of our field, we work in close co-operation with engineering offices, commissioners, universities and research departments. www.drainproducts.nl\n\nCarmela Bogman\nThe Pop-Up is furniture for public spaces. Pop-Up is furniture that can be pumped out of the sidewalk by the inhabitants. After use, the Pop-Up it then deflated back into the sidewalk, creating a peaceful street scene without any obstacles. This means that the inhabitants have the freedom to decide for themselves when they want to use the Pop-Up and in which way. Several keys that give access to the pumping system are spread among different users of the furniture. Pop-Up blurs the boundaries between public and private. www.carmelabogman.nl\n\nGlobe4D\nThis interactive four-dimensional globe shows on a physical sphere how our planet changes over time. Globe4D can be viewed from all angles and can be controlled directly by rotating the sphere itself and turning the ring around the sphere. Globe4D introduces time as the fourth dimension for a globe. It shows animations about the earth\'s history and future, changing seasons, earthquakes, daylight changes, human migration and phenomena on other planets. These are just a few examples of the unlimited possibilities created by this interactive and tangible globe. Recently, a topography game and a visualization of live Twitter data were also developed. www.globe4d.com\n\ntheFactor.e\nOffer your visitors a rich interactive 3D experience of your products, services and stories! Sfeerz makes it possible to create attractive 3D applications quickly and easily, based on 360-degree panoramas or 360-degree videos. Sfeerz can be connected to the CMS of your website and be managed and maintained by yourself. Experience Sfeerz for yourself during PICNIC Festival 2011. Visit our stand for a free personal interactive “3D greetings from PICNIC card”. Please visit www.sfeerz.com for more information and http://virtueel.umcg.nl and http://opendaghanze.nl for inspirational cases. Sfeerz is an application from theFactor.e: www.tfe.nl\n\nGreen Olive/Greenlung\n“De groenten uit Amsterdam” will be the first indoor city farm in Western Europe. The veggies grow under ideal circumstances with LED lights in plant production units in empty office space and other buildings. The future of farming takes place in the cities and not on farmland. The cities are getting bigger and more densely populated and all those products need to be transported to the cities. Producing in the city means less transportation, fresh food and means less use of space through vertical production. So, de groenten uit Amsterdam is the future of farming. www.degroentenuitamsterdam.nl\n\nPhanta Vision\nPhanta Vision is a unique creative company. It‟s a cross-over of 3 independent organizations, located in a historical building in Amsterdam. We are specialists in Film productions, Film Editing and Audiovisual installations. We design and develop audio-visual solutions throughout the cultural sector. At PICNIC we will show one of our powerful projects. Creating an interactive installation in a small mobile theater, with live projection connected to sensors. “Magic in a nutshell” www.phantavision.com\n\nLiveNetLife International B.V.\nLiveNetLife is a service that allows you to set up connections between visitors of web pages. This is not new in itself; our innovation is that we do not request any direct link to connect users! So no email address, no FB friend connection or similar user information is needed – users don‟t even have to be on the same page or site. Our customers are websites that market products or services (we help sellers get more leads and higher hit rates), publishers (grow traffic and retention) and companies in general. The service is up and running on various websites and we have submitted a patent claim for our offering. www.livenetlife.com\n\nPavegen Systems\nImagine if every step you took generated electricity. Pavegen produces paving slabs that generate power from human footsteps. An unnoticeable 5mm of movement is enough to harvest the wasted kinetic energy and convert it into off-grid power. The electricity can either be collected in our storage system or be used instantly for interactive applications such as street lighting, advertising displays, bus stops and more. Pavegen is ideally used in high footfall locations such as shopping centers, transport hubs, supermarkets and sports stadiums. With an ever-expanding population this untapped resource allows for a localized solution for low power devices. www.pavegensystems.com\n\nMadLogic B.V.\nMadLogic develops innovative online advisory tools on the basis of serious gaming. The first strategic tool with which they intend to „gamify‟ consultancy is 3TGO. 3TGO is played digitally on a GO-inspired board with, on opposing sides, strategic and operational players who can visualize, analyze and optimize the structural DNA of their organization by making use of statements: http://www.youtube.com/user/madlogicbv. Consultants are provided with a FUNctional tool to help their clients achieve their ambitions or solve problems in any language at any place and time. 3TGO: How FUNctional are YOU? www.3tlogic.nl\n\nLightstorm Productions\nReplay My Day is a magic diary that tracks where you‟ve traveled in a day. Facebook and Twitter posts, appointments and photos you take will automatically pop up along the way. You can also add them yourself by dragging and dropping them onto the map. At the end of your day, press replay and relive your adventures. The longer you have Replay My Day, the richer it becomes: relive yesterday or that city trip several months ago, as a fast forwarded movie with you in the starring role. www.lightstorm.nl\n\nRoetz-Bikes\nRoetz-Bikes is a young brand with a mission. We believe that it is possible to provide robust, beautiful bicycles, while also reducing waste. Responsible bikes with a trendy look! More than one million bicycles are sold in the Netherlands every year. On the other hand, there are just as many bikes discarded. By reusing components of old bikes, we reduce the waste. In addition, for new parts we use natural materials as often as possible. For instance, Roetz-Bikes have wooden mudguards and cork handles. Roetz likes to make robust bikes. For all components we choose high quality brands that have proven themselves over the years. Finally, sheltered employment is an important element in creating our sustainable bike. www.roetz-bikes.nl\n\nDe Werff Architectuur\nChild Friendly Cities Families are one of the bearers of the new urbanity. How do you make a city child friendly? In the city is where we, De Werff Architectuur, work. On the urban level data is gathered and analyzed with others. For districts concepts are being developed in which the livability, children‟s development and the urban layout are the basis for the design of a safe, healthy, challenging and green environment. Within urban space the concepts are being tested and becoming part of new urban strategies that envision a healthy and livable city for all its inhabitants. www.dewerff.nl\n\nVliegende Varkens\nBehangrijk, a new way of standing out in the crowd. Behangrijk is a new product in the creative/exclusive wallpaper market. We create a unique design in which the customer can select which elements he want to customize -- for example a background color, pictures or ornaments. Our expert crew will then generate a personalized and unique wallpaper of excellent quality. Thanks to our personal approach, our quality of work and design we can distinguish ourselves in the world of interior design. We are also fully equipped to conceive a custommade design according to your desires. Everyone wants to be unique! www.vliegendevarkens.nl\n\nbuzzAR\nQRcode 3.0! buzzAR is a free smartphone app and a self-service “visual search platform”. With buzzAR the user can take a photo of an image (article, logo, ad or TV screen). buzzAR will send the photo to our server. The server analyzes the photo to find a match within the platform. If there is a match, the server returns a list of results. The list can contain a variety of actions: a link to a website, PDF, video, audio, navigation, direct calling, e-mail, text, nearest locations and Augmented Reality. buzzAR is a solution to connect offline expressions to information. www.buzzar.net\n\nKenlog B.V.\nwww.kenlog.nl\n\nFourceLabs\nFourceLabs designs playful experiences for the public spaces to grab attention and influence the way people feel and behave. We combine interaction and game design to deliver creative and imaginative solutions, highly bespoke and focused on our clients and their target audience. We will be showing our product Friends at the PICNIC Marketplace. Friends is a playful, physical and social platform for urban, professional and healthcare settings. It\'s a collective digital pet that everyone can see and interact with and which in both a literal and figurative sense brings color into a location. We would love to speak to you about Friends or our other services. See you at The Marketplace! www.fourcelabs.com\n\nSecuReceipt\nSR//Expenses is an expense management solution. It lowers transaction and processing costs, saves time and space, is easy to manage and allows for direct synchronization with your accounting software (e.g. Exact, SAP or Twinfield). SR//Expenses is accessible worldwide through your smartphone or web browser. Receipts and expense reports are stored on our secure servers, eliminating the need to save your paper receipts in many countries. With mobile applications for iPhone, iPad, Android and BlackBerry anyone can process receipts anywhere. www.srexpenses.com\n\nInqubative\nCities are changing at a fast pace and so is the media landscape. Governments and companies are constantly looking for innovative means of communication to reach today\'s population and consumers. That\'s why Inqubative presents BrandScreen. BrandScreen is a video display screen in the shape of a logo or icon. It combines technology with aesthetics and hig- end design and offers companies and (local) government a chance to link their logo to core value-based visuals (information, art, mood, commercials). BrandScreen is a perfect city marketing tool. The I amsterdam logo would transform into an interactive communication platform for citizens, artists and tourists (social media, uploads, mobile phones). This way the BrandScreen concept brings citizens, companies, politics and communities closer together. www.inqubative.com\n\nNegotica Development Projects\nUrban Futures & the power of the Brain The main concept behind the technology of Negotica is making it possible to connect all electrical devices through one open system. So why not imagine a urban future where you can control every electrical device with your brain? Negotica Development Projects, with a focus on the field of Brain-Computer Interface technology, has created Carebro. We have a solution to control our living environment by means of the human brain and as a result we entered the Dutch MKB Innovation Top 100. Coming from green building technology our aim is to help people improve in self-care and independence. Additional advantages are reduced energy costs, reduced operating costs, more intelligence and improvement of the living comfort. www.negotica.net\n\nPraktijk voor Industrieel Ontwerp\nOur industrial design practice helps companies and entrepreneurs to conceptualize and develop physical products. For series and mass production, from sketch to realization. We aim for sustainable results derived from clear concepts that add value for both users and businesses. Currently we are working on functional human-centered LED applications. A fascinating technology because of the endless possibilities in form, color and function in addition to the reduced energy consumption. At PICNIC we will present a LED light application that is based on The New Way of Working. We will show how light solutions can have a positive effect on modern day living and working. www.praktijk.io\n\nAnneke Jakobs\nAnneke Jakobs unravels existing products. With her findings she designs unusual, interactive projects that reveal information about the construction and origin of the product. By exposing such insights she wants to stimulate consumers to think about our industrialized environment. With her projects she tries to build a bridge between consumers and industry. At the Marketplace she will present her Mobile Ice Cream Workshop. The visitors are the ice cream machine themselves. Without electricity. And the composition of the ingredients depends on the environment and the season. www.annekejakobs.nl\n\nMCW Studio\'s\nMCW Studio‟s is an innovative multimedia studio with 5 separate disciplines: AV and Film Audio and Sound Interactive multimedia Internet 3D visualization and animation Over the past 17 years we have developed various innovative and interactive productions. We always look for the perfect integration of different forms of media, resulting in productions that aim to meet and exceed the goals of the client. A perfect example is a game we developed in which two players have to work together to run a factory. Both players need to use both hands and multiple fingers at the same time to get the best results. www.mcw.nl\n\nTwnkls augmented reality\ntwnkls | augmented reality is a full-service AR bureau that focuses on the creation, development, production and implementation of mobile AR applications. Our clients come from sectors edutainment, marketing & branding, construction and industrial sectors. twnkls is creative and innovative, and has extensive technical knowledge and experience in the area of Augmented Reality projects. At twnkls experienced specialists are working together on new location and image-based recognition technologies that result in new forms of interaction, user experience and business concepts.\n\nwww.twnkls.com\n\nMangrove\nSeachange is working in collaboration with Mangrove on the development of an iPad application for cable operators. The app combines the power of the back office software Seachange (Adrenalin) and current social media applications. Cable subscribers get access to premium video content on demand, an electronic program guide, and – in the near future – even a live television option. The app takes over the traditional remote control functions and makes large movie catalogs easily accessible. The app transforms the iPad into an extra TV screen and creates a social TV experience through smart integration with platforms like Twitter and Facebook. This application provides subscribers more value while watching television, such as additional content, virtual parties and intelligent social recommendations. For cable providers, the application offers a platform for targeted marketing campaigns around video on demand and linear broadcast. www.mangrove.nl\n\nEvident Interactive B.V.\nUrban Nature is about sharing our experience in providing access to nature; nature that is never far away from the shadows of the Dutch cities. The success of two recent concepts for Staatsbosbeheer proves that the urban species of man can be seduced by the pure and true inspiration of nature. Volgdevos.nl: a real life soap about a family of Foxes was visited 2.2 million times in 3 months. The Naar Buiten iPhone app to find nature close by has been downloaded more than 25,000 times. Inspired and powered by Evident Interactive. www.evident.nl\n\nWAACS Design & Consultancy\nWAACS Design & Consultancy is a professional and well-known design studio based in Rotterdam, specializing in product innovation and UX design (user experience). Our projects for multinationals like Sara Lee/DE, Microsoft, Medisana, G24 Innovations, ATAG, Alessi, Henkel/Pritt, H.J.Heinz, and Indesit prove that our way of working combines very well with internal R&D and marketing departments as well as large international target groups. Our best known product is the Philips Senseo that we designed with Sara Lee and later with Philips. www.waacs.com\n\nUrban Bike Concepts BV\nBeixo designs bikes that go beyond all traditions. First of all we use a shaft drive in stead of the old fashioned chain. Then the design: we put the usage and the user first without losing our sense of style. In the design of the new beixo GO, a 16-inch folding bike, we have looked at the needs of our users. The result is a super fast, foldable, easy to carry bike with a great look. www.urbanbikeconcepts.com\n\nFONKmobile\nAmsterdam-based FONKmobile is a digital agency that specializes in conceptualizing and developing mobile applications. Besides custom-made apps for a variety of clients, FONKmobile developed a number of mobile products: with the Automatic Book Compiler, artist and illustrator Bob Takens has a convenient tool to generate iPad apps for the children books he and Joke van Leeuwen create. Referred to as Mobile Efficiency, FONKmobile developed applications to speed up business processes using smartphones. We allow sales people to access all necessary product information (including stock) and created a tool to simplify B2B ordering in catering and retail. www.fonkmobile.nl\n\nVeeel ontwerpers\nVeeel Ontwerpers develops innovative products for leading brands and companies. Co-creation with designers is our specialty, innovation is our goal. We select the best designers for each project by using Designrider ™, our online platform consisting of over 1350 professional designers. We facilitate a solution-based process. Starting with a clear strategy, we develop concepts and optimize these to a produce-able design. Co-creation with designers means letting individual designers work together on problems, generating out-of-the-box insights, inspiration and a feasible solution. The combination of scalable creative skills and technical knowledge makes us the ideal partner for innovation. www.veeel.com\n\nOne-o-Niners\nFinding a voiceover in just 4 easy steps and knowing straightaway what it is going to cost you… Quite impossible, until now. Voiceover agency Voicebooking.com facilitates this process by setting up their website just like a web shop. Most voiceover agencies offer the customer such an extensive database of voices that it is impossible to keep track. Voicebooking.com has made a selection for you. It offers selected groups of professional voiceovers in several languages. Like every web shop, Voicebooking.com offers you additional services like scriptwriting, and mixing your production. Above all, we are able to work cost effectively because all our voices work from their own recording studios. www.voicebooking.com\n\nRanj\nTeacher in a Box – Learn how to write with a game A strong education in writing gives children a head start with respect to language development, reading comprehension and fine motor skills. Unfortunately the primary school curriculum fails to address this need. How can you make sure that children spend a lot of time practicing the necessary movements? By making it fun! Juf in a Box approaches writing lessons in a playful and educational way by combining the challenge, feedback and fun of games with an adaptive teaching method. The method is used by both physical therapists and teachers. www.ranj.com/nl\n\nButterflyworks\nGetH20 is a serious game that simulates the complexity of life in the slums, the scarcity of resources, how to deal with them and ultimately, how to prevent escalation of conflict. Around the world 1 billion people live in informal settlements and their numbers are growing as migration to cities increases. Butterfly Works and youth from Kenya have co-created a mobile app and a board game that deal with the themes of water scarcity, corruption, crime and community development. The aim of the game is to build houses and grow the water source, while maintaining a stable and happy community. By playing the game users become aware of the daily challenges in slums and gain insights into how these problems can be tackled in the real world. The game is currently soft launched in Kenya, is due for full launch in Uganda, and has proven to be unexpectedly popular in Saudi Arabia. The android version is in development and in 2012 we will expand the game with virtual goods that will translate into community projects with slum dwellers in the real world. www.geth20game.com www.butterflyworks.org\n\nCrafting Peace\nCrafting Peace is a design label and philosophy that uses crafts as a means to expand compassion in the world: stitch-by-stitch, bead-by-bead, color-by-color. Our approach is to co-create design products with craftsmen in developing countries. On the one hand, crafting is a method of tapping into someone‟s (often undiscovered) potential using hand, head and heart. But on the other hand crafting – however graceful, authentic and artistic it may appear – simply means putting bread on the table in some parts of our world. The design label Crafting Peace was established to create a new approach towards crafts and trade with developing countries. www.craftingpeace.com\n\nRoamler\nRoamler is a mobile workforce that lets businesses, brands and governments get their tasks done by enthusiastic Roamlers. A task can mapping a playground, reporting dangerous intersections or broken traffic signs, or even helping decide where a new bike rack is needed. Besides these examples, more commercial or creative assignments are possible as well. By performing these tasks, Roamlers earn money and experience points. The more experience points a Roamler earns, the more complex jobs he or she will get. www.roamler.com\n\nSense-os\nSense creates context awareness by combining and interpreting sensor data. For this purpose, we use sensors that are commonly and/or publicly available, such as sensors in smartphones, or Open Data. Context aware systems are capable of providing meaningful information to users, or pro-actively support users with services based on the personal context of the user. Furthermore, we aggregate personal context on a group level, to be used by others. Our solution can be applied in health care, mobility, energy management and smart cities. www.sense-os.nl\n\nCityconcept\nOur Little Utopia Back in those days when you were a child, you would draw your ideal house for you and your loved ones. Now, being grown up brings new wishes and needs in a fast-moving world. Nowadays we have to rediscover our ideal home and its environment. If we want to achieve our goals, we have to find new ways of (re)developing houses and real estate. CITYCONCEPT is creating an online community that matches people with similar desires and needs. We are using matching principles of online dating to allow like-minded people to group around shared housing needs. Together they find a location and design & develop their ideal home. We believe this type of co-creation leads to greater involvement and responsibility of people within their community in the city. www.cityconcept.nl\n\nA New Spring B.V.\nA New Spring: Technology that will personally help you study Today\'s e-learning can be compared to traditional maps. There might be an indicated route, but you still have to find your own way. In our vision the next generation e-learning should be more like navigation software. You set a personal goal and the platform will continuously make sure you stay on track by suggesting you directions. When you encounter obstacles the route will adjust to you. The result is a personalized learning experience that is more efficient. We believe internet technology can personally help students with their education. www.anewspring.com/platform-tour\n\nShapers\nAt Shapers we believe that learning can be both fun and effective. We design learning experiences that help organizations like schools, companies and museums to get the best out of people, by giving them more enjoyment and greater learning efficiency. A learning experience is best described as a process. Various factors such as people, learning objectives and different types of media play a role in that process. Using these elements we create a tailor-made solution for a logical and meaningful learning experience. www.shapers.nl\n\nAS Film\nRCAS - a Joint Venture between Drs.ir. Andre Schreuders en Drs. Rene Castelijn – is formed to program video installations and autonomous photography on urban screens in cities across the Netherlands. RCAS wants to be an agent between owners of (public) real estate, screen content suppliers, advertisers and visual artists. Concept: At important places in the city, art will be shown on “Urban Screens” – it grabs the attention of the passerby. Your advertisement - shown on the same screen - gets more attention from the audience, and the building gets added value. Art reclaims its place in society. Art and commerce work hand in hand in and everybody benefits. www.asfilm.nl\n\nTribe of Noise B.V.\nTribe of Noise is an online music community connecting artists and business. Artists remain 100% in control, but are empowered by our tools, legal framework and global community to gain exposure and secure music deals worldwide. We believe that non-exclusive and transparent business models are crucial for the future of the digital content industry. We are now gaining momentum in the advertisement, video gaming, video production, mobile app development and narrow-casting industry. From now on, if you need great music for commercial projects: Tribeofnoise.com is your #1 online resource. Let\'s make some Noise! www.tribeofnoise.com\n\n'),(8,'2011 Marketplace Participants_15Aug','2011/08/15/02_54_44_176_Marketplace_Participants_PICNIC_11_15Aug.pdf','Marketplace Participants PICNIC 11_15Aug.pdf','pdf',36,1,'2011-08-15 09:54:44','2011-08-15 09:54:44',NULL,'MARKETPLACE Participants\nPICNIC Festival 2011\n\nDPI Animation\nDPI Animation House is a visual communication agency and 3D producer based in the Netherlands. We create computer illustrations, augmented reality applications, animations, educational programs, video productions, interactive presentations, websites, apps and other touch-technology based solutions. Our productions have won various awards at national and international animation festivals. 3D Animation has many faces and applications. DPI is the national market leader in the field of real estate and infrastructure projects, having been involved in more than 1,800 plans to date. These range from minor inner-city changes to comprehensive new housing developments and national projects involving high-speed railways, airports, shopping malls and harbors. www.dpi.nl www.dpinewmedia.nl\n\nDigifit B.V. = VirtuaGym\nDIGIFiT develops new wellness applications in the field of fitness and lifestyle, applying smart technology to motivate people to live healthier and more active lifestyles in an easy and fun way. DIGIFiT‟s fitness ecosystem VirtuaGym, comprising mobile apps, connected hardware and an online portal has over 700,000 users worldwide. DIGIFiT has now developed YourLifestyle™, a solution that allows third parties to use this rich and proven lifestyle portal solution, completely with their own branding and domain name. This allows them to offer participants a personalized training and nutrition plan through the automated system and/or the online coaching interface. http://www.miclub.nl/yourlifestyle\n\nStudio Überdutch\nWe are Studio Überdutch. We develop creative brand concepts with a strong focus on product and interior design and consumer interaction. Last March we started a new brand called “Swipespot” that offers tablet-related products for the corporate market. We used a very innovative, open approach by sharing every step in our design / development process and using our network‟s input to improve the product. This resulted in great exposure and enthusiastic reactions. In August 2011 we will deliver the first 50 Tablet Stands. The elegant design invites users to communicate interactively. A real Dutch Design product to improve corporate presentations. www.swipespot.nl\n\nSense Company\nSense Company awakens your senses! Sense Company is specialized in advising, developing and executing total experiences. Our motto is “Awakening your senses”. Our main focus is scent. The advantages of scent are highly underestimated: our nose has a direct influence on our wellbeing, emotions and judgments. Therefore scent is a very important marketing instrument. http://www.sense-company.nl\n\nMuzar.org\nWe create location- based and augmented reality experiences for creatives, brands, agencies, content owners and you! Visar helps to set up, host and publish your own location-based/AR services with ease and on multiple platforms (like Layar and QR codes). It offers power users unique tools to manage large data sets. Visar requires no technical background or programming skills: through its intuitive interface, anyone can learn to use it. It‟s web based, runs in the cloud and is offered as a service (SAAS) so it‟s easy to set up, scalable and highly reliable. www.visar.biz\n\nMoop.me\nMoop.me is developing an iPad Cash Register \"Cashier\" for pubs, clubs, restaurants & cafes. The choice used to be either a large glorified calculator or an expensive Windows-based touch-screen point of sale system. The iPad Cash Register is cheaper, more user friendly and beautifully designed. It also automatically backs up its data in the cloud, and makes it available through a web interface. www.getcashier.com http://moop.me/\n\nWhatser\nWhatser is your city, your collection of favorite spots. From restaurants to galleries, from coffee bars to pop-up stores, Whatser offers a collection that reflects your taste and preference, in the city where you live, work or simply love to hang out. To get more inspiration and inside information you follow other people‟s collections; the ones of friends, specialists or big shots, so that you always have suggestions to discover new places. Wherever you are and wherever you‟d like to go. www.whatser.com/\n\nStudioNUM\nNew Urban Media (NUM) is specialized in integrating network technology with urban development: locating and optimizing connections in urban areas. With project “CloudMrkt” NUM combines traditional urban planning research (density, demographics, infrastructure) and information technology. It is a process that translates both physical and digital flows efficiently and intuitively into a business application. This interface (desktop and mobile) uses real-time data mapping and social media functionality. Information from different companies and the region becomes visible and available. It gives you the ability to easily share knowledge and expertise and saves up to 20% in costs. Transparent, reliable, efficient, scalable and repeatable \"CloudMrkt\' unlocks local economic and sustainable opportunities. www.studionum.com/\n\nOAT Shoes\nOAT Shoes are shoes that bloom. That‟s right, when you wear these sneakers out, you can bury them in the ground and let the seeds in the tongue bloom into a colorful bouquet of wildflowers. Meanwhile, the shoes will decompose into compost in the ground. OAT was born out of a desire to create products that are not only good-looking. “We want to create products that connect people with their environment in an imaginative way. So in every product, there is a story for the buyers to share. Like the little seeds in our shoes.” www.oatshoes.com\n\nTreemagotchi\nTreemagotchi is a unique, award-winning and proven social media tool that makes sustainability and CSR concrete, easy and fun for large crowds of individuals - at home and in the workplace. How? You get your own personal digital tree that you can place on your Facebook profile or blog. Treemagotchi handpicks the best and most viable actions available online and sends you action reminders. If you perform an action regularly, your tree will automatically react, it will grow and flourish and you are in the race for prizes. However, if you don‟t take action, your tree will deteriorate… www.treemagotchi.nl\n\nTygron Serious Gaming\nTygron is a leading developer of Serious Games regarding spatial development and multi-actor situations in the Netherlands. We specialize in bringing complex multi-actor management challenges into a multiplayer Serious Game. We often rebuild a real-life situation in our virtual 3D-world. Therefore, stakeholders can experience the challenges of the future in a safe environment. Our customers vary from government institutions like Rijkswaterstaat and several Ministries and Municipalities to large companies like the Port of Rotterdam. They all choose Serious Gaming experiences where interests conflict and converge. We are pleased to show our experiences regarding urban challenges like livability, real estate and water problems. www.climategame.nl\n\nGreen map system\nData visualization is our medium for fostering inclusive participation in sustainable community development. We share adaptable mapmaking tools and universal Green Map Icons with 750 diverse teams in 55 countries. Hundreds of locally published Green Maps have connected millions of people to local social, cultural, ecological and green living sites. Our new social mapping platform at http://GreenMap.org has radically reduced financial, technical and financial barriers to public participation. Mobile apps and widgets offer residents, visitors, entrepreneurs and policymakers inspiring local models and global connections. We offer the PICNIC audience a great way to extend leadership capacity and impact urban sustainability initiatives. www.greenmap.org\n\nBureau BlauwGeel\nBureau BlauwGeel – Augmented Reality adventure in the city At PICNIC we will show Molecular City. Molecular City is an Augmented Reality adventure that you could experience with your smartphone during the Night of Art & Science in Groningen. More cities to come! Bureau BlauwGeel is a creative web agency. We help you with your online strategy and we make beautiful things to support that strategy. We do online campaigns, websites and mobile applications. Clients call us because our work evokes immersive experiences and because we deliver one-timeright. We dive into your issue and come up with innovative solutions. http://bureaublauwgeel.nl/\n\nPixelPixies\nGetting your message across is increasingly difficult nowadays. Serious Games offer you the possibility to let your target audience “experience” the message instead of reading, hearing or watching it. Using the immersion effect of games, players will learn and remember more. At PixelPixies we have been creating (serious) games since 2002. At PICNIC we will show our latest project “Villa Eeckhoorn” aimed at kids in primary school. The game makes them aware of the influence they have on the environment as a consumer. \"From Bangkok till New York, make a difference with your fork.\" www.pixelpixies.nl\n\nSnappCar\nSnappCar offers you the possibility to rent out your own car or rent someone else\'s car in an easy and fully reliable manner. All matters one can potentially worry about, like insurance, road assistance and payment are taken care of by this new service in the Dutch mobility market. Car owners can earn money by renting out their expensive and quickly depreciating asset, profiting from the occasions when they don‟t need to use the car themselves. Car renters who are looking for flexibility have the opportunity to rent at decent prices and select from a large range of brands and types. In addition, they can pick up their car close to their home as the car owner is living nearby. Car use is reinvented with a service offering convenience, reliability, affordability, efficiency and care for the environment. www.snappcar.nl\n\nBy-wire.net\nAccording to Marina Toeters, founder of by-wire.net, “If technicians and designers would join forces and start interdisciplinary projects with added benefits to society, the fashion and textile industries will become innovative once again and can take responsibility for environmental issues by implementing high-tech solutions in the commercial market.” By-wire.net loves to expand innovative fashion by sharing knowledge. As a freelance intermediary, Marina Toeters works for both fashion and technical companies. She creates concepts, brainstorm sessions, presentations and garments for technical companies that are looking for a new application for their materials or advises designers interested in material and process innovation. www.by-wire.net\n\nPur Sang Royal\nWe offer an innovative app for web-based and smart phone platforms, to help people find jobs and accommodation near their school. The goal of our application is to help people improve their mobility, thanks to a new algorithm that enables smarter use of data. The app includes: Shorter distances to accommodation, work and education (school), with focus on environment and time savings Traffic analysis for people travelling to their work, accommodation and education and to predict trends Platform to attract new housing and job projects www.pursangroyal.com\n\nGreenGraffiti\nYou hear a lot about new media. GreenGraffiti® is the new media. Creating messages by means of the most appropriate new sustainable methods, we use communication techniques that have a high impact on the audience but a low impact on the environment. Sustainable by its very nature, GreenGraffiti® is not simply about environmental box-ticking. We offset 100% of the water we use, and our processes are completely carbon neutral. So, it‟s an alternative communication method, but that‟s about as alternative as we get. We provide pragmatic, innovative communication solutions for pragmatic, innovative businesses and organizations. We help to increase visibility and raise profiles using methods that depart radically from traditional communications, and are socially responsible. www.greengraffiti.com\n\nSpringtime Holding\nSpringtime Holding is a group of 3 companies that are involved in mobility. Springtime industrial design is a design consultancy with over 15 years experience in mobility and brand development. Bikedispenser is world\'s most compact and fully automatic bicycle storage and rental system. LEEV Mobility is the latest company in the group, developing and marketing light electric vehicles. LEEV‟s first product - the Mantys Golf - is an electric vehicle for the golf course. The Mantys will have its global launch this summer. We welcome you to visit us at the PICNIC Marketplace to discuss your mobility needs and ideas! www.springtime.nl\n\nMediamatic\nMediamatic is an art space and design lab based in Amsterdam. Mediamatic Lab develops connections between the virtual and the real world. Our projects include social networks and installations that encourage interaction, collaboration and knowledge sharing. We work for NTR, INNL, Puma, Amsterdam Museum, DOEN Foundation, Renault, Jewish Historical Museum, Pakhuis De Zwijger, ANP, Stadsherstel, Women Inc. and about fifty other organizations. Examples of our products include the ikPod: our prize-winning multimedia guide, the offline “check in” for Facebook Places and the physical “Like” button. Our sister organization Mediamatic Foundation organizes exhibitions, workshops, dev camps and lectures on new media, art, culture and society. Projects include El Hema: an Arabic department store, and the Expired Food Club: a protest against the demonization of expired, but irresistibly good food. Combined we are Mediamatic, sharing ideas, facilities and talent. www.mediamatic.nl\n\nDrain Products Europe B.V.\nWith years of experience, Drain Products Europe BV is the specialist in water treatment and management, and a leader in introducing innovative new products. Many of the now common products used for water treatment and management have been developed by Drain Products Europe. To stay at the forefront of our field, we work in close co-operation with engineering offices, commissioners, universities and research departments. www.drainproducts.nl\n\nCarmela Bogman\nThe Pop-Up is furniture for public spaces. Pop-Up is furniture that can be pumped out of the sidewalk by the inhabitants. After use, the Pop-Up it then deflated back into the sidewalk, creating a peaceful street scene without any obstacles. This means that the inhabitants have the freedom to decide for themselves when they want to use the Pop-Up and in which way. Several keys that give access to the pumping system are spread among different users of the furniture. Pop-Up blurs the boundaries between public and private. www.carmelabogman.nl\n\nGlobe4D\nThis interactive four-dimensional globe shows on a physical sphere how our planet changes over time. Globe4D can be viewed from all angles and can be controlled directly by rotating the sphere itself and turning the ring around the sphere. Globe4D introduces time as the fourth dimension for a globe. It shows animations about the earth\'s history and future, changing seasons, earthquakes, daylight changes, human migration and phenomena on other planets. These are just a few examples of the unlimited possibilities created by this interactive and tangible globe. Recently, a topography game and a visualization of live Twitter data were also developed. www.globe4d.com\n\ntheFactor.e\nOffer your visitors a rich interactive 3D experience of your products, services and stories! Sfeerz makes it possible to create attractive 3D applications quickly and easily, based on 360-degree panoramas or 360-degree videos. Sfeerz can be connected to the CMS of your website and be managed and maintained by yourself. Experience Sfeerz for yourself during PICNIC Festival 2011. Visit our stand for a free personal interactive “3D greetings from PICNIC card”. Please visit www.sfeerz.com for more information and http://virtueel.umcg.nl and http://opendaghanze.nl for inspirational cases. Sfeerz is an application from theFactor.e: www.tfe.nl\n\nGreen Olive/Greenlung\n“De groenten uit Amsterdam” will be the first indoor city farm in Western Europe. The veggies grow under ideal circumstances with LED lights in plant production units in empty office space and other buildings. The future of farming takes place in the cities and not on farmland. The cities are getting bigger and more densely populated and all those products need to be transported to the cities. Producing in the city means less transportation, fresh food and means less use of space through vertical production. So, de groenten uit Amsterdam is the future of farming. www.degroentenuitamsterdam.nl\n\nPhanta Vision\nPhanta Vision is a unique creative company. It‟s a cross-over of 3 independent organizations, located in a historical building in Amsterdam. We are specialists in Film productions, Film Editing and Audiovisual installations. We design and develop audio-visual solutions throughout the cultural sector. At PICNIC we will show one of our powerful projects. Creating an interactive installation in a small mobile theater, with live projection connected to sensors. “Magic in a nutshell” www.phantavision.com\n\nLiveNetLife International B.V.\nLiveNetLife is a service that allows you to set up connections between visitors of web pages. This is not new in itself; our innovation is that we do not request any direct link to connect users! So no email address, no FB friend connection or similar user information is needed – users don‟t even have to be on the same page or site. Our customers are websites that market products or services (we help sellers get more leads and higher hit rates), publishers (grow traffic and retention) and companies in general. The service is up and running on various websites and we have submitted a patent claim for our offering. www.livenetlife.com\n\nPavegen Systems\nImagine if every step you took generated electricity. Pavegen produces paving slabs that generate power from human footsteps. An unnoticeable 5mm of movement is enough to harvest the wasted kinetic energy and convert it into off-grid power. The electricity can either be collected in our storage system or be used instantly for interactive applications such as street lighting, advertising displays, bus stops and more. Pavegen is ideally used in high footfall locations such as shopping centers, transport hubs, supermarkets and sports stadiums. With an ever-expanding population this untapped resource allows for a localized solution for low power devices. www.pavegensystems.com\n\nMadLogic B.V.\nMadLogic develops innovative online advisory tools on the basis of serious gaming. The first strategic tool with which they intend to „gamify‟ consultancy is 3TGO. 3TGO is played digitally on a GO-inspired board with, on opposing sides, strategic and operational players who can visualize, analyze and optimize the structural DNA of their organization by making use of statements: http://www.youtube.com/user/madlogicbv. Consultants are provided with a FUNctional tool to help their clients achieve their ambitions or solve problems in any language at any place and time. 3TGO: How FUNctional are YOU? www.3tlogic.nl\n\nLightstorm Productions\nReplay My Day is a magic diary that tracks where you‟ve traveled in a day. Facebook and Twitter posts, appointments and photos you take will automatically pop up along the way. You can also add them yourself by dragging and dropping them onto the map. At the end of your day, press replay and relive your adventures. The longer you have Replay My Day, the richer it becomes: relive yesterday or that city trip several months ago, as a fast forwarded movie with you in the starring role. www.lightstorm.nl\n\nRoetz-Bikes\nRoetz-Bikes is a young brand with a mission. We believe that it is possible to provide robust, beautiful bicycles, while also reducing waste. Responsible bikes with a trendy look! More than one million bicycles are sold in the Netherlands every year. On the other hand, there are just as many bikes discarded. By reusing components of old bikes, we reduce the waste. In addition, for new parts we use natural materials as often as possible. For instance, Roetz-Bikes have wooden mudguards and cork handles. Roetz likes to make robust bikes. For all components we choose high quality brands that have proven themselves over the years. Finally, sheltered employment is an important element in creating our sustainable bike. www.roetz-bikes.nl\n\nDe Werff Architectuur\nChild Friendly Cities Families are one of the bearers of the new urbanity. How do you make a city child friendly? In the city is where we, De Werff Architectuur, work. On the urban level data is gathered and analyzed with others. For districts concepts are being developed in which the livability, children‟s development and the urban layout are the basis for the design of a safe, healthy, challenging and green environment. Within urban space the concepts are being tested and becoming part of new urban strategies that envision a healthy and livable city for all its inhabitants. www.dewerff.nl\n\nVliegende Varkens\nBehangrijk, a new way of standing out in the crowd. Behangrijk is a new product in the creative/exclusive wallpaper market. We create a unique design in which the customer can select which elements he want to customize -- for example a background color, pictures or ornaments. Our expert crew will then generate a personalized and unique wallpaper of excellent quality. Thanks to our personal approach, our quality of work and design we can distinguish ourselves in the world of interior design. We are also fully equipped to conceive a custommade design according to your desires. Everyone wants to be unique! www.vliegendevarkens.nl\n\nbuzzAR\nQRcode 3.0! buzzAR is a free smartphone app and a self-service “visual search platform”. With buzzAR the user can take a photo of an image (article, logo, ad or TV screen). buzzAR will send the photo to our server. The server analyzes the photo to find a match within the platform. If there is a match, the server returns a list of results. The list can contain a variety of actions: a link to a website, PDF, video, audio, navigation, direct calling, e-mail, text, nearest locations and Augmented Reality. buzzAR is a solution to connect offline expressions to information. www.buzzar.net\n\nKenlog B.V.\nwww.kenlog.nl\n\nFourceLabs\nFourceLabs designs playful experiences for the public spaces to grab attention and influence the way people feel and behave. We combine interaction and game design to deliver creative and imaginative solutions, highly bespoke and focused on our clients and their target audience. We will be showing our product Friends at the PICNIC Marketplace. Friends is a playful, physical and social platform for urban, professional and healthcare settings. It\'s a collective digital pet that everyone can see and interact with and which in both a literal and figurative sense brings color into a location. We would love to speak to you about Friends or our other services. See you at The Marketplace! www.fourcelabs.com\n\nSecuReceipt\nSR//Expenses is an expense management solution. It lowers transaction and processing costs, saves time and space, is easy to manage and allows for direct synchronization with your accounting software (e.g. Exact, SAP or Twinfield). SR//Expenses is accessible worldwide through your smartphone or web browser. Receipts and expense reports are stored on our secure servers, eliminating the need to save your paper receipts in many countries. With mobile applications for iPhone, iPad, Android and BlackBerry anyone can process receipts anywhere. www.srexpenses.com\n\nInqubative\nCities are changing at a fast pace and so is the media landscape. Governments and companies are constantly looking for innovative means of communication to reach today\'s population and consumers. That\'s why Inqubative presents BrandScreen. BrandScreen is a video display screen in the shape of a logo or icon. It combines technology with aesthetics and hig- end design and offers companies and (local) government a chance to link their logo to core value-based visuals (information, art, mood, commercials). BrandScreen is a perfect city marketing tool. The I amsterdam logo would transform into an interactive communication platform for citizens, artists and tourists (social media, uploads, mobile phones). This way the BrandScreen concept brings citizens, companies, politics and communities closer together. www.inqubative.com\n\nNegotica Development Projects\nUrban Futures & the power of the Brain The main concept behind the technology of Negotica is making it possible to connect all electrical devices through one open system. So why not imagine a urban future where you can control every electrical device with your brain? Negotica Development Projects, with a focus on the field of Brain-Computer Interface technology, has created Carebro. We have a solution to control our living environment by means of the human brain and as a result we entered the Dutch MKB Innovation Top 100. Coming from green building technology our aim is to help people improve in self-care and independence. Additional advantages are reduced energy costs, reduced operating costs, more intelligence and improvement of the living comfort. www.negotica.net\n\nPraktijk voor Industrieel Ontwerp\nOur industrial design practice helps companies and entrepreneurs to conceptualize and develop physical products. For series and mass production, from sketch to realization. We aim for sustainable results derived from clear concepts that add value for both users and businesses. Currently we are working on functional human-centered LED applications. A fascinating technology because of the endless possibilities in form, color and function in addition to the reduced energy consumption. At PICNIC we will present a LED light application that is based on The New Way of Working. We will show how light solutions can have a positive effect on modern day living and working. www.praktijk.io\n\nAnneke Jakobs\nAnneke Jakobs unravels existing products. With her findings she designs unusual, interactive projects that reveal information about the construction and origin of the product. By exposing such insights she wants to stimulate consumers to think about our industrialized environment. With her projects she tries to build a bridge between consumers and industry. At the Marketplace she will present her Mobile Ice Cream Workshop. The visitors are the ice cream machine themselves. Without electricity. And the composition of the ingredients depends on the environment and the season. www.annekejakobs.nl\n\nMCW Studio\'s\nMCW Studio‟s is an innovative multimedia studio with 5 separate disciplines: AV and Film Audio and Sound Interactive multimedia Internet 3D visualization and animation Over the past 17 years we have developed various innovative and interactive productions. We always look for the perfect integration of different forms of media, resulting in productions that aim to meet and exceed the goals of the client. A perfect example is a game we developed in which two players have to work together to run a factory. Both players need to use both hands and multiple fingers at the same time to get the best results. www.mcw.nl\n\nTwnkls augmented reality\ntwnkls | augmented reality is a full-service AR bureau that focuses on the creation, development, production and implementation of mobile AR applications. Our clients come from sectors edutainment, marketing & branding, construction and industrial sectors. twnkls is creative and innovative, and has extensive technical knowledge and experience in the area of Augmented Reality projects. At twnkls experienced specialists are working together on new location and image-based recognition technologies that result in new forms of interaction, user experience and business concepts.\n\nwww.twnkls.com\n\nMangrove\nSeachange is working in collaboration with Mangrove on the development of an iPad application for cable operators. The app combines the power of the back office software Seachange (Adrenalin) and current social media applications. Cable subscribers get access to premium video content on demand, an electronic program guide, and – in the near future – even a live television option. The app takes over the traditional remote control functions and makes large movie catalogs easily accessible. The app transforms the iPad into an extra TV screen and creates a social TV experience through smart integration with platforms like Twitter and Facebook. This application provides subscribers more value while watching television, such as additional content, virtual parties and intelligent social recommendations. For cable providers, the application offers a platform for targeted marketing campaigns around video on demand and linear broadcast. www.mangrove.nl\n\nEvident Interactive B.V.\nUrban Nature is about sharing our experience in providing access to nature; nature that is never far away from the shadows of the Dutch cities. The success of two recent concepts for Staatsbosbeheer proves that the urban species of man can be seduced by the pure and true inspiration of nature. Volgdevos.nl: a real life soap about a family of Foxes was visited 2.2 million times in 3 months. The Naar Buiten iPhone app to find nature close by has been downloaded more than 25,000 times. Inspired and powered by Evident Interactive. www.evident.nl\n\nWAACS Design & Consultancy\nWAACS Design & Consultancy is a professional and well-known design studio based in Rotterdam, specializing in product innovation and UX design (user experience). Our projects for multinationals like Sara Lee/DE, Microsoft, Medisana, G24 Innovations, ATAG, Alessi, Henkel/Pritt, H.J.Heinz, and Indesit prove that our way of working combines very well with internal R&D and marketing departments as well as large international target groups. Our best known product is the Philips Senseo that we designed with Sara Lee and later with Philips. www.waacs.com\n\nUrban Bike Concepts BV\nBeixo designs bikes that go beyond all traditions. First of all we use a shaft drive in stead of the old fashioned chain. Then the design: we put the usage and the user first without losing our sense of style. In the design of the new beixo GO, a 16-inch folding bike, we have looked at the needs of our users. The result is a super fast, foldable, easy to carry bike with a great look. www.urbanbikeconcepts.com\n\nFONKmobile\nAmsterdam-based FONKmobile is a digital agency that specializes in conceptualizing and developing mobile applications. Besides custom-made apps for a variety of clients, FONKmobile developed a number of mobile products: with the Automatic Book Compiler, artist and illustrator Bob Takens has a convenient tool to generate iPad apps for the children books he and Joke van Leeuwen create. Referred to as Mobile Efficiency, FONKmobile developed applications to speed up business processes using smartphones. We allow sales people to access all necessary product information (including stock) and created a tool to simplify B2B ordering in catering and retail. www.fonkmobile.nl\n\nVeeel ontwerpers\nVeeel Ontwerpers develops innovative products for leading brands and companies. Co-creation with designers is our specialty, innovation is our goal. We select the best designers for each project by using Designrider ™, our online platform consisting of over 1350 professional designers. We facilitate a solution-based process. Starting with a clear strategy, we develop concepts and optimize these to a produce-able design. Co-creation with designers means letting individual designers work together on problems, generating out-of-the-box insights, inspiration and a feasible solution. The combination of scalable creative skills and technical knowledge makes us the ideal partner for innovation. www.veeel.com\n\nOne-o-Niners\nFinding a voiceover in just 4 easy steps and knowing straightaway what it is going to cost you… Quite impossible, until now. Voiceover agency Voicebooking.com facilitates this process by setting up their website just like a web shop. Most voiceover agencies offer the customer such an extensive database of voices that it is impossible to keep track. Voicebooking.com has made a selection for you. It offers selected groups of professional voiceovers in several languages. Like every web shop, Voicebooking.com offers you additional services like scriptwriting, and mixing your production. Above all, we are able to work cost effectively because all our voices work from their own recording studios. www.voicebooking.com\n\nRanj\nTeacher in a Box – Learn how to write with a game A strong education in writing gives children a head start with respect to language development, reading comprehension and fine motor skills. Unfortunately the primary school curriculum fails to address this need. How can you make sure that children spend a lot of time practicing the necessary movements? By making it fun! Juf in a Box approaches writing lessons in a playful and educational way by combining the challenge, feedback and fun of games with an adaptive teaching method. The method is used by both physical therapists and teachers. www.ranj.com/nl\n\nButterflyworks\nGetH20 is a serious game that simulates the complexity of life in the slums, the scarcity of resources, how to deal with them and ultimately, how to prevent escalation of conflict. Around the world 1 billion people live in informal settlements and their numbers are growing as migration to cities increases. Butterfly Works and youth from Kenya have co-created a mobile app and a board game that deal with the themes of water scarcity, corruption, crime and community development. The aim of the game is to build houses and grow the water source, while maintaining a stable and happy community. By playing the game users become aware of the daily challenges in slums and gain insights into how these problems can be tackled in the real world. The game is currently soft launched in Kenya, is due for full launch in Uganda, and has proven to be unexpectedly popular in Saudi Arabia. The android version is in development and in 2012 we will expand the game with virtual goods that will translate into community projects with slum dwellers in the real world. www.geth20game.com www.butterflyworks.org\n\nCrafting Peace\nCrafting Peace is a design label and philosophy that uses crafts as a means to expand compassion in the world: stitch-by-stitch, bead-by-bead, color-by-color. Our approach is to co-create design products with craftsmen in developing countries. On the one hand, crafting is a method of tapping into someone‟s (often undiscovered) potential using hand, head and heart. But on the other hand crafting – however graceful, authentic and artistic it may appear – simply means putting bread on the table in some parts of our world. The design label Crafting Peace was established to create a new approach towards crafts and trade with developing countries. www.craftingpeace.com\n\nRoamler\nRoamler is a mobile workforce that lets businesses, brands and governments get their tasks done by enthusiastic Roamlers. A task can mapping a playground, reporting dangerous intersections or broken traffic signs, or even helping decide where a new bike rack is needed. Besides these examples, more commercial or creative assignments are possible as well. By performing these tasks, Roamlers earn money and experience points. The more experience points a Roamler earns, the more complex jobs he or she will get. www.roamler.com\n\nSense-os\nSense creates context awareness by combining and interpreting sensor data. For this purpose, we use sensors that are commonly and/or publicly available, such as sensors in smartphones, or Open Data. Context aware systems are capable of providing meaningful information to users, or pro-actively support users with services based on the personal context of the user. Furthermore, we aggregate personal context on a group level, to be used by others. Our solution can be applied in health care, mobility, energy management and smart cities. www.sense-os.nl\n\nCityconcept\nOur Little Utopia Back in those days when you were a child, you would draw your ideal house for you and your loved ones. Now, being grown up brings new wishes and needs in a fast-moving world. Nowadays we have to rediscover our ideal home and its environment. If we want to achieve our goals, we have to find new ways of (re)developing houses and real estate. CITYCONCEPT is creating an online community that matches people with similar desires and needs. We are using matching principles of online dating to allow like-minded people to group around shared housing needs. Together they find a location and design & develop their ideal home. We believe this type of co-creation leads to greater involvement and responsibility of people within their community in the city. www.cityconcept.nl\n\nA New Spring B.V.\nA New Spring: Technology that will personally help you study Today\'s e-learning can be compared to traditional maps. There might be an indicated route, but you still have to find your own way. In our vision the next generation e-learning should be more like navigation software. You set a personal goal and the platform will continuously make sure you stay on track by suggesting you directions. When you encounter obstacles the route will adjust to you. The result is a personalized learning experience that is more efficient. We believe internet technology can personally help students with their education. www.anewspring.com/platform-tour\n\nShapers\nAt Shapers we believe that learning can be both fun and effective. We design learning experiences that help organizations like schools, companies and museums to get the best out of people, by giving them more enjoyment and greater learning efficiency. A learning experience is best described as a process. Various factors such as people, learning objectives and different types of media play a role in that process. Using these elements we create a tailor-made solution for a logical and meaningful learning experience. www.shapers.nl\n\nTribe of Noise B.V.\nTribe of Noise is an online music community connecting artists and business. Artists remain 100% in control, but are empowered by our tools, legal framework and global community to gain exposure and secure music deals worldwide. We believe that non-exclusive and transparent business models are crucial for the future of the digital content industry. We are now gaining momentum in the advertisement, video gaming, video production, mobile app development and narrow-casting industry. From now on, if you need great music for commercial projects: Tribeofnoise.com is your #1 online resource. Let\'s make some Noise! www.tribeofnoise.com\n\n');
