INSERT INTO `members` VALUES (1,'si@yoomee.com','si','olive123','Si','Wilkins',1,'','I am a Ruby on Rails developer for Yoomee, a great web development agency based in Sheffield, UK. I helped create this website.','2011-04-28 11:18:54','2011-08-16 17:51:39','2011/06/01/02_03_37_696_IMG_6807_1.jpg',0,0,'77.86.30.132','537473622',14265787,14,'web development skills, music and reflections.','5arWR0bjfN','siwilkins',NULL,'14265787-wOscQ26TiHpSVoMgSf2z5Pchxcb1zDy7CrvV0bfvU','PVCTD3txKuQpUEdVu6zqBkFStEbJNLsbplo31GfM',0,'bf6b078f-bd6d-4a6b-91fb-94daafdb0a22','942012b7-9f46-4563-a53a-037505bf5432','http://www.linkedin.com/pub/si-wilkins/19/291/a36',0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2,'andy@yoomee.com','andy','olive123','Andy','Mayer',1,'Yoomee','I\'m the founder of <a href=\"http://www.yoomee.com\" target=\"_new\">Yoomee</a>. We create bespoke social networks, tools and apps for online communities using Agile/Lean principles. We\'re helping PICNIC build this website - starting with a simple beta, and then continuously improving based on your feedback.\n\nAt Yoomee, we specialise in building social web technologies for social good. Typical projects involve creative ways of connecting people together online, solving specific problems that bring about positive social outcomes in the real-world. We work with nonprofit, social entrepreneurs, charity, third sector and advocacy groups to create bespoke custom social networking websites and social media tools.\n\nFeel free to get in touch if you have any questions about this site, or want to discuss developing a similar project. If you\'d like to find out more about what we do at <a href=\"http://www.yoomee.com\" target=\"_new\">Yoomee</a>, then please check out our website at <a href=\"http://www.yoomee.com\" target=\"_new\">yoomee.com</a>.\n\nWhen I am not doing Yoomee, then I am busy being a father, husband, petrolhead, Arduino and fencing fan - touché!','2011-04-28 06:18:54','2011-08-24 17:05:45','2011/05/05/06_35_05_970_IMG_0055.JPG',1,0,'77.86.30.132','747785309',14701791,139,'you and me together online; Yoomee','xldlPUCLQB','andymayer',NULL,'14701791-y62zfHeAiezSd5q65hwBlvYshYSI2K2V201baYbxM','taIv480Qt4PiwbMzkipQF7wh0FHPjLGwsbSPnY9GIg',0,NULL,NULL,'http://uk.linkedin.com/in/yoomee',0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4,'rich@yoomee.com','rich','olive123','Rich','Wells',1,'','I\'m the lead designer at Yoomee, an agile web agency in the UK. I helped to create this site (which is still a work in progress so go easy on me!)','2011-04-28 10:18:54','2011-07-22 07:12:41','2011/05/20/10_04_12_815_lomo_0.06.53.09_.jpg',0,0,'77.86.30.132','632136536',14713297,35,'drawing skills, and a passion for creating engaging user experiences.',NULL,'richwells',NULL,'14713297-f3NvVY2pWUglJYpHVPcv259GqNOkKkPAmdTALk2RI','ugOUKbT7tkiIMpibyUMW39XHCSRtVzqIz9kI0Q0pxE',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(5,'ian@yoomee.com','ian','olive123','Ian','Mooney',1,'','I\'m a web developer from Sheffield. I work for a company called Yoomee and helped make this site awesome.','2011-04-28 09:18:54','2011-07-15 14:13:55',NULL,0,0,'77.86.30.132','61102010',19117562,14,'a lovely mop of ginger hair.','5OLA9xcrVI','ianmooney',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'http://uk.linkedin.com/pub/ian-mooney/29/85a/aa9',0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(7,'matt@yoomee.com','matt','olive123','Matt','Atkins',1,'','Sheffield-based web developer, musician and tea-drinker.','2011-04-28 11:18:54','2011-08-24 10:05:50','2011/05/31/01_48_50_736_matt_squarebw.png',1,0,'77.86.30.132','286103766',18734348,34,'developer skillz','O05vUjvOun','matkins',NULL,'18734348-7wSsilt3HqI9B3RBbtRrrBa1EfPlmB59jltDBJck','Eqs1Nj6yuw8mygUBvFNtcI2X70AMeK7gSU7mcw',0,'3c6967ab-d743-407f-ae7b-1399fa313365','12018bb7-759c-4392-9ea3-32b2b40f53ac','http://www.linkedin.com/pub/matthew-atkins/15/a45/b39',0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(9,'stikker@waag.org','','PICNIC11','Marleen','Stikker',0,'PICNIC','“Since technology defines our culture, culture should define our technology” is Marleen Stikker’s credo.\r\n\r\nAfter reading Philosophy in Amsterdam, Stikker (1962) was the founder of De Digitale Stad (The Digital City) in 1994, the first virtual community introducing free public access to the internet.\r\nSoon she co-founded the “Society of Old and New Media”, now Waag Society, Institute for Art, Science and Technology. Waag Society actively developes creative technology for social innovation through R&D projects with leading international partners.\r\nAs CEO of Waag Society she launched succesful products as the Storytable for the elderly and the Museum App, enabling every citizen to remain part of the mediatized society.\r\n\r\nTogether with Bas Verhart (Media Republic) she created PICNIC, the leading European event for the creative industries, an innovation platform hosted yearly in Amsterdam.\r\n\r\nIn 2007 Marleen Stikker  initiated the ICT Innovation Platform Creative Industries (IIPcreate) which aims to bring together science, industry and the creative sector to formulate a strategic research agenda.\r\nStikker is a member of the  Board of Directors at WPG Publishers, an independent publishing group. She continues to advocate her message of \"inclusion through technology\" around the world.','2011-05-05 09:11:46','2011-08-24 12:30:05','2011/05/05/03_10_27_315_screen_capture_37.png',0,0,'213.84.156.209','1119185503',NULL,39,'social innovation and a sixth sense for what’s next.',NULL,NULL,'Chair PICNIC, CEO Waag Society',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(10,'Bas@mediarepublic.com','','PICNIC11','Bas','Verhart',0,'PICNIC','I\'m a co-founder of PICNIC as well as co-founder & CEO of Media Republic, a leading digital media and entertainment company based in Amsterdam.\r\n\r\nI\'m a passionate entrepreneur and always on the lookout for the next big idea. I\'m currently a board member at Trendwatching.com and Eccky.com, and am busy with a new project seeking innovation in education.\r\n\r\n','2011-05-05 09:11:46','2011-07-14 19:36:27','2011/05/05/03_21_07_218_screen_capture_38.png',0,0,NULL,'',NULL,12,'the spirit of entrepreneurship and killer guitar riffs.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(11,'kitty@picnicnetwork.org','','kitty','Kitty','Leering',1,'PICNIC','I\'m the Program Director & interim General Manager of PICNIC. \n\nI have been involved with PICNIC from the very start. I have been responsible for project management of the whole Festival in 2006 and 2007. In 2008 I got more involved with the programming of the Specials and the Labs. As of 2009 I have been responsible for all of the PICNIC Festival programming. \n\nIn addition I develop, program, give advise on and manage professional events on a freelance basis (DutchBlend). I mostly work on events that focus on the crossroads between creativity, (media)technology, business and governance. A few examples of events that I have been working on are SpinAwards, ICT Delta, Mediapark Jaarcongres, Dutch Bloggies and TEDxWomen (as a volunteer project manager). \n\nUntil 2005 I worked as the Event Director Benelux for IT-research firm IDC, building their regional event business from the ground up. At Media Plaza (1997-2002) I got acquainted with the world of internet, ICT and new media. ','2011-05-05 09:11:46','2011-08-24 15:33:35','2011/08/04/12_45_43_489_Photo_on_2011_08_04_at_21.30.jpg',1,0,'95.97.39.198','100000000380345',6235172,204,'you urban future scenarios and gourmet cooking skills.','q6KCLDkLiM','KittyLeering',NULL,'6235172-anhrPj4l7QpqCusDyL75Pyz7bXqa4CAcIPFf1lrCaU','vbBbVdZGYIf5fyfTQgWJaacWAVPdZGrHzV5ReImFU',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(12,'Annemarie@picnicnetwork.org','','PICNIC11','Annemarie','van Asselen',0,'PICNIC','I\'m the Director of Sponsoring & Partnerships at PICNIC.\r\n','2011-05-05 09:11:47','2011-08-10 09:06:44','2011/06/07/04_40_00_488_AK_reunie.jpg',0,0,'87.210.12.170','',NULL,27,'you a passion for building relationships and capturing memories on film.','qra3l8_JWB',NULL,'Director Sponsoring & Partnerships',NULL,NULL,0,'3f06ad25-e0c8-484f-b78d-00a89ed14697','f96bfa4e-d873-4add-b354-db4e4ce06396','http://www.linkedin.com/pub/annemarie-van-asselen/0/54b/baa',0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(16,'juha@non-fiction.nl','','PICNIC11','Juha','van ‘t Zelfde',0,'Viral Radio','Co-founder, Non-fiction\n\nAs researcher, developer and radical user in the converging domains of art, heritage, network technology and urbanism, Juha works as a middleman between those who oversee the past and those who invent the future. With Michiel van Iersel he founded Non-fiction, an Amsterdam-based interdisciplinary innovation agency working at the intersection of the arts, heritage, network technology and urban development. Non-fiction works with the Stedelijk Museum, Stadsherstel and the Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra, among other organizations.\n\nWith Ben Cerveny and James Burke, Juha co-founded VURB, a European framework for policy and design research concerning urban computational systems. The VURB foundation provides direction and resources to a portfolio of projects investigating how our cultures might come to use networked digital resources to change the way we understand, build, and inhabit cities.\n\nLastly, Juha founded Viral Radio, a vehicle for discovery and distribution of electronic music. Viral Radio sets up site-specific performances for festivals and music venues in Europe, displaying new developments in computer music exploration and hyperrhythmic dance music. It works with Exit Festival, Appelsap, North Sea Jazz Festival, Bimhuis and more.','2011-05-05 09:14:54','2011-08-21 12:45:00','2011/05/24/03_13_31_380_screen_capture_2.png',1,0,'82.157.242.48','725890240',NULL,37,'a museum, a moustached futurist, a Moon artist, a festival-within-the-festival, the city & the city.',NULL,NULL,'Co-founder, Non-fiction',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,1,1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL),(33,'todd@picnicnetwork.org','todd','hamper123','Todd','Savage',1,'Marketing Manager','I\'m the Marketin