3:10:46','2011-08-18 14:00:03','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-05-23 12:10:00',1,NULL,0,'Air France KLM Global Meetings Information',0),(80,27,'Answer PICNIC’s call to REDESIGN THE WORLD',NULL,'<p>\r\n	HeadsUp! 2011, along with PICNIC, has brought together an extraordinary group of advisors from the worlds of design, communication, data visualization and climate science to forge a unique competition: a challenge to international designers to transform climate data into an interactive animated digital display &ndash; a &ldquo;heads up display&rdquo; for the planet.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Slides of the session are available here.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Communication of climate trends is a difficult problem uniquely suited to designers: crafting clear messages of unfamiliar substances at unimaginable scales into recognizable and actionable news. Advances in data visualization, the embrace of social networks and mobile platforms coupled with virtual and augmented realities offer new opportunities to create a shared sign in the public square.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	And not just any public square....</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	TIMES SQUARE !</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Today HeadsUp! 2011 and PICNIC are thrilled to announce the participation</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	of Thomson Reuters in providing an extraordinary venue for the competition.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The winning entries to the HeadsUp! 2011 Design Challenge will be awarded display time on TS2, Times Square Squared, a Reuters / NASDAQ Alliance. TS2, comprising both the NASDAQ and Reuters displays commands over 19,000 square feet of digital signboards over 21 stories high. 1,5 million people a day passing through Times Square, looking up: What will you post there?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	TS2 live webcam</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	September 2010 - LAUNCH</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	January 2011 - COMPETITION OPENS</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	MAY 2011 - FINALISTS CHOSEN</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	JUNE 2011 - DISPLAY TIME ON TS2</p>\r\n','2011-05-24 12:22:55','2011-08-18 14:00:03','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-05-24 11:21:00',1,19,0,'HeadsUp!',0),(81,1,'PICNIC in Beta','<p>\r\n	We are currently in beta - which means we&#39;ve released our new online platform before it&#39;s finished.&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Why did we do that? The answer is simple. We want to get feedback from you, our community, during the development process rather than afterwards.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	And we sincerely appreciate your constructive comments! So don&#39;t be shy and tell us what you think! Than we&#39;ll build our new online platform together.</p>\r\n','2011-05-27 15:35:50','2011-08-18 14:00:03','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-05-27 14:34:00',1,27,7,'Beta',0),(89,4,'Festival History','<p>\r\n	In 2006, Bas Verhart (founder of Media Republic) joined forces with Marleen Stikker (founder and CEO of Waag Society) to develop a new platform for creativity and innovation in Amsterdam.&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	They wanted to bring together the world&rsquo;s top creative and business professionals to develop new partnerships and opportunities. Supported by their network of friends, collaborators and admirers, including former Amsterdam Mayor Job Cohen, PICNIC was born. The first edition of PICNIC was launched in September 2006.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Whether you&#39;re a veteran or first-timer, dive into our visual archives documenting past PICNIC festivals to enjoy both images at <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/crossmediaweek/sets/72157624988417397/\" target=\"_blank\">Flickr</a> and some of our <a href=\"http://www.vimeo.com/picnic\" target=\"_blank\">PICNIC speakers at Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Looking for more history? Explore the speakers and program from <a href=\"http://archive.picnicnetwork.org/page/40961/en\" target=\"_blank\">past PICNIC festivals</a>.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>\r\n	What did everyone bring to PICNIC &#39;10?</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://www.vimeo.com/16245565</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Reinier de Graaf on&nbsp;Urban Paradigm Shifts</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://www.vimeo.com/16107033</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Dennis Crowley, Foursquare founder, on Social Cities</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://www.vimeo.com/17756354</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Aza Raskin on Redesigning Memories</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://www.vimeo.com/16729734</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Evan Ratliff of Wired Magazine on Vanishing in the Digital Age</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://vimeo.com/15732565</p>\r\n','2011-05-27 20:12:42','2011-08-24 14:17:23','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-05-27 19:12:00',1,6,8,'Festival History',0),(91,15,'Out of town visitors','<p>\r\n	PICNIC Festival attracts some of the world&#39;s most creative and innovative minds. We&#39;ve arranged special rates on airfare and hotels.</p>\r\n','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Book one of the three festival hotels <a href=\"/travel-and-accommodations\" target=\"_blank\">before 1 July</a> for special savings, including the brand-new Mint Hotel.</h5>\r\n','2011-05-27 22:43:21','2011-08-18 14:00:04','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-05-27 21:43:21',1,140,0,'Hotel and travel info ',0),(93,15,'Early Bird registration is open!','','<p>\r\n	Yay! PICNIC Early Bird Registration is open. Make sure you profit from our spectacular early bird offer and <a href=\"/festival-registration\" target=\"_blank\">buy a ticket now</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This year&#39;s PICNIC Festival will take place between 14 and 16 September, of course in beautiful Amsterdam. We&#39;d love to welcome you, so join us.</p>\r\n','2011-05-27 23:20:12','2011-08-18 14:00:04','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-01 04:00:00',1,38,0,'Registration starts today',0),(94,1,'Contributors',NULL,'<p>\r\n	We are proud to have so many creative minds in the PICNIC community that we can call our friends. Not only do they have great ideas to make PICNIC an even better and more beautiful platform, they also help us to realize all of our crazy plans. And we love them for that! Big time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2011-05-29 16:56:24','2011-08-18 14:00:04','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-05-29 15:56:00',1,NULL,4,'',0),(96,31,'Nationale Postcode Lotterij','','<p>\r\n	The <strong>Dutch Postcode Lottery</strong> (Nationale Postcode Loterij) is a charitable organization focused on supporting organizations working to create a more just and green world through fundraising and increasing public awareness with the help of a lottery.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It&#39;s Holland&rsquo;s biggest and most popular charitable lottery and it supports 75 charity organizations UNICEF, Greenpeace, WWF, IUCN and the Clinton Foundation. In 2009, the lottery allocated 256 million euros to its beneficiaries.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><a href=\"http://www.postcodeloterij.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.postcodeloterij.nl</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<strong>Postcode Lottery Green Challenge 2011</strong></h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Green Challenge 2011 calls on creative, innovative minds to come up with concrete solutions to fight climate change. Anyone with a good idea for a product or service that reduces greenhouse gas emissions in a consumer-friendly way and contributes to a sustainable lifestyle is welcome to take part. Together with PICNIC, the Dutch Postcode Lottery started this initiative in 2007. The winner receives 500,000 euro from the Postcode Lottery to execute their plan.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.greenchallenge.info\" target=\"_blank\">www.greenchallenge.info</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 09:19:32','2011-08-18 14:00:04','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-01 08:14:00',1,225,0,'Nationale Postcode Lotterij',0),(97,31,'Vodafone','','<p>\r\n	<strong>Vodafone</strong> is one of the largest mobile communications companies in the Netherlands and is part of the Vodafone Group, the world&rsquo;s leading mobile telecommunications group. Vodafone Netherlands has a customer base of 4.4 million customers. It has a Head Offices in both Maastricht and Amsterdam. Almost 3000 employees work with Vodafone Netherlands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Vodafone is dedicated to providing the best products and services for the ever-innovative mobile telecoms market. Their goal is to provide the best accessibility and connectivity worldwide, for the best possible price. Their passionate and talented employees help keep Vodafone at the leading edge of their market.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more information visit: <a href=\"http://www.vodafone.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.vodafone.nl</a></p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Vodafone Mobile Clicks 2011</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em>With Vodafone Mobile Clicks we provide a stage for young innovative mobile internet start ups to accelerate their ideas and support them in making their next step in the mobile market.</em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Vodafone Mobile Clicks</strong> is an international contest to identify and develop the best, most innovative mobile internet start-ups. Announced at The Next Web Conference in Amsterdam, the closing date for entries is midnight CET on 12th June, 2011.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Already known as the biggest start-up competition of its kind, this year&rsquo;s Vodafone Mobile Clicks is open to seven markets. Any start-up in Germany, the Netherlands, Portugal, the Republic of Ireland, Spain, Turkey or the United Kingdom that has a mobile site, service or application can compete for the <strong>&euro;225,000</strong> prize fund.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Judging will take place over three rounds. Firstly, each competing market will draw up a shortlist of their five best submissions, then a local winner will be selected. Lastly, all seven local winners will be invited to represent their country in a live final at the PICNIC festival in the Netherlands on 15th &ndash; 16th September 2011, where the overall winner will be chosen.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This year&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://developer.vodafone.com/mobileclicks2011/jury-bios/\" target=\"_blank\">high-profile judges</a> include Rudy de Waele, founder of Mobile 2.0 Europe and dotopen; Peter Barry, Head of VC and Start-up at Vodafone Ventures; Paul Jozefak, Managing Partner at Mobile VC; Reshma Sohoni, Partner at Seedcamp, and Lee Epting, Director of Content Services at Vodafone Group. Each judge will score entries based on five criteria:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Originality, creativity and innovativeness</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Technical and operational feasibility</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Economic and financial viability</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Value to end-users</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The quality of the management team (e.g. their experience, knowledge, skills, relationships)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	This is a fantastic opportunity to gain expert feedback for your entry, both qualitatively and quantitatively from all of the jury members. And if your entry reaches the finals, then you&rsquo;ll also benefit from our extensive PR and coverage.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you have the inspiration and desire to be the best, then <a href=\"https://id.developer.vodafone.com/user/signin/?next=/authenticate/%3Fopenid.claimed_id%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fspecs.openid.net%252Fauth%252F2.0%252Fidentifier_select%26openid.identity%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fspecs.openid.net%252Fauth%252F2.0%252Fidentifier_select%26openid.assoc_handle%3D%257BHMAC-SHA256%257D%257B4de5ec95%257D%257B%252F9pBdA%253D%253D%257D%26openid.return_to%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fsubmit.vodafonemobileclicks.com%252Fdesktopmodules%252Fauthenticationservices%252Fvodafoneopenid%252Fentrypage.aspx%253Fdnoa.userSuppliedIdentifier%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fid.developer.vodafone.com%25252Fauthenticate%26openid.realm%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fsubmit.vodafonemobileclicks.com%252F%26openid.mode%3Dcheckid_setup%26openid.ns%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fspecs.openid.net%252Fauth%252F2.0%26openid.ns.alias3%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fopenid.net%252Fsrv%252Fax%252F1.0%26openid.alias3.required%3Dalias1%252Calias2%252Calias3%252Calias4%252Calias5%252Calias6%252Calias7%252Calias8%26openid.alias3.mode%3Dfetch_request%26openid.alias3.type.alias1%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252Fcontact%252Femail%26openid.alias3.count.alias1%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias2%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252FnamePerson%26openid.alias3.count.alias2%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias3%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252FnamePerson%252Ffriendly%26openid.alias3.count.alias3%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias4%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252FnamePerson%252Ffirst%26openid.alias3.count.alias4%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias5%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252FnamePerson%252Flast%26openid.alias3.count.alias5%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias6%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252Fcontact%252Fphone%252Fdefault%26openid.alias3.count.alias6%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias7%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252Fcompany%252Fname%26openid.alias3.count.alias7%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias8%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252Fcontact%252Fweb%252Fdefault%26openid.alias3.count.alias8%3D1\" target=\"_blank\">enter today!</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 10:17:46','2011-08-18 14:00:04','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-01 09:17:00',1,229,1,'',0),(98,32,'UPC',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<em>Our products are used to communicate, interact, be entertained, seek information, share content and help the consumer understand the world around them.</em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Cable and media firm <strong>UPC</strong> is one of the leading providers of television, broadband internet, and telephone services in the Netherlands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	UPC provides 2 million households with digital or analog television. As of 31 March 2010, UPC supplied 772,000 households with broadband internet and had 654,000 subscribers for digital telephone services.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	UPC is a consolidated subsidiary of Liberty Global, Inc. (NASDAQ: LBTYA, LBTYB, LBTYK). Liberty Global delivers television, broadband internet and telephone services to 10 million customers in eleven European countries.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more info visit: <a href=\"http://www.upc.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.upc.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 10:50:34','2011-08-18 14:00:04','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-01 09:50:00',1,223,2,'',0),(99,32,'Chamber of Commerce','','<p>\r\n	The Dutch Chamber of Commerce (Kamer van Koophandel) manages the trade register of all businesses in the Netherlands. The Chamber of Commerce for Amsterdam, the regional representative organization for the private business sector, is the country&#39;s largest Chamber with over 200.000 companies on its register.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Chamber takes all steps within its power to maintain and stimulate the robust economic health of the Amsterdam region. The Chamber accumulated knowledge, contacts and partnerships makes it the essential reference point for every firm doing or seeking to do business in the Amsterdam region. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.kvk.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.kvk.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 10:58:59','2011-08-18 14:00:04','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-01 09:58:00',1,232,4,'',0),(100,32,'RTL',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>RTL Nederland</strong> is an all round media company and nationwide market leader with four television stations (RTL 4, RTL 5, RTL 7, RTL 8), the digital channel RTL Lounge and the number one Dutch radio station Radio 538.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	RTL Nederland entertains and informs a broad audience 24/7 on all relevant platforms. RTL Nederland&#39;s channels offer a wide variety of Dutch and foreign films, series and shows, including popular formats such as RTL Boulevard and RTL News. With its leadership in the Dutch television and radio markets and its expanding role in digital media with for example RTL.nl and RTL Gemist (TV shows online), RTL Nederland is one of Holland&#39;s leading media companies.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	RTL Nederland is a subsidiary company of RTL Group and part of the international Bertelsmann organization.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.rtlnederland.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.rtlnederland.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 11:07:23','2011-08-18 14:00:05','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-01 10:07:00',1,224,3,'',0),(101,32,'SII','','<p>\r\n	<em>SII is involved in a large number of service innovation projects which are of interest of people who want to be updated about the latest ICT developments in relation to cutting edge innovative services.</em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The goal of the innovation program <strong>Service Innovation &amp; IC</strong>T (SII) is to make the Netherlands the European hub for content services and the European centre of excellence for financial logistics. The program SII has started by the Dutch ministry of Economic Affairs in January 2010 and the first phase of SII will run till end 2011. The government has provided a subsidy for the first phase of 12.5 million euro. The program consists of a number subprograms such as the Infrastructure Program, the TOP Program and the Tender Program. The SII office will also execute the subprogram Knowledge Dissemination and Value Acceleration.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The main subjects in the Tender Program are content, connectedness, e-lifestyle, e-invoicing and e-payments. SII focuses on service innovation realized by consortia of co-operating companies and institutions representing large companies, SME&rsquo;s en knowledge institutes. SII stimulates the growth o ecosystem that will secure the growth of the knowledge intensive service industry.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more information visit: <a href=\"http://www.si-i.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.si-i.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 11:27:47','2011-08-18 14:00:05','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-01 10:27:00',1,234,6,'',0),(102,32,'Logica','','<p>\r\n	<strong>Logica</strong> is a leading IT and business services company.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Logica employs 40,000 people across 36 countries. The company provides business consulting, systems integration, and IT and business process outsourcing services.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Logica works closely with its customers to release their potential - enabling change that increases efficiency, accelerates growth and manages risk. The company applies its deep industry knowledge, technical excellence and global delivery expertise to help its customers build leadership positions in their markets. Logica is listed on both the London Stock Exchange and Euronext (Amsterdam) (LSE: LOG; Euronext: LOG).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.logica.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.logica.com</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 11:36:59','2011-08-18 14:00:05','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-01 10:36:00',1,233,5,'',0),(103,45,'Boilerplate','<p>\r\n	About PICNIC</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	The PICNIC name represents everything we strive to be. It is a gathering of friends old and new, where everyone brings something to the table.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC is about innovative ideas for business, people and society. It is a platform that brings together people from diverse backgrounds who like to exchange ideas and insights and are keen to expose themselves to ideas outside their own area of expertise. PICNIC offers an online meeting place to do that through the PICNIC Club, our online community, and the PICNIC News Network (PNN) that offers inspiring, crowdsourced and co-hosted content.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition PICNIC also organizes off line events, culminating in our annual festival in Amsterdam. During three intensive days we mix creativity, science, technology, media and business to explore new solutions in the spirit of co-creation. Curious minds eager to exchange knowledge, ideas and skills gather at PICNIC and leave with a new perspective on what is possible.</p>\r\n','2011-06-01 12:19:20','2011-08-18 14:00:05','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-01 11:18:00',1,NULL,0,'',0),(104,15,'Last chance to submit for Vodafone Mobile Clicks 2011!','<p>\r\n	With only a few days to go before the Vodafone Mobile Clicks 2011 competition closes, the race is on across the Mobile start-up community. Make sure to submit and maybe you&#39;ll win a share of the &euro;225,000 prize fund. The closing date for entries is midnight on Sunday, 12th June, 2011 CET, so no time to lose!</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	This year&rsquo;s panel of impressive local and global judges includes Rudy de Waele, founder of Mobile 2.0 Europe and dotopen; Peter Barry, Vodafone Ventures; Paul Jozefak, Mobile VC; Reshma Sohoni; partner at Seedcamp and Lee Epting, Vodafone Group. Each judge will be scoring entries based on five criteria: originality, creativity and innovation; technical and operational feasibility; economic and financial viability; value to end-users; and finally, the quality of the management team.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Budding start-ups looking for inspiration need look no further than last year&rsquo;s Vodafone Mobile Clicks winner, Cardmobili. Since winning the competition in September 2010, Portugal-based Cardmobili has launched its application on Windows Phone 7, translated the app into French and Spanish and also has seen its user base increase by 80%. Check out this short interview with Helena Leite, CEO of Cardmobili <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/vodafone#p/u/0/UpCaYOx88QE\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This Sunday at midnight sharp, the registration period will close. Do not wait till the last minute, as it will take around 30 to 40 minutes to submit! And you do not want to be too late. So submit your entry now into the Vodafone Mobile Clicks 2011 competition at <a href=\"http://www.vodafonemobileclicks.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.vodafonemobileclicks.com</a>!</p>\r\n','2011-06-08 11:07:44','2011-08-18 14:00:05','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-08 10:07:44',1,65,0,'',0),(106,15,'Sign up for The Marketplace by 4 July','<p>\r\n	Are you a small company with an exciting new product or service that you want to introduce to thousands of leaders in the creative and business sectors? Then make sure to sign up for The Marketplace! Organized by the Chamber of Commerce and Syntens together with KansenKanon and Mediaguild, The Marketplace is taking place for the 6th time during the PICNIC Festival 2011.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	The theme of this year&#39;s PICNIC Festival&nbsp;is Urban Futures. The world is undergoing the largest wave of population growth in history: we are looking at more than 8 billion people in 2030 and essentially all of the growth will take place in the less developed countries, concentrated among the poorest populations in urban areas. By that time at least 70% of the world population will be living in an urban environment. This will have a huge impact on social interaction, government, infrastructure, sustainability and healthcare. Technology and design will play a leading role in developing potential solutions. <a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/themes\" target=\"_blank\">Find out more about the theme</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Each day at the&nbsp;PICNIC Festival (14-16 September 2011), The Marketplace will give 25 different young companies the chance to present themselves and interact with the PICNIC audience.&nbsp;Each company will create their own stand in a unique, casual, fast-paced networking environment that looks like a marketplace - but with a PICNIC twist. Companies who have a clear connection to or passion for this year&#39;s theme are especially encouraged to apply.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you&#39;re ready to meet inspiring people, share your ideas and get some great business leads, be sure to <strong>sign up for The Marketplace before 4 July</strong>. You can view more detailed information on the <a href=\"http://www.syntens.nl/Nieuwsberichten/Nieuws/6de-Marketplace-tijdens-Picnic-11.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Syntens website</a> (in Dutch) or send an email to <a href=\"mailto:brh@syntens.nl?subject=Marketplace%20at%20PICNIC\" target=\"_blank\">Bruni Hofman</a> at Syntens to register your company. Don&#39;t hestitate - this is an opportunity you don&#39;t want to miss.</p>\r\n','2011-06-09 15:26:18','2011-08-18 14:00:05','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-09 14:23:00',1,66,0,'',0),(107,21,'Club ground rules',NULL,'<p>\r\n	We want the Club to be an interesting community of people - from those who&rsquo;ve been sharing the PICNIC blanket for a number of years, and who&rsquo;ve helped to make it well worn, to those who&rsquo;ve only just heard about about PICNIC, and everybody in between.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The PICNIC Club is open to all, so you can:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			find other people who love to PICNIC and all it stands for</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			share ideas, ask questions and generally use people you can trust as a sounding board</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			have conversations about the many and diverse issues which interest you</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			inspire others with your passion, knowledge and experience.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>\r\n	The rules</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	We want the Club to be a fun place, which means everybody playing by the rules - which are simply;&nbsp;don&#39;t be boring.&nbsp;If you don&#39;t know what boring is, then you probably are. Here are some clues:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Boring people drone on and on about what they do when nobody has asked them or is interesed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people post irrelevant links to commercial projects. Please don&#39;t use PICNIC to carry out your next marketing campaign or to advertise. If somebody is interested and wants to find out, they can ask you directly</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people spam those who&rsquo;ve chosen to share their PICNIC experience</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people hide behind fake online identities&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people don&#39;t use their real name online</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people don&#39;t keep their profiles up to date.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please don&#39;t spoil it for others. If you choose to be boring, then we reserve the right to lock you out of our PICNIC Club. Got it?</p>\r\n','2011-06-14 14:51:27','2011-08-18 14:00:05','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-14 13:51:00',1,133,0,'Ground rules',0),(108,15,'Join PICNIC next week at Futur en Seine','<p>\r\n	We&rsquo;re heading to France for upcoming Futur en Seine festival! Following the success of the 2009 edition, the <a href=\"http://www.futur-en-seine.fr/en/\" target=\"_blank\">Futur en Seine Festival</a> again takes hold of the city and region of Paris from 17th to 26th June. This is THE popular Festival of Life and Creativity, where the general public meets the innovative creative industries to imagine, build and celebrate the digital future together!</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	The incredibly rich and diverse festival program allows everyone --&nbsp;whether curious, passionate, amateur or professional -- to share one, common experience: to test new technology <em>in situ </em>and to create the digital future together around five central themes: The Future of Life, the Future of Music and Image, the Future of Creation, the Future of Communications and the Future of the City.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	At the very heart of the festival, a cycle of international conferences and workshops will be held over a period of six days in prestigious locations (Coll&egrave;ge de France, 104, Ga&icirc;t&eacute; Lyrique, Forum des Images et Ecole Normale Sup&eacute;rieure). Internationally renowned speakers have confirmed their participation, including Everyware author Adam Greenfield, FabLab inventor Neil Gershenfeld, McLuhan associate Derrick de Kerckhove, futurist and molecular biologist Jo&euml;l de Rosnay, educationalist Sugata Mitra, artists Maurice Benayoun and Yoichiro Kawaguchi, legendary pioneer of satellite communications, Candace Johnson, designer, architect and author Michael Shamiyeh, transportion innovator Robin Chase, SXSW Producer Shaw O&#39;Keefe, <strong>PICNIC co-founder Marleen Stikker</strong>, &quot;Internet of Things&quot; author Rob van Kranenburg and many more...</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The conference cycle will also include the second edition of the <a href=\"http://www.futur-en-seine.fr/en/fiche/874/\" target=\"_blank\">European Street Design Challenge</a>, which will culminate in the selection of the award winner during the Future of the City.&nbsp;<strong>PICNIC is coming with three teams (from Eindhoven, Amsterdam &amp; Rotterdam) to compete in the second edition of the European Street Design Challenge</strong>. This competition, first held at PICNIC &lsquo;10, brings together students, start-ups and SMEs for a three-day urban design challenge. At Futur en Seine the teams will battle to develop solutions that increase a sense of &ldquo;connectedness&rdquo; between historic Paris and its expanding suburbs.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For four days, the CentQuatre urban arts and creativity centre will host the &quot;Innovation Village&quot;. Here visitors can test future-oriented prototypes which have been specially developed with the support of the Cap Digital cluster and the Paris Region. Moreover, delegations from such major international cities as Tokyo, Brazil, Amsterdam, London, Vienna, Berlin, and Copenhagen will present their visionary and innovative digital services and technologies. International design competitions, digital installation and multi-media performances will complement this universal exhibition of the digital revolution. <strong>Don&#39;t forget to visit PICNIC and IIP Create at the Innovation Village as well</strong>!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please visit the Futur en Seine website for the <a href=\"http://www.futur-en-seine.fr/en/\" target=\"_blank\">full program</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>PICNIC&nbsp;website readers will receive a very special discount offer for all tickets to the festival.</strong> Please email Charlotte Sagnier (charlotte.sagnier[at]capdigital.com)&nbsp;for details about the discount.</p>\r\n','2011-06-14 18:36:28','2011-08-18 14:00:05','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-14 16:41:00',1,71,0,'',0),(109,15,'\'Best Scene in Town\' is back at PICNIC Festival!','<p>\r\n	This year the Mobile Design Challenge &#39;Best Scene in Town&#39; is back again at the PICNIC festival - bigger and better than ever!</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	Best Scene in Town is a design challenge in which you designers from different disciplines compete to create the ultimate mobile experience. Students teams mixed(!) from leading learning institutions combine creative forces to design, present and pilot new ideas on how we can interact with locations and people using our smartphones.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Participating are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Massachusetts Institute of Technology</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Hong Kong Design Institute</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Parsons - The New School for Design</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		University of Amsterdam</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		University of Applied Sciences, Amsterdam</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Utrecht University</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	But we are open to have creative and enthusiastic students from other institutions join in as well. So check out the <a href=\"http://www.bestsceneintown.com/\" target=\"_blank\">website of 7Scenes</a> for more info on how to join the Challenge. And maybe you&#39;ll win a trip to PICNIC Festival 2011 in Amsterdam to build and test case your idea!</p>\r\n','2011-06-14 21:57:36','2011-08-18 14:00:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-14 20:57:36',1,72,0,'',0),(110,31,'Waag Society','','<p>\r\n	Waag Society, the institute for art, science and technology, develops creative technology for social innovation. The foundation researches, develops concepts, pilots and prototypes, and acts as an intermediate between the arts, science and the media.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Six years ago, Waag Society Director Marleen Stikker co-founded PICNIC, creating the leading innovation platform in Amsterdam.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more info visit: <a href=\"http://www.waag.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.waag.org</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-16 08:13:54','2011-08-18 14:00:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-16 07:13:00',1,230,2,'Waag Society',0),(111,36,'Wired (UK)',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Wired</strong> is the magazine about what&rsquo;s next &ndash; bringing you the people, the trends and the big ideas that will change our lives. Each month, through thought-provoking features and stunning photography, we explore the next big ideas in science, culture, business &ndash; wherever innovation and new thinking are reshaping our world.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Since the US edition of Wired launched in 1993, the magazine has been synonymous with informed and intelligent analysis, and a consistently reliable predictor of change. The UK edition, launched in April 2009, is similarly committed to bringing you the best writers and photographers; compelling long-form journalism; extraordinary photography and design; and the people, products and ideas that matter.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Follow Wired <a href=\"http://www.wired.co.uk\" target=\"_blank\">online</a> and on <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/wireduk\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2011-06-16 08:24:21','2011-08-22 09:59:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-20 07:24:00',1,292,9,'Wired (UK)',0),(115,15,'Look who\'s talking at PICNIC 2011','<p>\r\n	PICNIC prides itself on bringing attention to some of the world&#39;s most innovative thinkers. Here&#39;s your chance to see and hear them before the rest of the world has discovered them!</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	We&#39;re just announcing this year&#39;s line-up. Here are just six of the people you&#39;ll have the chance to hear from and meet at PICNIC Festival 2011 and what you can expect from them:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/adam-greenfield\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Adam Greenfield</strong></a> brings&nbsp;critical thinking about how applied technology in the public space will never make the city smart, but should instead make its inhabitants smarter through human-centered (interaction) design.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/toby-barnes\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Toby Barnes</strong></a> brings&nbsp;inventive ways to open up the cities&#39; dynamics with visualisation and gamification.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/mark-woerde\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Mark Woerde</strong></a> brings&nbsp;insights in how to transform brands into meaningful pro-social brands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/eva-gladek\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Eva Gladek</strong></a> brings designs for closed ecosystems that provide the possibility for net-zero impact food production.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/peter-corbett\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Peter Corbett</strong></a> brings&nbsp;creative approaches on interactive marketing and a focus on civic innovation through community building.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/heath-bunting\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Heath Bunting</strong></a> brings his artist&#39;s vision&nbsp;to create a new (and legal!) identity for you, which you can actually purchase from him in neat, ready to use packages. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Browse their profiles and read about all of the speakers at PICNIC Festival 2011 in our <a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/picnic11-speakers\" target=\"_blank\">speakers gallery</a>. &nbsp;Be sure to check back for exciting new announcements throughout the summer.</p>\r\n','2011-06-20 13:43:35','2011-08-18 14:00:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-22 12:40:00',1,80,0,'2011 Speakers',0),(116,15,'Share your green idea and win! ','<p>\r\n	Enter the Postcode Lottery Green Challenge by 29 July</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	People from all over the world are signing up for the Postcode Lottery Green Challenge. So far, they have received entries from 52 different countries including Nepal, India, Sri Lanka, Kazakhstan, Nigeria, Russia, Belgium, Germany, Australia, the UK, the Netherlands and the USA. You can submit your idea or product at <a href=\"http://www.greenchallenge.info\">www.greenchallenge.info</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Postcode Lottery Green Challenge is looking for ideas that will contribute to a better, greener world. Dream up a greenhouse-gas-reducing product or service and send in your idea before 29 July. The entrant with the best idea will win &euro;500,000, expert coaching and help to bring his or her idea to market. The finalists will present their ideas and the prize winners will be revealed during PICNIC Festival 2011.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Put your green idea on Facebook for a chance to win an iPad 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Even those without a business plan can participate in the Green Challenge. Got a simple but brilliant idea? Share it in just two lines on the <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/PostcodeLotteryGreenChallenge\" target=\"_blank\">Green Challenge Facebook</a> page. Green Challenge ambassador Richard Branson is calling on all Facebook visitors to think of a green idea, and share it with the world. The best one wins an iPad 2, a design eco-case and an iPad2 solar charger.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Past Green Challenge winner creates Mushroom Packaging for Dell Computers</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Check out the Green Challenge blog for green ideas in action, including the latest initiative from 2008 Green Challenge winner Eben Bayer. Find out more about his <a href=\"http://www.greenchallenge.info/MediaDetails/MushroomPackagingForDellComputers.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Mushroom Packaging for Dell Computers</a>.</p>\r\n','2011-06-22 20:53:10','2011-08-18 14:00:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-22 19:53:10',1,34,0,'',0),(117,39,'PICNIC Business Club',NULL,'<h2>\r\n	PICNIC Business Club is for companies like yours that want to&nbsp;get more out of their PICNIC experience.&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC&rsquo;s reach extends far beyond our yearly festival.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our strength lies in the people, opinions, knowledge and ideas we bring together.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Do you want to be sure you and your colleagues experience PICNIC to the fullest? Are you looking for a way formally associate your company with PICNIC? Do you want stronger connections to creative business leaders in Amsterdam and beyond? The PICNIC Business Club was created for you.</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Tap a network of inspiring individuals</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Besides tickets to the yearly festival, you&rsquo;ll join our inner circle and an intimate network of like-minded creative professionals, partners and advisors. Not to mention special benefits and events just for Business Club members.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC Business Club membership packages are available for EUR 10,000. The membership is valid for one full year.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	PICNIC Business Club Benefits</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>10 Passe-partouts</strong> to PICNIC &lsquo;11 for you and your colleagues</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>40% off additional tickets</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; An <strong>exclusive experience during PICNIC &rsquo;11</strong>, including access to the Business Club Lounge and a special side event just for Business Club members</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>Listing as a Business Club partner </strong>on the website at PICNIC &lsquo;11</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>Invitation to closed PICNIC partner events</strong> throughout the year for networking, brainstorming &amp; more</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>A fun and casual event</strong> just for Business Club members in spring 2012</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Want to find out more?</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Get in touch with us at <a href=\"mailto:info@picnicnetwork.org\">info@picnicnetwork.org</a> or call&nbsp;+31 (0)20 320 5813 to find out how you can become&nbsp;a member of the PICNIC Business Club.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>','2011-06-23 14:17:48','2011-08-18 14:00:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-23 13:17:48',1,82,0,'Business Club',0),(119,40,'CnB (Creativity & Business Convention)',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	22-24 June 2011</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Cologne, Germany</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	The three-day event invites experienced experts and startups, company founders and dedicated freelancers, creative people and business pros, university graduates and students, to discuss future formats for production, financing and exploitation, new life and business models, new trends and visions. C&#39;n&#39;B offers creative people a home and an action platform - instead of passive consumption, our agenda involves active participation, and creative interaction.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Watch the convention trailer here:&nbsp;http://bit.ly/CnBTrailer</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.c-o-pop.de/en/cnb-convention/home\" target=\"_blank\">Website</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-23 14:58:50','2011-08-18 14:00:07','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-23 13:58:00',1,295,4,'CnB (Creativity & Business Convention)',0),(120,40,'SXSW',NULL,'<p>\r\n	9-18 March 2012</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Austin, Texas</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.sxsw.com\" target=\"_blank\">Website</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The South by Southwest (SXSW) Conferences &amp; Festivals offer the unique convergence of original music, independent films, and emerging technologies</p>\r\n','2011-06-23 15:03:16','2011-08-18 14:00:07','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-09-23 14:03:00',1,NULL,3,'SXSW',0),(121,40,'Futur en Seine',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	17-26 June 2011</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Paris, France</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Following the success of the 2009 edition, the Futur en Seine Festival again takes hold of the city and region of Paris from 17 to 26 June. This is THE popular Festival for Digital Life and Creativity, where the general public meets the innovative creative industries to imagine, build and celebrate the digital future together! The incredibly rich and diverse festival program allows everyone &ndash; whether curious, passionate, amateur or professional &ndash; to share one, common experience: to test new technology in situ and to create together the digital future around five central themes: The Future of Life, the Future of Music and Image, the Future of Creation, the Future of Communications and the Future of the City.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://www.futur-en-seine.fr/en/</p>\r\n','2011-06-23 15:06:26','2011-08-18 14:00:07','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-23 14:06:00',1,296,8,'Futur en Seine',0),(122,40,'NEXT11',NULL,'<p>\r\n	May 17-18, 2011</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Berlin, Germany</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://nextconf.eu/next11/\" target=\"_blank\">Website</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Business developers, marketing experts and agency managers are faced with the challenge to create new applications out of the ever-growing data stream with added value for the consumer. In our data-driven economy, the consumer is in the focus point of consideration. Because his behaviour determines who wins, what lasts and what will be sold. Data is the crucial driver to develop relevant products and services for the consumer.</p>\r\n','2011-06-23 15:08:16','2011-08-18 14:00:07','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-09-23 14:08:00',1,NULL,5,'NEXT11',0),(123,36,'M/I/S/C/',NULL,'<p>\r\n	M/I/S/C/ is a quarterly magazine distributed globally about business innovation and design thinking. Organized around four key concepts: Movement / Intuition / Structure / Complexity /, it&#39;s a magazine about art. It&#39;s a magazine about design. It&#39;s a magazine about business. M/I/S/C/ is about pushing new creative territories and providing new perspectives on everything from strategic innovation to design thinking to social innovation to behavioral economics.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://miscology.com/</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 08:19:48','2011-08-22 09:59:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 07:19:48',1,237,6,'M/I/S/C/',0),(124,41,'Virtueel Platform',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Virtueel Platform</strong> is the sector institute for e-culture in the Netherlands. Its mission is to stimulate and strengthen cultural innovation by sharing knowledge about e-culture and increasing its visibility and scope.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Virtueel Platform has three main strategic goals:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	- Track developments and stimulate research</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	- Give the sector&rsquo;s achievements national and international recognition</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	- Strengthen relationships between the sector and cultural/social/political organisations</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Virtueel Platform is particularly interested in reaching out to individuals and organisations working in the arts and culture sectors, the government, funding agencies, education and the creative industry.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	E-culture has two main aspects. In one&nbsp;sense, e-culture refers to electronic arts, network culture, media use and research into the cultural appropriation of new technologies. However, e-culture includes the much broader impact that digital technologies and interactive media currently have as the most important catalysts for change in the way we live, work and play. Meanwhile we should also remember that culture and the arts have always been at the basis of inspiring the developments in digital media. In short, e-culture is at the very cutting edge of all social and economic development.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Virtueel Platform is an independent foundation subsidised by the Ministry of Education, Culture and Science in the Netherlands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.virtueelplatform.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:32:59','2011-08-18 14:00:07','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 09:32:59',1,269,22,'Virtueel Platform',0),(125,41,'7Scenes','<br />\r\n','<p>\r\n	<strong>7scenes </strong>is a mobile storytelling platform that makes it easy for organizations to develop, publish and play GPS tours and games. 7scenes links photos, videos, sounds, tasks, rewards, polls and more to locations, so you can navigate the city with your smartphone in a brand new way. Organizations can use 7scenes straight out-of-the-box or create their own customized features and branded Apps.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	7scenes is used in the heritage, tourism, education and events sector, both in The Netherlands as in many other parts of the world.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more info check <a href=\"http://www.7scenes.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.7scenes.com</a>.</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:35:26','2011-08-18 14:00:07','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 09:35:00',1,248,0,'7Scenes',0),(126,41,'Syntens',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Syntens&rsquo; mission is to strengthen the capacity to innovate of small and medium-sized companies, to stimulate successful innovation and to make a visible contribution towards sustainable growth.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our network can help strengthen your business by providing the right knowhow and resources, enabling you to innovate quicker and more efficiently. Syntens understands who and what you need to successfully create new business.&nbsp;&nbsp;If your motto is &#39;Things can always be improved&#39; and if you believe in the power of cooperation, then Syntens is here for you!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It is an initiative from the Ministry of Economic Affairs (economics, agriculture &amp; innovation)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.syntens.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:37:12','2011-08-18 14:00:07','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 09:37:12',1,268,21,'Syntens',0),(127,41,'Non-fiction',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Non-fiction</strong> is an innovation agency reconfiguring popular engagement with public institutions for the 21st century. It was founded by Michiel van Iersel and Juha van &lsquo;t Zelfde in 2008.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We work for and with a growing number of public institutions, museums, universities, design agencies, artists, architects and musicians. Amongst them are the Stedelijk Museum, Bimhuis, Muziekgebouw aan &lsquo;t IJ, Museum De Paviljoens, Stadsherstel, North Sea Jazz, Netherlands Institute of Cultural Heritage, SNS REAAL Fonds and Michel van der Aa.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Through artistic, economic and social synthesis we design bespoke situations for collaborative experience of cutting-edge art, music, heritage and public space. These always happen both in real space and online, via ubiquitous digital networking technologies.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our office is situated in the former chemistry lab of the Netherlands Institute of Cultural Heritage, right in the middle of the Amsterdam&rsquo;s vibrant museum quarter at Museumplein.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.non-fiction.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.non-fiction.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:40:04','2011-08-18 14:00:07','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 09:40:04',1,299,18,'Non-fiction',0),(128,41,'Mediagilde',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Mediagilde</strong> (Media Guild) is a not for profit organization that fosters innovation and brings it to the market and to society. Mediagilde has two important goals that follow naturally from each other:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		To support innovative starters in the creative industry</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		To bring businesses and knowledge institutes in touch with the creative industry and innovation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Everybody who is talented and has a good (interactive media) idea can be considered for a place at Mediagilde. All you need is an entrepreneurial character and an excellent innovative idea that can potentially reach the market.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Mediagilde selects the best proposals and offers selected starters a completely equipped workspace. Like this, you (and your team) will have a dynamic creative environment to work in. All workspaces are&nbsp;equipped with excellent technical facilities such as glass fibre connections. Besides that, all starters participate in a extensive support program geared towards technological development, matter-of-fact business knowledge and entrepreneurship.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.mediagilde.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:53:01','2011-08-18 14:00:07','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 09:53:01',1,263,16,'Mediagilde',0),(130,41,'Kenniskring',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Amsterdam is knowledge</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition to the canals, Anne Frank and the Van Gogh Museum, Amsterdam has another important trump card: the presence of a broad spectrum of knowledge.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Seven spearheads</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In seven areas knowledge in Amsterdam ranks among the top regions of the world:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		a strong creative industry</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		an outstanding logistic network via Schiphol, the ports and the world-famous flower auction in Aalsmeer</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		a strong position from the international perspective in the area of IT and new media</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		financial and business services</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		life sciences</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		the world famous flower auction in Aalsmeer and the wholesale foodcompanies</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		toerism and conferences</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	These clusters function outstandingly because knowledge is exchanged efficiently between institutions, companies and government authorities, not only within a cluster, but also through interconnections between the different clusters.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Sharing knowledge</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Knowledge exchange is high on many people&rsquo;s list of priorities; after all, in unity lays strength.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The KennisKring Amsterdam (Amsterdam Knowledge Network Foundation) forms an overarching knowledge network in the region. In the last sixteen years the KennisKring has grown to be a distinguished platform, with approximately 7000 knowledge partners. The network includes a wide variety of entrepreneurs, lecturers and researchers at knowledge and educational institutes (including of course the two universities and the three colleges of higher education), administrators and policy officials of regional and provincial government authorities and organizations such as the Deloitte, KPMG, Boer&amp;Croon, PwC, Ernst&amp;Young, Schiphol Group, KLM, TNT, Van Gansewinkel, Alliander, ING, Deutsche Bank, Rabobank, ABN AMRO Bank, Shell and Amsterdam Chamber of Commerce. What they have in common is natural curiosity and eagerness to learn more. Together, these partners endeavour to strengthen and make better use of the knowledge infrastructure which is already in place.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>KennisKring Amsterdam is more than a network</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	To make the Amsterdam region better known as an eminent knowledge centre, a programme called Amsterdamse Innovatie Motor (AIM) has been started. The projects in this programme are intended to stimulate knowledge exchange and the creation of spin-offs for the universities and knowledge institutes in the areas of IT, creative industry, life sciences, financial services, logistics and sustainability.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.kenniskring.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:54:26','2011-08-18 14:00:08','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 09:54:26',1,261,14,'Kenniskring',0),(131,41,'European Journalism Centre',NULL,'<p>\r\n	The <strong>European Journalism Centre</strong> (EJC) is an independent, international, non-profit institute dedicated to the highest standards in journalism, primarily through the further training of journalists and media professionals. Building on its extensive international network, the Centre operates as a facilitator and partner in a wide variety of training projects.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The main goals of the EJC are to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		promote high quality journalism through professional training, particularly in a European context;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		provide a forum for discussion, debate, and exchanges of views and experience for journalists, editors, media executives and other media professionals;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		support, through training and networking, high standards of journalism in developing countries;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		promote further journalism training that answers the needs of media professionals and the media industry;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		monitor and reflect, via research, surveys and publications, on the present and future challenges facing the media;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		create and support networks among media professionals within Europe and with other parts of the world.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	The EJC plays a unique role at the European level as a partner and organiser for media companies, professional organisations, journalism schools and governmental bodies seeking to establish activities and projects.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.ejc.net\" target=\"_blank\">www.ejc.net</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:55:45','2011-08-18 14:00:08','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 09:55:45',1,258,11,'European Journalism Centre',0),(132,41,'Creative Amsterdam ','','<p>\r\n	<b>Creative Amsterdam </b>stimulates the creative industries in the seven cities of the Amsterdam Metropolitan Area. The programme was initiated in 2007, with a pledge to cooperate on the part of the region&rsquo;s local government and other organisations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Creative Amsterdam offers national and international companies access to the creative potential of the region. Conversely, it also helps the region&rsquo;s creative companies find the right facilities to stimulate their entrepreneurialism.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The programme does this through three key activities:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Concentrating information and activities, by bringing them together in a single physical and digital location: <a href=\"http://www.creativeamsterdam.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.creativeamsterdam.nl</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Facilitating, by improving services to foreign companies and to starting and growing entrepreneurs</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Promoting the creative industries in the region so that they attract national and international attention</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.creativeamsterdam.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.creativeamsterdam.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:58:53','2011-08-18 14:00:08','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 09:58:00',1,253,6,'Creative  Amsterdam ',0),(133,41,'Amsterdam Innovation Motor','','<p>\r\n	<strong>Amsterdam Innovation Motor</strong> (AIM) was established to maintain and consolidate the trendsetting position of the Amsterdam region in the knowledge economy. AIM is directed by the Economic Development Board Amsterdam (EDBA).AIM promotes innovation, cooperation and new business in the Amsterdam Metropolitan area. To do so, we focus on the development of sectors that are the most promising in terms of strengthening the position of the region, namely:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Creative industries</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		ICT</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Life sciences</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Financial and Business Services</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Sustainability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.aimsterdam.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 11:01:03','2011-08-18 14:00:08','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-27 10:01:03',1,249,1,'Amsterdam Innovation Motor',0),(134,15,'The PICNIC Poster Project','<p>\r\n	This year at PICNIC Festival 2011 we&rsquo;re building a city around the theme Urban Futures. But what defines a city? It&rsquo;s made up of so many unique elements, including the rich visuals you find on the streets. With this in mind, our creative director Marcel Kampman introduced the PICNIC Poster Project.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	He invited leading designers and agencies&nbsp;from our international networks to make artwork for us in the form of posters. We&rsquo;ll be using these powerful visuals in a variety of ways, from promotion online and offline to physical and screen-based applications at the festival itself. The variety of images will help us create a diverse and eclectic atmosphere &ndash; just like you&rsquo;d find in a real city.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please take a moment to <strong><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/crossmediaweek/sets/72157627067325702/\" target=\"_blank\">look at the amazing contributions</a></strong> we&rsquo;ve received so far!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We&rsquo;d like to extend a special thank you to Ben Lambers of <a href=\"http://www.studioaandacht.nl\" target=\"_blank\">Studio Aandacht</a>, Chris van Diemen of <a href=\"http://takenbystorm.nl\" target=\"_blank\">Taken by Storm</a>, Karim Cherif and Liam Aelmans of <a href=\"http://www.united135.com\" target=\"_blank\">United 135</a>, Jonathan Looman of <a href=\"http://www.hellowman.nl\" target=\"_blank\">Studio Lowman</a>, Ralston &amp; Bau of <a href=\"http://www.transplant.nu\" target=\"_blank\">Transplant</a>, Paul O&rsquo;Connell of <a href=\"http://www.nephronim.com\" target=\"_blank\">Nephronim</a> and Saskia Pouwels of <a href=\"http://www.nephronim.com\" target=\"_blank\">Studio Dumbar</a> for their hard work and impressive submissions.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you would like to contribute to the visual identity of the PICNIC Festival, please email <a href=\"mailto:marcel@kampman.nl?subject=Picnic%20Poster%20Project\">Marcel Kampman</a> for more details.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em>Photo credit: Karim Cherif, United 135</em></p>\r\n','2011-06-29 14:24:56','2011-08-18 14:00:08','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-29 13:24:56',1,148,0,'',0),(135,15,'Emphas.is: Show your support for photojournalism ','<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.emphas.is/\" target=\"_blank\">Emphas.is</a> is a new model for crowdfunding impactful, high-quality journalism. Photographers show their work, share their motivations and highlight the news-worthy projects they are undertaking. Anyone can make a contribution to back a story.</p>','<p>\r\n	In line with our theme, Urban Futures, <strong>PICNIC has &ldquo;adopted&rdquo; a new project from Emphas.is</strong> that exposes the impact of the housing shortage in Sao Paulo, Brazil. Called <strong><a href=\"http://www.emphas.is/web/guest/discoverprojects?projectID=316\" target=\"_blank\">&ldquo;Citizen X&rdquo;</a></strong>, photographer Julio Bettencourt is documenting the people that live on the fringes of Brazil&rsquo;s society. After completing this series of portraits, Julio will project his images on facades in five central locations in Sao Paulo to create discussion and bring awareness to Brazil&rsquo;s urgent urban issues.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.emphas.is/web/guest/discoverprojects?projectID=316\" target=\"_blank\">View Julio&rsquo;s stunning photographs</a> and consider supporting this moving project.</p>\r\n','2011-06-29 17:36:11','2011-08-18 14:00:08','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-06-29 16:36:11',1,90,0,'',0),(136,15,'Virtueel Platform wants to hear about your problems!','<p>\r\n	Well, maybe not your all your problems. To be more specific, they want to hear about the problems, challenges and issues your organization faces in the area of e-culture.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	For the fifth time, Virtueel Platform will be hosting the HOT100 sessions at the PICNIC Festival 2011 (14-16 Sept).&nbsp; HOT100 is a full day of lectures, masterclasses, workshops and networking opportunities for the most talented alumni from e-culture programs across the Netherlands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Share your challenges or issues related to e-culture</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Starting now, Virtueel Platform is asking creative companies, cultural organizations, educational institutes and other organizations to submit their question or problem related to&nbsp; e-culture to the cr&egrave;me de la cr&egrave;me of the Netherlands&rsquo; e-culture alumni.<strong> Got a challenge you&rsquo;d like help solving? Submit your issue to <a href=\"mailto:klaas@virtueelplatform.nl ?subject=HOT100%20issue%20suggestion\" target=\"_blank\">Klaas</a> or <a href=\"mailto:merel@virtueelplatform.nl?subject=HOT100%20issue%20suggestion\" target=\"_blank\">Merel</a> at Virtueel Platform by 11 July.</strong> You&rsquo;ll hear within two weeks whether or not your issue was selected.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>What do you get in return?</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If your issue is selected, Virtueel Platform will arrange a free &ldquo;pressure cooker&rdquo; workshop of&nbsp; about three hours where a team of HOT100s will tackle your challenge. You can&rsquo;t expect a complete solution, but we do guarantee <strong>useful feedback, a fresh look at your issues and some brilliant new ideas</strong>. Not to mention a network of bright young minds with promising futures!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Last year, the challenges came from organizations like NRC, the Netherlands Uitburo and the City of Eindhoven, among others. For more information about past HOT100 workshops, visit <a href=\"http://www.virtueelplatform.nl/hot100\" target=\"_blank\">www.virtueelplatform.nl/hot100</a>.</p>\r\n','2011-07-01 13:14:52','2011-08-18 14:00:08','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-01 12:14:52',1,92,0,'',0),(137,40,'Startup Weekend Amsterdam','','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	July 8-10</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Amsterdam</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Find out if entrepreneurship is for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Have you ever considered becoming an entrepreneur? Not sure whether entrepreneurship is something for you? Are you planning to become an entrepreneur and looking for other business minds, programmers, or designers who stand behind your idea? Or are you working on developing a new web concept and are looking for help in coming up with a killer business plan? Find like-minded people and work on your idea during Startup Weekend Amsterdam.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Startup Weekend is an intensive 54-hour event focused on building a web or mobile application that will form the basis for your company. And all in one weekend! At Startup Weekend, people with different backgrounds such as online media, software developers, (graphic) designers and business developers all come together. Bring the new Twitter, Zynga or Foursquare to life!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You could find yourself following in the footsteps of these exciting startups: Foodspotting (SW San Francisco), Launch Rock (SW Philly) Zaar.ly (SW Los Angeles), Jimmy Fairly (SW Toulouse), Memo Lane (SW Copenhagen) and many others!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Startup Weekend Amsterdam is the ideal place to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Turn up to work on the prototypes and design for your idea: build a website or mobile application and pin down your business case. Then present it to a jury of startup experts.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Meet and gain advice from experienced engineers, IP advisors, patent attorneys, researchers, (online) serial entrepreneurs and marketing experts.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Find an enthusiastic co-founder and core team for company.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Cost: &euro; 80 for regular members, &euro; 45 for students, including meals and beverages. Sunday pitch night only&nbsp;&euro; 20.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC Network: Take 20% off a ticket by using promo code&nbsp;<b>sw_PICNIC </b>when you register for <a href=\"http://swams.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Startup Weekend Amsterdam</a>.</p>\r\n','2011-07-04 13:42:45','2011-08-18 14:00:09','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-04 12:42:45',1,240,7,'Startup Weekend Amsterdam',0),(138,41,'Lorentz Center',NULL,'<p>\r\n	The <strong>Lorentz Center</strong> is an international center that coordinates and hosts workshops in the sciences, based on the philosophy that science thrives on interaction between creative researchers. Lorentz Center workshops focus on new collaborations and interactions between scientists from different countries and fields, and with varying seniority.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>The Lorentz Center concept</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In order to allow both junior and senior researchers to catch up with the rapid international developments and to establish new contacts and collaboration, Lorentz Center workshops bring together groups of 40 to 50 junior and senior researchers in a stimulating environment with working space for all participants: offices with a desk, personal computer, white boards, meeting rooms. Through a combination of informal talks, working sessions and discussions, participants are able to assess the status of a field and its future, and to collaborate, establish new international contacts, and spot upcoming talent.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Workshops can be proposed and organised by any researcher from any country. Workshops organised by researchers from different scientific backgrounds and nationalities are encouraged. Proposals for workshops are reviewed by the Scientific Advisory Boards. Currently, the advisory boards within the natural sciences are astronomy, informatics, life sciences, mathematics, and physics. The Center is also open to proposals from outside these fields in the framework of computational science or our colalboration with NIAS</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.lorentzcenter.nl</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 10:42:59','2011-08-18 14:00:09','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 09:42:59',1,262,15,'',0),(139,41,'European Creative Business Network',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>European Creative Business Network</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The European Creative Business Network (ECB Network) is a foundation, established by multiple European organizations that work for and in Europe&rsquo;s creative industry.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The main goal of the ECB Network is to contribute towards establishing the EU as an accessible, effective and rewarding single market for creative and cultural entrepreneurs. The ECB Network offers three key services:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1. Pitching events, where creative businesses pitch to clients and investors</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2. Creative trade missions, to enter new markets and develop new products</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3. Connecting creative businesses through the online ECB Network community</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	At the first meeting of the ECB Network in Essen, Germany, there was unanimous agreement for developing a pilot programme of services and opportunities that the Network will offer. The first concrete opportunity arranged through the ECB Network was the first Creative Trade Mission in Bristol, GB, hosted and funded by the network&rsquo;s founding partner, South West Screen. Over 60 business and support agencies from cities across Europe attended to discuss the benefits that the Network offers, whilst also exploring the latest developments in Internet Protocol Television (IPTV), focusing on differing European business models, rapidly evolving audiences, developments in digital technology, and new opportunities for interaction.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	After the great success in Bristol, the Network now presents its second Creative Trade Mission during PICNIC 2011 in Amsterdam</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.ecbnetwork.eu</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 10:50:49','2011-08-23 15:05:17','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 09:50:49',1,318,10,'',0),(140,41,'Dentsu London',NULL,'<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Dentsu London</strong> is an advertising and creative communications company launched in April 2010. Clients include Canon, greentomatocars, Tetley, Wallpaper, Pok&eacute;mon and Uniqlo.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Making Future Magic is Dentsu London&rsquo;s philosophy. As an approach it guides all the work Dentsu London does, through client partnerships and also through its own agency initiatives. &ldquo;Making&rdquo; emphasises craft and collaboration; &ldquo;Future&rdquo; is an inventive approach to materials, media and business; &ldquo;Magic&rdquo; means transformative and powerful, culturally and commercially.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dentsu London thinks creative communications go beyond advertising, to include product, service, design and technology. The company aims to make work that is culturally enriching and socially beneficial.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dentsu London is owned by Dentsu Inc but has creative and strategic autonomy as the network&rsquo;s first independent flagship agency in the west. Making Future Magic is a Dentsu London initiative.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.dentsulondon.com</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 11:26:44','2011-08-18 14:00:09','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 10:26:44',1,255,8,'',0),(141,41,'European Centre for Creative Economy',NULL,'<p>\r\n	The <strong>European Centre for Creative Economy</strong> (ecce) is an institute of RUHR.2010 GmbH, located in the Dortmunder U - Centre for Art and Creativity, whose brief is to develop and support the creative industries at a local, national and international level. With its 11 branches, widespread markets, technological affinity and identity-establishing products, the creative economy contributes greatly to economic, cultural and urban development. Ideas and creativity are set to become the most important economic asset of the 21st century and thus a driving force for the change from industrial to knowledge society. In Europe the creative economy has, with rising tendency, already grown into the third-largest industry. It is therefore of central importance to intensify the discourse on the creative economy in Germany and to develop the creative fields - from film through games to music, from literature to design and from the performing arts to the free cultural scenes.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For ecce the creative economy is a mixture of culture, economy, art, technology, urban development and education and it believes it is necessary to engage in an interdisciplinary debate on these fields in order to develop specific and long-term support measures. This must not only be done on a regional level with local protagonists, but it is also necessary to stimulate intensive European dialogue so that experiences can be shared and suitable framework conditions create.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	ecce sees its role in participating in the discussion on structural support of the creative economy at a European level and in positioning North Rhine-Westphalia as a centre of the creative economy. ecce further supports the creative industries with an integrative promotional concept that not only considers talents and their needs, but also develops existing locations of creativity further and creates new space through strategic urban development. The measures initiated so far can be summarised by four key words:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		LOCALISATION: Further development of existing locations and creation of new space</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		NETWORKING: Intensification and structuring of exchange</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		CONSOLIDATION: Realisation of large annual events with an international reach</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		COMMUNICATION: Extensive communication measures</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	The goal is to grow the creative economy over the long term to help overcome structural change in the Ruhr metropolis.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.e-c-c-e.de</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 11:44:43','2011-08-18 14:00:09','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 10:44:00',1,256,9,'',0),(142,41,'European Network of Living Labs',NULL,'<p>\r\n	The <strong>European Network of Living Labs</strong> (ENoLL) is the international federation of benchmarked Living Labs in Europe and worldwide. Founded in November 2006 under the auspices of the Finnish European Presidency, the network has grown in &lsquo;waves&rsquo; up to this day. To this date, 5 Waves have been launched, resulting in 274 accepted Living Labs. The ENoLL international non-profit association, as the legal representative entity of the network, is headquartered in Brussels, at the heart of Europe.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>What is a Living Lab?</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A Living Lab is a real-life test and experimentation environment where users and producers co-create innovations. Living Labs have been characterised by the European Commission as Public-Private-People Partnerships (PPPP) for user-driven open innovation. A Living Lab employs four main activities:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Co-Creation: co-design by users and producers</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Exploration: discovering emerging usages, behaviours and market opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Experimentation: implementing live scenarios within communities of users</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Evaluation: assessment of concepts, products and services according to socio-ergonomic, socio-cognitive and socio-economic criteria.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.openlivinglabs.eu</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 11:55:20','2011-08-18 14:00:09','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 10:55:19',1,259,12,'',0),(143,41,'Amsterdam Living Lab',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Amsterdam Living Lab</strong> has started in 2008 with the goal to help companies to test new products in a real user environment. User interaction is nowadays part of the design process and ALL means to facilitate this.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Amsterdam Living Lab is supported by the City of Amsterdam, the Province of Noord-Holland, Stadsregio Amsterdam and the Ministry of Economic Affairs. The project is executed in close cooperation between the Amsterdam Innovation Motor, Novay, University of Amsterdam and Waag Society. In the current projects several companies are involved like: Logica, Far West, Accenture and NUON.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A strong connection exists towards Europa with other Living Lab initiatives. The people behind the Amsterdam Living Lab are member of the policy council of the European Network of Living Labs and are also involved in the i2Cat Living Lab in Barcelona and have close ties to Forum Virium in Helsinki. Other involved cities are Rome, Stockholm, Paris and Brussels. From the European Committee a keen interest is in the leading role Amsterdam is willing to play in the Living Lab movement. This leads to an excellent position to acquire extra funding for innovation from the European Committee.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.amsterdamlivinglab.nl</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 12:00:44','2011-08-18 14:00:09','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 11:00:44',1,250,2,'',0),(146,41,'STT Future Studies',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>STT Future Studies </strong>(Stichting Toekomstbeeld der Techniek)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	STT explores new trends and develops inspiring foresights on technology and society. For that purpose STT facilitates a free space in which enthusiastic stakeholders meet and construct creative views on the future. The results serve as starting points for new initiatives, such as applied research programmes or public-private cooperation. Project participants are the most important ambassadors of the results, which are also distributed through the media, lectures and workshops.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	STT was established in 1968 by The Netherlands Royal Institute of Engineers (KIVINIRIA). STT is a non-profit organiza&not;tion funded by the Dutch government and business contributions. STT&rsquo;s advisory board consists of around 30 members who are selected among contributors and scientific institutions, all appointed on personal title. In addition, STT hosts four academic chairs on futures studies and research. Do take a look at current and past foresight projects and our recent publications on our website <a href=\"http://www.stt.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.stt.nl.</a></p>\r\n','2011-07-05 12:45:33','2011-08-18 14:00:10','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 11:45:33',1,267,20,'',0),(147,41,'Creative Commons',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Creative Commons Netherlands</strong> (CC-NL) is a joint venture between Knowledgeland, Waag Society and the Institute for Information Law (IViR) in cooperation with Creative Commons International, a not-for-profit organization, founded in 2001, that promotes the creative re-use of intellectual and artistic works.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Creative Commons Netherlands has been working on promoting and supporting the use of Creative Commons Licenses in the Netherlands since 2004. Our activities include workshops, presentations, on and offline support as well as academic research into legal questions raised by the use of the Creative Commons Licenses.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Creative Commons Netherlands is supported by the Dutch Ministry for Education, Culture and Science.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.creativecommons.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.creativecommons.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-07-05 12:59:42','2011-08-18 14:00:10','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 11:59:42',1,254,7,'',0),(148,41,'Council',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Council </strong>is a loose group of professionals with different ideas and opinions. We sometimes differ and will probably clash. We prefer to host the full range of opinions on what will be a small avalanche of disruptive innovations. We do have something in common though. We have been through the full range of emotions and conceptual breakdown that comes with grasping the territory, the full logistical, business, social and philosophical implications of the Internet of Things. According to G&eacute;rald Santucci, Head of RFID Unit EU, the IOT can not be build withouth artists, designers and philosophers. These insights were known to us from the moment we spotted them as designers, artists, coders, tinkerers and thinkers. Slowly over the past decade they trickled down into the Future and Emergent FP7 programs and the high end labs where the vision could not be scaled into everyday life so the notion of Living Labs seemed like a good idea.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In a similar way it found its way into the chapter 7s of each FP7 project, the moment where an ethical person was brought in to sort of evaluate the damage this new technology would undoubtedly do. In recent years we heard of pervasive computing, ubicomp, things take think and studies concerning its societal and ethical implications.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These studies are always interesting, years after the infrastructure has been rolled out.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	So yes we think that the words of G&eacute;rald Santucci are of paramount importance as for the first time we hear of this need for creativity, innovation and a human approach in the heart of the technical divisions and programs.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	/www.theinternetofthings.eu</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 13:09:02','2011-08-18 14:00:10','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 12:09:02',1,252,5,'',0),(149,41,'Premsela',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Premsela,</strong> the Netherlands Institute for Design and Fashion, creates opportunities for the growth of Dutch design. We collaborate intensively with a large number of partners. With them, we organise lectures, debates and exhibitions in the Netherlands and abroad. Premsela also publishes Morf, the Netherlands&rsquo; biggest design magazine, and the international web portal Design.nl. Our activities are aimed at designers, students, clients, producers, and everyone interested in the value of design and fashion.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.premsela.org</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 13:29:33','2011-08-18 14:00:10','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 12:29:33',1,266,19,'',0),(150,41,'Forum Virium Helsinki',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Forum Virium Helsinki </strong>creates internationally competitive digital services for consumers and clients in the Helsinki Metropolitan Area through cooperation between corporations, public institutions and citizens.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Vision 2015</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Forum Virium Helsinki has made Finland and the Helsinki Metropolitan Area an internationally recognized showcase for digital services, in the process attracting a number of top-level international organizations to invest in their operations here. Forum Virium Helsinki is the central node of the EU in the development of digital services. The project has enabled participating companies to generate significant international business.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Values</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Open co-operation: </strong>In Forum Virium Helsinki companies, public bodies and citizens create together services based on customer needs. Openness is a competitive advantage.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Commitment to goals: </strong>Forum Virium Helsinki works in a long-term and challenging manner by learning from each other. The result is more than the sum of the parts.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Creating innovations:</strong> Forum Virium Helsinki is looking for radical, systematic innovations, taking risks and learning from challenges.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.forumvirium.fi/en</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 13:42:43','2011-08-18 14:00:10','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 12:42:43',1,260,13,'',0),(151,41,'COMM',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>COMM</strong> is a two-day conference on the innovative, creative and technical applications and economic growth in the field of ICT and mobile phones, focusing on Africa. Matchmaking, networking, inspiration, learning, great food and entertainment. At COMM you are an active player. Projects and companies are presenting their current work and technical applications. Field experts and specialists will lecture and give workshops focusing on real issues, ethics, environment en techniques. After COMM you will have expanded your network which may lead to economic growth and innovation in and for your projects in Africa.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Mission statement:&nbsp;</strong>Contribution to a better world through digital connection between the Netherlands, other western countries and developing and emerging economies.</p>\r\n','2011-07-05 13:51:47','2011-08-18 14:00:10','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-05 12:51:47',1,145,4,'COMM',0),(155,15,'Explore the future of immersive technology at b.TWEEN 3D on 21 July','<p>\r\n	b.TWEEN is back &ndash; and this year it&rsquo;s all in 3D - a true playground for pioneers. This one-day gathering at BFI Southbank in London combines the most inspiring speakers with the chance to network with innovators and thought leaders. Find out what&rsquo;s happening at the cutting edge of augmented reality, AI, sci-fi and 3D.</p>\r\n','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height: 19px; font-family: helvetica, arial, &amp;quot;liberation sans&amp;quot;, freesans, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">Attendees and presenters from gaming, advertising, TV, film, science, fashion and education will come together to imagine a future when the virtual spills from the screen onto the streets. At <a href=\"http://btween3d.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">b.TWEEN 3D</a>, they&rsquo;ll be shaping the future of immersive technologies with debates and discussions and showcasing ideas from the best industry players. <a href=\"http://btween3d.co.uk/event/programme\" target=\"_blank\">Check out their packed program of speakers and inspirational sessions</a>.</span></h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Friends of PICNIC can attend b.TWEEN 3D on 21 July 2011 with a very special discount &ndash; 20% off! Just use the code <strong>picnic_btween3d</strong> when you <a href=\"http://btween3d.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">buy your ticket</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/BAhbBlsHOgZmIi0yMDExLzA3LzA4LzAzXzA4XzM1XzczNl9iLnR3ZWVuXzNEXzIuanBn\" alt=\"\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 200px; float: left;\" /></p>\r\n','2011-07-08 10:04:01','2011-08-18 14:00:10','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-10-10 09:04:00',1,5,0,'',0),(156,40,'b.TWEEN 3D','','<p>\r\n	21 July 2011</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	London</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://btween3d.co.uk/</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	b.TWEEN is back &ndash; and this year it&rsquo;s all in 3D - a true playground for pioneers. This one-day gathering at BFI Southbank in London combines the most inspiring speakers with the chance to network with innovators and thought leaders. Find out what&rsquo;s happening at the cutting edge of augmented reality, AI, sci-fi and 3D.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Attendees and presenters from gaming, advertising, TV, film, science, fashion and education will come together to imagine a future when the virtual spills from the screen onto the streets. At b.TWEEN 3D, they&rsquo;ll be shaping the future of immersive technologies with debates and discussions and showcasing ideas from the best industry players. <a href=\"http://btween3d.co.uk/event/programme\" target=\"_blank\">Check out their packed program of speakers and inspirational sessions</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Friends of PICNIC can attend b.TWEEN 3D on 21 July 2011 with a very special discount: &nbsp;20% off! Just use the code picnic_btween3d w when you <a href=\"http://btween3d.eventbrite.com/\" target=\"_blank\">buy your ticket</a>.</p>\r\n','2011-07-08 10:34:58','2011-08-18 14:00:11','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2020-07-08 09:30:00',1,132,9,'',0),(157,41,'Boom Chicago',NULL,'<p>\r\n	The creative organization <strong>Boom Chicago</strong> makes comedy shows, television productions, and tailored programs for corporate events. They also create original video for external and internal campaigns.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Boom Chicago&rsquo;s comedy shows are a fast-paced mix of sharp writing, quick improvisation, video, music and elements from the internet. Many see Boom Chicago at their theater in the heart of Amsterdam. The 280 seat venue offers great technical facilities, a creative kitchen, and a separate bar/lounge and terrace. It is also available for private parties and events.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition, Boom Chicago is a leader in shows and improvisation trainings on location for companies. Next to daily shows in Amsterdam, they create another 200 tailored programs a year for clients in Europe and beyond. They also make tailored videos with the world&rsquo;s top companies for campaigns and events.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.boomchicago.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.boomchicago.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-07-08 11:49:01','2011-08-18 14:00:11','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-08 10:49:00',1,251,3,'',0),(158,1,'Jobs at PICNIC','<p>\r\n	Looking for a way to get more involved with PICNIC? How about applying to be a part of our PICNIC Festival 2011 volunteer team!</p>\r\n','<h2>\r\n	<strong>Festival volunteers</strong></h2>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, Arial, \'Liberation Sans\', FreeSans, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 19px; \">Every year we welcome thousands of visitors to Amsterdam for our three-day festival. During our event, we rely on a team of hardworking volunteers to help us with everything from production to registration to press. In short, our volunteers temporarily join the team to ensure every visitor has an amazing experience.</span></h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	We&rsquo;re currently recruiting volunteers for a variety of roles to work at the PICNIC Festival 2011 from 14 to 16 September at the NDSM Wharf in Amsterdam.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Basic requirements for all our volunteers:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Live in Amsterdam area</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Good spoken English</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Available all three days of PICNIC (14-16 September), with the understanding that these are long days (it&#39;s not a 9 to 5 position!)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Available for volunteer kick-off meeing (1 September, 19:00 - 21:00)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Available for event site walk-through (13 September, 13:30 - 15:30)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>What will you get in return?</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		2 days working + 1 day off to participate in PICNIC for free (&euro;395 value)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Great experience in international events production</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Exposure to the leading creative minds in Europe</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Free t-shirt</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Free lunch every day</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Free tickets to evening events (parties) for you + 1 friend</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Keep reading for more information about the various roles and how to apply.</strong></p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	PICNIC Festival 2011 Volunteer Teams</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Production Team</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The production team works together to ensure that PICNIC&rsquo;s thousands of guests have a great overall experience. Production volunteers work together with the PICNIC Production team in a variety of roles, including registration, production office assistance, location assistance and more.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Successful production team candidates:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		are service-oriented</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		have a general affinity for event production</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		can effectively multitask</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		can communicate professionally and effectively within a large team</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		know how to smile even in stressful moments</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		have a driver&rsquo;s license (applies to only a few roles, not all)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Program &amp; Speakers Team</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The program team works together to ensure that our 70+ speakers are well supported and have the best possible experience at PICNIC. Program volunteers work together with the PICNIC program team in a variety of roles, including speaker registration, &ldquo;agenda&rdquo; management for the speakers, speaker room assistance, and interview coordination (together with the PR team).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Successful press team candidates:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		are naturally service-oriented and easily connect with people</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		can effectively multitask</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		are responsible, presentable and committed</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		can communicate professionally in English</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		know how to smile even in stressful moments</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		have a pro-active attitude to meeting speakers&rsquo; needs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Press Team</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The press team works together to ensure that our 300+ journalists and press attendees are well supported and have the best possible experience at PICNIC. Press volunteers work together with the PICNIC PR team in a variety of roles, including press registration, press room assistance, and interview coordination.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Successful press team candidates:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		have a general affinity for press &amp; media</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		are service-oriented</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		can effectively multitask</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		can communicate professionally</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		feel comfortable interacting with senior-level journalists</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		know how to smile even in stressful moments</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Media Team</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The media team supports our professional photographers, cameramen and marketing manager in documenting the &ldquo;PICNIC magic&rdquo;. Media volunteers capture the essence of PICNIC on (digital) film, video and in words. Roles range from assistant photographer to Twitter master to compiling the best clips to put online. You help make sure that attendees are well-informed during the event and have a great collection of memories to view online after the festival is over.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Successful media team candidates:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		have a general affinity for media production/creation</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		can effectively multitask</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		can communicate professionally in English</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		feel comfortable interacting with senior-level attendees</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		have their own camera equipment (only for certain roles)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Apply today to be a PICNIC volunteer!</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	To apply to be a PICNIC Festival 2011 volunteer, fill in the <a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/documents/2\" target=\"_blank\">Volunteer Application Form</a> and email it to <a href=\"mailto:info@picnicnetwork.org?subject=Volunteer%20application\" target=\"_blank\">info@picnicnetwork.org</a>. Based on your preferred role, one of the members of the PICNIC team will be in touch to let you know if you have been selected.</p>\r\n','2011-07-08 15:26:20','2011-08-18 14:00:11','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-08 14:26:00',1,137,5,'',0),(159,41,'NIMk',NULL,'<p>\r\n	The <strong>Netherlands Media Art Institute</strong> (NIMk) promotes the wide development, application and distribution of, and reflection on new technologies in the visual arts. The Netherlands Media Art Institute supports media art in three core areas: presentation, research and collection, and through its facilities provides extensive services for artists and art institutions. Associated with this are educational programmes, which are developed for all activities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The NIMk is supported by the Ministry of Education, Culture and Science and the city of Amsterdam.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The NIMk is powered by BeamSystems.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://nimk.nl/eng/\" target=\"_blank\"> http://nimk.nl/eng/</a></p>\r\n','2011-07-11 09:58:35','2011-08-18 14:00:11','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-11 08:58:35',1,264,17,'',0),(162,45,'Press Releases',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Don&#39;t miss the latest news from&nbsp;PICNIC, as well as our&nbsp;sponsors and partners. Have a look at&nbsp;our announcements below:</h5>\r\n<h4>\r\n	PICNIC Press Releases</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/documents/5\" target=\"_blank\">PICNIC Builds City with BAM at NDSM</a> (29 July 2011)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/documents/4\" target=\"_blank\">Urban Futures - Building the PICNIC City</a> (14 April 2011)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Partner Press Releases</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		National Postcode Lottery:<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/documents/3\" target=\"_blank\"> Energy sector is hot amongst investors </a>(7 July 2011)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2011-07-12 11:55:37','2011-08-18 14:00:11','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-12 10:55:00',1,NULL,5,'',0),(163,48,'Everything is better when you experience it together--even PICNIC Festival!','<p>\r\n	Bring your best friend, colleague, neighbor or squash partner along to PICNIC Festival 2011 and get a great discount.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	<strong>From now until 31 July</strong>, both of you <strong>get 25% off your Festival Passe-partout&nbsp;</strong>with the PICNIC Buddy Offer.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Want the discount for you and a pal? Send an email to <strong>registration@picnicnetwork.org</strong> with the full names and email addresses of you and your friend, and we&rsquo;ll send you both your unique buddy code.</p>\r\n','2011-07-14 12:18:17','2011-08-18 14:00:11','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-13 11:16:00',1,144,20,'PICNIC Buddy Offer',0),(164,15,'Special offer: Free ticket to Hello Etsy in Berlin','<p>\r\n	Etsy, the online global marketplace for hand-made goods, is launching a brand new event in Berlin from 17-18 September &ndash; the weekend after PICNIC. Find out how you can get your free ticket to Hello Etsy!</p>\r\n','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Hello Etsy: A Summit on Small Business and Sustainability is a hands-on gathering for small business owners who want to connect with their peers, learn the skills to find success and independence, and be part of the movement to build human-scale economies.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	We&rsquo;re pleased to offer you a FREE ticket to <strong><a href=\"http://helloetsy.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Hello Etsy </a></strong>when you buy a ticket to PICNIC. Just send an email to <a href=\"mailto:registration@picnicnetwork.org?subject=Free%20Etsy%20Offer\" target=\"_blank\">registration@picnicnetwork.org</a> to request you unique code for this promotion.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<strong>Hello Etsy is for small businesses with big ambitions </strong></h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Etsy is excited by the rise of small businesses around the world, after decades of focusing on economic growth and a corporate mentality. Small businesses present opportunities to measure success in new ways: to build local, living economies, and most importantly, to help create a more permanent future.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The conference will be organized loosely around the entire process of coming up with an idea, turning it into a product, taking it to market, and building a business that is mindful and sustainable. Inspirational sessions will be held for all in attendance, and are followed by a variety of hands-on workshops that will take place in the smaller rooms around the venue. <a href=\"http://helloetsy.com/about/sessions/\" target=\"_blank\">Find out more about the sessions at Hello Etsy in Berlin</a>.</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<strong>Get a free ticket to Hello Etsy</strong></h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	From now until 1 September, you can get a ticket to Hello Etsy (value &euro;85) absolutely FREE of charge when you buy a ticket to PICNIC. Just email <a href=\"mailto:registration@picnicnetwork.org?subject=Free%20Etsy%20Offer\" target=\"_blank\">registration@picnicnetwork.org</a> for your special promo code.</p>\r\n','2011-07-19 13:20:24','2011-08-18 14:00:11','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-19 12:20:23',1,152,0,'',0),(165,32,'Microsoft','','<p>\r\n	At Microsoft, our mission and values are to help people and businesses throughout the world to realize their full potential.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We focus on people-centered, social experiences that push the boundaries of technology in ways that matter to people. Our big bets on great technology (NUI, Cloud, and Smart Devices) will help people enjoy experiences today and shape new and exciting possibilities of what technology can deliver tomorrow. We&rsquo;ve built deep integration between devices, content and services, using the cloud to power person-to-person interaction through voice, images and text. By bringing together the PC, Phone and the cloud, we&rsquo;re giving consumers amazing experiences that let them create, connect and share the content that matters most to them.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We believe technology has the power to transform lives for the better and Microsoft seeks ways to have this transformative impact in reaching a sustainable future. Armed with a diverse group of world-class talent deeply motivated to change the world, we feel we have a unique approach to creating and delivering new products and new technologies. An extensive partner ecosystem and deep partnerships with industry, academics, governments and international standards allow us to push the state of the art and have a broad impact.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Developing new ideas and technologies that will someday change the world is deeply woven into our DNA.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Will you join us?&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2011-07-20 13:48:21','2011-08-18 14:00:11','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-22 10:00:00',1,231,1,'Microsoft',0),(166,32,'BMW i',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	BMW i &ndash; Born Electric</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.youtube.com/watch?v=IPhRITdnrhE</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.bmw-i.com/en_ww/\" target=\"_blank\">BMW i </a>is dedicated to providing mobility solutions for the urban environment. It delivers not only purpose-built electric vehicles to reduce congestion in cities. It also delivers smart mobility services within and beyond the car. These services allow more freedom in urban life and can provide relief on city infrastructure.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The most important access point for most of the services is the mobile phone. The field of location-based mobility services is emerging and continuously changing. In order to engage in the most flexible way, the BMW Group has founded BMW i Ventures &ndash; a Venture Capital Company based in New York City. BMW i Ventures provides early- and mid-stage investments with high-potential in the area of Mobility Services.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	BMW i wants to engage, discuss and learn, together with the PICNIC community. We look forward to exploring and discovering new facets and possibility around urban mobility.</p>\r\n','2011-07-20 14:48:45','2011-08-18 14:00:12','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-22 10:00:00',1,228,0,'BMW i',0),(167,48,'WIRED',NULL,'<h2>\r\n	Welcome Wired readers!</h2>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Wired and PICNIC are partnering to offer a <strong>20% discount</strong> on all tickets to PICNIC Festival 2011, to be held 14-16 September in Amsterdam. Use special code <strong>WIREDPIC11 </strong>when<strong>&nbsp;</strong>buying tickets on the <a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/festival-registration\" target=\"_blank\">registration page</a> of the PICNIC website.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Want to know more first? Start <a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/welcome-1\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>, then read more about the line-up of 80 speakers <a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/picnic11-speakers\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Any questions? Email registration@picnicnetwork.org or call +31 20 320 5813.</p>\r\n','2011-07-21 10:57:59','2011-08-24 14:01:31','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-21 09:57:59',1,292,0,'WIRED',0),(168,36,'Designspotter','','<p>\r\n	DESIGNSPOTTER international design &amp; architecture platform</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We publish your creative works and force a worldwide media coverage in lifestyle and architecture magazines, newspapers, blogs and broadcasters. We spread the word for your creativity!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	With an easy upload of your product you create a profile and become part of our extended design network. And by the way you can reach hundredthousands of people and become splendid and famous :-) DESIGNSPOTTER is a design platform dedicated to everything related to young modern contemporary design including: accessories, books, design-contests, exhibitions, fashion, furniture, hotels, lighting, new materials, residential architecture, interior design and prototypes. Including Online Shop / Jobboard / marketplace / Events / etc.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.designspotter.com</p>\r\n','2011-07-25 15:26:42','2011-08-22 09:59:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-25 14:26:00',1,235,3,'Designspotter',0),(169,49,'BAM',NULL,'<p>\r\n	The origins of Royal BAM Group nv date back to the founding of a small carpentry workshop in the heart of the Netherlands in 1869. Today, more than 140 years later, the Group is a successful construction and property services enterprise with activities in numerous European countries and worldwide.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Royal BAM Group provides construction, property, civil engineering, public-private partnerships, mechanical and electrical contracting, and consultancy and engineering services to clients.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our organisation has an extensive network of business locations close to our clients. In addition, our services encompass every phase of the construction process, from development and design to construction, operation and maintenance. Our commitment to sustainability is integral to all our&nbsp;activities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.bam.nl</p>\r\n','2011-07-27 09:10:24','2011-08-18 14:00:12','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-27 08:10:00',1,289,1,'BAM',0),(171,15,'PICNIC builds city at NDSM with BAM','<p>\r\n	It might be the middle of the Dutch builder&rsquo;s vacation period, but that isn&rsquo;t stopping PICNIC from making big construction plans! Partners are in place, permits have been requested, and plans are underway to create the PICNIC City at the NDSM wharf in Amsterdam from 14 to 16 September 2011.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	<strong>Relying on the construction experts</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In the collaborative spirit of PICNIC, the city will be a joint production with a variety of partners. And when you&rsquo;re building a city, you look to the best in the construction business. This year, PICNIC is partnering with European construction firm BAM to create a &ldquo;green city&rdquo; in more ways than one. The PICNIC City will be composed of a variety of structures using re-purposed materials from BAM, in the company&rsquo;s classic green color. Prior to PICNIC Festival, BAM will put their logistical talents to work, transporting the building materials in a huge convoy from their plant yard in Kesteren.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/documents/5\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full press release about this year&#39;s festival decor and our partnership with BAM</a>.</p>\r\n','2011-07-29 12:25:06','2011-08-18 14:00:12','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-07-29 11:25:06',1,167,0,'',0),(173,15,'Green Challenge gets record number of submissions','<p>\r\n	This year, the Postcode Lottery Green Challenge has received a record&nbsp;number of submissions. A total of 717 people from around the world sent their green business plan for consideration for this year&#39;s award.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	From the amazing number of submissions, between 5 and 7 semifinalists will be selected to move on to the next round and compete for the grand prize of 500,000 EUR. In addition, another 200,000 EUR will be made available to the most deserving runner-up (or split between 2 runners-up).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Green plans from 81 countries</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Green Challenge has truly become a global phenomenon - this year the Postcode Lottery received submissions from 81 countries! As it to be expected, the greatested number of submissions came from the Netherlands (231), but were closely followed by the US (101), UK (91), and India (92). This year, the most popular categories were Engergy, Lifestyle,&nbsp;Mobility, Design and ICT, in that order.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Selection process and award ceremony</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The semifinalists will be revealed by the preliminary jury on 1 September. During the first 2 days of PICNIC Festival 2011, these semifinalists will present their business plans to an international jury and the PICNIC audience. On 15 September, the winners will be announced.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Green Challenge is certainly a can&#39;t miss event during PICNIC! Thanks to the generous support of the Postcode Lottery, including their publicity and network, past winners have gone on to realize their ambitions and achieve further success.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Find out more about this innovative award at <a href=\"http://www.greenchallenge.info\">www.greenchallenge.info</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><img src=\"/media/BAhbBlsHOgZmIjUyMDExLzA4LzA0LzA4XzQzXzM2XzUyMl9HcmVlbl9DaGFsbGVuZ2VfMjAxMS5wbmc\" alt=\"\" style=\"width: 490px; height: 135px; float: left;\" /></strong></p>\r\n','2011-08-04 15:59:28','2011-08-18 14:00:12','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-04 14:59:28',1,215,0,'',0),(174,40,'re/cruit :The Creative Industries Recruiting Fair','','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	September 23-25, 2011</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Cologne, Germany</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	&nbsp;</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	More than 1 million people work in the eleven sectors of creative industries generating approximately 2.6% of the annual GDP which is almost the same as the automotive industry&rsquo;s contribution.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	re/cruit Cologne is a three-day creative industries job fair. It provides the infrastructural framework for presentations and acquisitions in the area of Creative Human Resources. Companies and agencies -including those who hitherto haven&rsquo;t been as visible in a creative context - have the opportunity to present themselves and conduct a targeted search for suitable candidates in the creative cluster. Candidates on the other hand can gain a representative overview of current job and project vacancies as well as do some networking and directly introduce themselves to potential clients.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	re/cruit Cologne serves as an interface between the economy/industry, culture and creative people. re/cruit establishes a professional level of communication within the frameworks of this job fair and facilitates the exchange between supply and demand in resource management.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.recruit-cgn.de</p>\r\n','2011-08-09 12:44:21','2011-08-18 14:00:12','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-09 11:41:00',1,221,6,'re-cruit',0),(175,36,'Intellectueel Kapitaal',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Intellectueel Kapitaal (IK) is a digital magazine for knowledge- and information specialists and library professionals. Topics that are covered include practical aspects of knowledge technology, copyright, digitization, search technology, articificial intelligence, smart working, implications of internet on our society, information literacy, open access/open content, knowledge sharing, language technology, social media and privacy. Founder and editor-in-chief is Henk Verbooy. IK is published by Essentials (Rotterdam).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.essentials-media.nl/</p>\r\n','2011-08-09 12:52:48','2011-08-22 09:59:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-09 11:52:47',1,290,5,'Intellectueel Kapitaal',0),(176,36,'De Groene Amsterdammer',NULL,'<p>\r\n	De Groene Amsterdammer is an independent weekly opinion magazine feeding the broader public discourse, most specifically in the areas of politics, literature, the arts and philosophy. It features the leading thinkers and essayists from Holland as well Europe and the US.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You can now discover De Groene Amsterdammer at no cost and no risk. Treat yourself to four weeks of De Groene, totally free and without any obligation. The trial ends automatically.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.groene.nl/4weken</p>\r\n','2011-08-09 12:58:44','2011-08-22 09:59:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-12 11:57:00',1,283,4,'De Groene Amsterdammer',0),(177,49,'NDSM',NULL,'<p>\r\n	A former shipyard on the northern banks of the IJ and larger than 10 football fields, the NDSM wharf is now a center for underground culture in Amsterdam. This huge area contains the NDSM hall, a hangar-like structure 20,000 sq. meters in area and 20 meters in height, and two historic ship slipways(hellingen) housing workshops and artists&rsquo; studios.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The NDSM wharf offers facilities for a number of artistic disciplines and small crafts. The wharf has also become a sanctuary for individual artists and craftspeople as well as for independent organizations, both established and less known, to cooperate, inspire and create.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.ndsm.nl\">www.ndsm.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-08-09 13:06:41','2011-08-19 13:39:46','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-09 12:06:41',1,288,8,'NDSM',0),(178,15,'Join our team: Volunteer at PICNIC Festival 2011!',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Looking for a way to get more involved with PICNIC? How about applying to be a part of our PICNIC Festival 2011 volunteer team!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Every year we welcome thousands of visitors to Amsterdam for our three-day festival. During our event, we rely on a team of hardworking volunteers to help us with everything from production to registration to press. In short, our volunteers temporarily join the team to ensure every visitor has an amazing experience.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We&rsquo;re currently recruiting volunteers for a variety of roles to work at the PICNIC Festival 2011 from 14 to 16 September at the NDSM Wharf in Amsterdam.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Read more about how you can get involved and fill out a volunteer application form&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/jobs-at-picnic\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n','2011-08-09 13:39:09','2011-08-18 14:00:13','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-09 12:39:09',1,26,0,'Join our team: Volunteer at PICNIC Festival 2011!',0),(179,36,'Volume',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Volume is an independent quarterly magazine that sets the agenda for design. With going beyond architecture&rsquo;s definition of &lsquo;making buildings&rsquo; it reaches out for global views on designing environments, advocates broader attitudes to social structures, and reclaims the cultural and political significance of architecture. Created as a global idea platform to voice architecture any way, anywhere, anytime, it represents the expansion of architectural territories and the new mandate for design.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Volume magazine is a project by:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Archis: an experimental think tank devoted to the process of real-time spatial and cultural reflexivity and action. archis.org</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	AMO, a research and design studio that applies architectural thinking to disciplines beyond the borders of architecture and urbanism. AMO operates in tandem with its companion company the Office for Metropolitan Architecture, Rotterdam, The Netherlands</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Columbia Laboratory for Architectural Broadcasting, an experimental research unit devoted to the development of new forms of communication in architecture, set up as a semi-autonomous think and action tank at the Graduate School of Architecture, Planning and Preservation of Columbia University.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	VOLUME is produced and published by the Archis Foundation, The Netherlands and has been made possible with the support of The Mondrian Foundation Amsterdam.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Follow Volume on</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Twitter:&nbsp;@<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/archisvolume\" target=\"_blank\">ArchisVolume</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/archisvolume\" target=\"_blank\">archisvolume</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Online:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.volumeproject.org\" target=\"_blank\">volumeproject.org</a></p>\r\n','2011-08-09 15:44:52','2011-08-22 09:59:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-09 14:44:52',1,281,8,'Volume',0),(180,40,'Hello Etsy','','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	September 17-18</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Berlin</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Hello Etsy: A Summit on Small Business and Sustainability is a hands-on gathering for small business owners who want to connect with their peers, learn the skills to find success and independence, and be part of the movement to build human-scale economies.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Etsy is excited by the rise of small businesses around the world, after decades of focusing on economic growth and a corporate mentality. Small businesses present opportunities to measure success in new ways: to build local, living economies, and most importantly, to help create a more permanent future.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The conference will be organized loosely around the entire process of coming up with an idea, turning it into a product, taking it to market, and building a business that is mindful and sustainable. Inspirational sessions will be held for all in attendance, and are followed by a variety of hands-on workshops that will take place in the smaller rooms around the venue. Find out more about the sessions at Hello Etsy in Berlin.</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Get a free ticket to Hello Etsy</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	From now until 1 September, you can get a ticket to Hello Etsy (value &euro;85) absolutely FREE of charge when you buy a ticket to PICNIC. Just email registration@picnicnetwork.org for your special promo code.</p>\r\n','2011-08-10 09:27:25','2011-08-18 14:00:13','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-10 08:25:00',1,152,1,'Hello Etsy',0),(181,49,'Fronteer Strategy',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Fronteer Strategy is a multidisciplinary consulting firm that supports teams, companies and brands in their challenges on the path towards new growth. Right from a sketch on a napkin through to market introduction or implementation.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	BREAK THROUGH  </p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our key areas of expertise are Innovation and Brand Development.  Expert Co-creation is one of our specialties and regularly applied for generating breakthrough solutions to complex, urgent and strategic matters.Our services and tools can be applied at any moment of the innovation or growth process. No challenge is the same, so there are no cookie cutters in our toolbox. Nor do we believe in simply preparing a report for in your drawer. We work side-by-side with clients to cocreate actionable solutions.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	TOGETHER </p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Whether it is a large project lasting 6 months, a one-day workshop on co-creation, a three week online validation of your new service concept or a small project to redefine your brand, we work closely together with our clients and their (external) stakeholders to ensure high involvement and direct impact. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.fronteerstrategy.nl</p>\r\n','2011-08-10 11:14:51','2011-08-18 14:00:13','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-10 10:14:51',1,293,5,'Fronteer Strategy',0),(182,49,'Livetime',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Livetime Productions specializes in technical production of events, concerts, festivals and television productions. For all of these types of events, Livetime provides turnkey services and works as a technical and logistic coordinator, facilitator/negotiator (with a great network of international suppliers) for all of the facilities needed for the event or production. Livetime translates creative ideas into practical planning that includes staging, temporary structures, tents, sound &amp; light equipment, video screens, power supply, machinery, decoration, and more.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Technical production is a specialized profession. From the initial concept to showtime, Livetime guarantees a great production where nothing is left to chance. We guarantee quality by taking care of logistics, infrastructure, technique and crew, but also by noticing the details that make the difference. The technical production process guarantees synergy among the supporting vendors at an event. Livetime has the purchasing power and knowledge to produce all of the facility aspects in a production within the specified budget.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.livetime.nl</p>\r\n','2011-08-10 11:17:03','2011-08-18 14:00:13','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-10 10:17:00',1,298,6,'Livetime',0),(183,49,'MTV',NULL,'<p>\r\n	www.mtv.nl</p>\r\n','2011-08-10 11:17:51','2011-08-18 14:00:13','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-10 10:17:00',1,NULL,7,'MTV',1),(184,36,'The Next Web',NULL,'<p>\r\n	www.thenextweb.nl</p>\r\n','2011-08-10 12:03:21','2011-08-22 09:59:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-12 11:03:00',1,NULL,7,'The Next Web',1),(185,49,'Event Wifi',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Event Wifi delivers reliable internet and Wifi for events with large numbers of (concurrent) users. Event Wifi is a product of Event Engineers, a company with years of experience in the event industry. We&#39;re known for thorough preparations, quick deployment and turn-key delivery of projects.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	High-quality internet services are achieved through deployment of first-class equipment. To deliver rock-solid Wifi we use a centrally managed Ruckus Zoneflex system. This provides a single center of control for all network connections and makes it possible to guarantee all wireless users a fair amount of bandwidth. During events we deliver either remote monitoring or on-site service of the network depending on the customer&rsquo;s demands.&nbsp;Afterwards we compile a simple but decisive report on the usage and performance of the network.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.event-wifi.nl</p>\r\n','2011-08-10 13:57:14','2011-08-18 14:00:14','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-10 12:57:00',1,285,3,'Event Wifi',0),(186,15,'Meet the 2011 Marketplace participants','<p>\r\n	Set up like&nbsp;a farmer&#39;s&nbsp;market with a unique PICNIC twist, the Marketplace&nbsp;is where creative and innovative small businesses&nbsp;can showcase their talents at PICNIC Festival 2011.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	Organized by the Chamber of Commerce and Syntens together with KansenKanon and Mediaguild, The Marketplace is taking place for the 6th time during the PICNIC Festival. This year&#39;s participants come from a wide range of sectors, but they all want to contribute to building a better future together with the rest of the Festival attendees. Each day, 25 different exciting small companies will be showing their skills at the Marketplace.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	From amazing animation projects,&nbsp;and serious(ly fun) games, to human-powered ice cream makers and sneakers that grow flowers, the companies at the Marketplace are sure to get you inspired.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We can&#39;t wait to meet all of this year&#39;s participants in person, but until then,&nbsp;take a look <a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/documents/8\" target=\"_blank\">everyone participating in the 2011 Marketplace</a> and learn more about&nbsp;what they have to offer!</p>\r\n','2011-08-11 16:31:58','2011-08-18 14:00:14','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-11 15:31:57',1,271,0,'',0),(187,51,'Intro page','','<p>\r\n	this should be first page of section</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Premium Sponsors: Postcode Loterij, Vodafone and Waag Society.</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Meet them here.</h5>','2011-08-11 19:49:30','2011-08-18 14:00:14','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-11 18:48:00',1,NULL,0,'',0),(188,36,'Architizer','<br />\r\n','<p>\r\n	Architizer is the largest and fastest-growing network for architecture online, harnessing the power of social media to create an active forum where clients and fans can search for architecture. Since launching in 2009, the rapidly-expanding platform for exhibiting and connecting about architecture has over 400,000 members, 28,000 design projects and 7,400 international firms. The New York Times calls the open-platform website a &quot;hybrid of Flickr, Facebook and LinkedIn for architects&quot;.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.architizer.com</p>\r\n','2011-08-12 08:31:01','2011-08-18 14:00:14','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-12 07:31:00',1,284,0,'Architizer',0),(189,1,'Business Club','<p>\r\n	The Business Club is for organizations who want to get more out the their PICNIC experience. Get to know the 2011 PICNIC Business Club members below.</p>\r\n','<p>\r\n	Business Club members are part of PICNIC&#39;s inner circle and have access to our network and organization all year round. Of course, our Business Club members also get special treatment during our yearly Festival, not to mention access to other networking events.&nbsp;We&#39;re pleased to introduce you to our current PICNIC Business Club members!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/BAhbBlsHOgZmIiwyMDExLzA4LzEyLzA2XzQ4XzE0Xzg5MF9jb3Jpb19zbWFsbC5qcGc\" alt=\"\" style=\"width: 210px; float: left; height: 70px\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Corio is a retail property company. Our core business is to select, invest in, develop, redevelop and manage shopping centers in Europe. Our mission is to create favorite meeting places: sustainable centers where people meet up, spend their time off, and shop; places they want to keep coming back to.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.corio-eu.com\">www.corio-eu.com</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/BAhbBlsHOgZmIi4yMDExLzA4LzEyLzA2XzQ5XzI0XzQ1OF9FZGVsbWFuX3NtYWxsLmpwZw\" alt=\"\" style=\"width: 200px; float: left; height: 86px\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Edelman has always had creativity at its core and, after nearly 60 years since the company was founded, this is still driving the business. Family owned, Edelman is the leading independent global PR firm and in EMEA it has 750 people in 18 offices who are fortunate enough to work with some of the most innovative and inspiring companies. Beyond core communications, Edelman brings together insights and expertise from specialists in brand strategy, digital, mobile, content, planning, issues management and strategic media. We service our clients, not Wall Street. No one owns us, so we are free to think. Independently. To listen, question and evaluate with an open mind unrestrained by conventional wisdom - and then decide for ourselves.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.edelmanpr.nl/en\">www.edelmanpr.nl/en</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/BAhbBlsHOgZmIjIyMDExLzA4LzEyLzA2XzUxXzU2XzE0OV9lcm5zdF95b3VuZ19zbWFsbC5qcGc\" alt=\"\" style=\"width: 224px; float: left; height: 71px\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	With quality as its driving force, Ernst &amp; Young makes the greatest possible contribution to the success of its people and clients. Ernst &amp; Young offers its people maximum opportunity for personal development and helps its clients successfully achieve their goals and realize their ambitions. It operates to the highest possible standards on transparency, integrity and professionalism.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	At Ernst &amp; Young, quality comes first: quality of the people, the systems and the services. Ernst &amp; Young&#39;s specialists not only create confidence they also generate guaranteed added value for their clients. They turn their clients&#39; challenges into problem-solving services. Accountancy, tax advice, legal advice and transaction advisory services are the four pillars of our service.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.ey.com/NL/EN\">www.ey.com/NL/EN</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/BAhbBlsHOgZmIjMyMDExLzA4LzEyLzA2XzUyXzI2Xzc3Ml9pbmhvbGxhbmRfaHNfc21hbGwuZ2lm\" alt=\"\" style=\"width: 218px; float: left; height: 69px\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Inholland University of Applied Sciences is an ambitious institution of higher education in the western part of the Netherlands. Its vibrant learning and working community and particularly its scale is ideal for students who are keen to develop their theoretical knowledge as well as their practical skills. Offering competence-based learning, Inholland University of Applied Sciences is professionally involved both with the student, the market and society as a whole.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In order to develop the quality of all higher education programs offered by Inholland it has many strategic cooperation agreements with educational institutions both within the Netherlands and with more than 60 universities and higher education institutions abroad.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.inholland.nl\">www.inholland.nl</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img src=\"/media/BAhbBlsHOgZmIjIyMDExLzA4LzEyLzA2XzUzXzAwXzgxMV9TYW5vbWFNZWRpYV9zbWFsbC5qcGc\" alt=\"\" style=\"width: 254px; float: left; height: 44px\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	With their newspapers, consumer media, television channels, events, websites, mobile sites, mobile apps and iPad apps, Sanoma Media has the greatest reach of any media company in the Netherlands. As of 29 July 2011, Sanoma is the owner of SBS Netherlands with a 67% share &ndash; partner Talpa has the remaining 33%. Sanoma Media&rsquo;s portfolio includes more than 100 tier-1 brands, including AutoWeek, Donald Duck, delicious., Flow, Kieskeurig.nl, Libelle, Margriet, Net5, NU.nl, Viva, Vrowonline.nl, SchoolBANK.nl, SBS 6, Startpagina.nl and Veronica magazine.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.sanomamedia.nl\">www.sanomamedia.nl</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em><strong>Want to find out more about the PICNIC Business Club and how your organization can participate? Send an email to <a href=\"mailto:info@picnicnetwork.org\">info@picnicnetwork.org</a>.</strong></em></p>\r\n','2011-08-12 13:43:07','2011-08-18 14:00:14','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-12 12:43:00',1,279,4,'',0),(190,48,'Thank You',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Thanks for requesting a press pass for PICNIC Festival 2011!</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please note, this form is simply a request, not a confirmation. We&#39;ll be in touch with you within a week to let you know whether or not you are on the press list for this year&#39;s event.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For any additional press-related requests, please email the press team: <a href=\"mailto:press@picnicnetwork.org\">press@picnicnetwork.org</a></p>\r\n','2011-08-12 15:17:42','2011-08-18 14:00:14','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-12 14:17:42',1,NULL,0,'',0),(191,49,'Evident Online',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Evident Online is a full service internet agency in Utrecht which combines conceptual creativity and high standard technological knowledge. With more than 60 specialists and generalists, Evident works since 1996 for big customers on various internet and intranet projects. Evident offers strategic business consultancy, creative concepts and smart design and also takes care of building, implementation and hosting of the project.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Evident is co-founder of the PIBN (Platform Dutch Internet Agencies). Besides this Evident is Microsoft Gold Partner and certified Sitecore and Kentico CMS supplier.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Among others, Evident worked/works for: Royal Canin, SRA, Kapitaalplaza, ROC A12, Kluwer, Universiteit Utrecht, Bouwfonds, Zadkine, Kennisnet, Weekbladpers, Dela, Drimpy, PON, Danone (Actimel, Activia, Danoontje, Evian), Fleurop, VNU, Sanoma Uitgevers, Hogeschool Utrecht, UMC Utrecht, Monsterboard, Rabobank, Staatsbosbeheer, ING IM, de Baak, Telegraaf Media Groep, ProRail, Thieme Meulenhoff, GITP, Gemeente Utrecht, Insinger de Beaufort, and Albelli.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.evident.nl</p>\r\n','2011-08-12 15:37:33','2011-08-18 14:00:14','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-12 14:37:33',1,282,4,'Evident Online',0),(192,49,'American Book Center',NULL,'<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.abc.nl</p>\r\n','2011-08-15 11:41:58','2011-08-18 14:00:15','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-15 10:41:00',1,294,0,'American Book Center',1),(193,49,'Engage',NULL,'<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.engagetv.com</p>\r\n','2011-08-15 15:38:56','2011-08-18 14:00:15','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-15 14:38:00',1,NULL,2,'Engage',1),(194,40,'Media Evolution',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	24-25 August 2011</h5>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Malmo, Sweden</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	This year Media Evolution The Conference will focus on who the media industry&#39;s future audiences are, technology at our hand and how the way we create media (film, music, games, etc) change to correspond with the era we live and work in.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Conference attracts 600 people from Swedish and international media, communication and technology companies mainly at executive and creative level.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Among the speakers are Bill Drummond (The KLF), Amber Case (Geoloqi), Paola Antonelli (MoMA), Yancey Strickler (Kickstarter), Naveen Selvadurai (Foursquare), Jessica Cola&ccedil;o (iHub Nairobi), Bj&ouml;rn Jeffery (Bonnier), Luke Williams (NYU / Frog design) and M&aring;ns Adler (Bambuser). &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://mediaevolution.se/theconference</p>\r\n','2011-08-15 16:52:35','2011-08-18 14:00:15','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-15 15:51:00',1,307,0,'Media Evolution',0),(195,40,'Doc/Fest','','<p>\r\n	13-17 June 2012</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sheffield, England</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sheffield Doc/Fest brings the international documentary and digital family&nbsp;together to celebrate the art and business of documentary making for 5 days&nbsp;in June. Doc/Fest is famous for its fabulous parties and endless networking&nbsp;opportunities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The programme includes over 120 films, 300 speakers from the digital and&nbsp;docs sector and over 150 decision makers from 20 countries participate in the&nbsp;marketplace. Millions of pounds of deals are done during the festival.&nbsp;Year round Doc/Fest holds a series of workshops offering complete preparation&nbsp;for getting ideas pitched, developed, funded and distributed in new ways.&nbsp;More information can be found at sheffdocfest.com</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://sheffdocfest.com/</p>\r\n','2011-08-15 16:53:52','2011-08-19 16:17:40','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-15 15:53:00',1,310,2,'Doc/Fest',0),(196,36,'De Zaak',NULL,'<p>\r\n	De Zaak is a trusted, inspiring and interactive knowledge network for entrepreneurs. At De Zaak, you find everything you need to lead your business successfully - all in one place. De Zaak provides the latest news, personalized advice and practical information, in a business-driven and efficient way. They put the focus on your questions and your solutions, in their broad range of media channels.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.dezaak.nl</p>\r\n','2011-08-16 10:06:42','2011-08-22 09:59:06','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-16 09:06:42',1,301,10,'De Zaak',0),(197,48,'Swag',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Content coming soon.</p>\r\n','2011-08-17 16:11:03','2011-08-18 14:00:15','2034-12-31 23:00:00','2011-08-17 15:10:00',1,NULL,0,'',0),(198,36,'Contagious Communications',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Contagious Communications specialises in the identification of the future-facing creative ideas, cultural trends and technological platforms behind the world&rsquo;s most innovative marketing campaigns and branded services. Contagious&rsquo; quarterly magazine is globally recognized as an early warning system, an indispensable resource for advertisers and marketers as they attempt to keep pace with the changing face of consumer culture.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.contagiousmagazine.com</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://twitter.com/contagiousmag</p>\r\n','2011-08-19 10:03:16','2011-08-19 10:04:26','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-08-19 10:03:16',1,308,1,'Contagious Communications',0),(199,36,'Cool Hunting',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Cool Hunting is synonymous with seeking inspiration. Our global team of editors and contributors sift through innovations in design, technology, art and culture to create our award-winning publication, consisting of daily updates and weekly mini-documentaries. Founded in 2003 as a designer&#39;s personal reference, we now have an international audience of like-minded creative people, who find our content on coolhunting.com and on our iPad app, follow us on sites like YouTube, Vimeo, Twitter and Facebook, and subscribe to our RSS feed and email newsletter.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.coolhunting.com</p>','2011-08-22 09:58:27','2011-08-22 09:59:06','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-08-22 09:58:27',1,312,2,'Cool Hunting',0),(200,15,'PICNIC Festival sub-theme spotlight: Media','<p>\r\n	Discussions about our urban future must include media: it&#39;s a means of communication, &ldquo;decoration&rdquo;, digital playground, augmented experience and so much more. At PICNIC Festival 2011, we&rsquo;ll look at the impact of media on all angles of city life. Keep reading to learn more about this year&rsquo;s media highlights.</p>\r\n','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Speakers&nbsp;addressing media-related topics at PICNIC Festival 2011</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Get to know the experts and innovators that will be speaking on the main stage:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/221\" target=\"_blank\">Mark Woerde</a></strong> of LEMZ will look at how brands can heal the world</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/923\" target=\"_blank\">Laurence Parkes</a></strong> of AKQA will talk about socializing brands</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/214\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Toby Barnes</strong></a> of Mudlark examines the city as a dashboard, and talks about games for social change</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/269\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Emer Beamer</strong></a> of Butterfly Works discusses the role of games in informal settlements</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/215\" target=\"_blank\">Peter Corbett</a></strong> of iStrategyLabs will introduce his Apps for Democracy projects</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/766\" target=\"_blank\">David Barrie</a></strong> talks about the role of media in urban spaces</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/895\" target=\"_blank\">Jake Barton</a></strong> looks at collaboration and storytelling on an urban scale</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/707\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Ben Hammersley</strong></a> will put his unique spin on the impact of technology on social relationships</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/931\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Scott Snibbe </strong></a>will wow us with his interactive experiences, including the apps he created for Bjork&rsquo;s Biophilia project</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/members/581\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Beth Coleman</strong></a> introduces principles of x-reality design with &ldquo;Hello Avatar&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Workshops &amp; labs with a focus on media</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Get more face-time with our presenters at these labs and workshops where the audience can actively engage with each other and leading specialists.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/conference_sessions/125\" target=\"_blank\">Urban Screens Lab</a>:</strong> featuring Matt Cottam, Chris Heathcote &amp; Beeker Northam</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/conference_sessions/178\" target=\"_blank\">Transmedia Lab</a>: </strong>featuring Howard Goldkrand, Beth Coleman, Jeff Hull &amp; Lucy Walker</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/conference_sessions/108\" target=\"_blank\">Slacktivism: How to get media attention for your cause</a>:</strong> featuring Mark Woerde, Ottilie Nieuwenhuis &amp; David Langley</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/conference_sessions/171\" target=\"_blank\">The Data of People, Place and Play</a>:</strong> featuring Bonnie Shaw, Jake Barton &amp; Annette Mees</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/conference_sessions/35\" target=\"_blank\">Future Cities: Designing for Ownership</a>:</strong> featuring Tracy Metz, Cathy Brickwood, Michiel de Lange, Carl Lens, Martijn de Waal</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/conference_sessions/123\" target=\"_blank\">From Database Cities to Urban Stories Session 1</a>:</strong> featuring Roman Gallo, Nerea Calvillo, Mirko Lorenz, &amp; Mark Shepard</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong><a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/conference_sessions/121\" target=\"_blank\">From Database Cities to Urban Stories Session 2</a>:</strong> featuring Saskia Sassen, Juha van &lsquo;t Zelfde, Martijn de Waal &amp; Mark Shepard</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2011-08-23 10:17:01','2011-08-23 11:18:35','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-08-23 10:17:01',1,313,0,'',0),(201,15,'PICNIC Loves FigureRunning!','<p>\r\n	Eager to go to the PICNIC Festival 2011, but don&rsquo;t have a ticket? Put on your running shoes and win a free PICNIC Festival 2011 passe partout!</p>\r\n','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	This is your chance to win a free festival passe partout! What do you have to do?</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	In line with this year&rsquo;s theme Urban Futures, we&rsquo;re excited to introduce you to a new creative tech sport called FigureRunning! <strong><a href=\"http://www.figurerunning.com\" target=\"_blank\">FigureRunning</a></strong> encourages you to get creative, go outside and discover new places while running and getting ﬁt. The competition is not about your running speed or distance, it&rsquo;s all about drawing.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Using GPS in your smartphone, you can draw images while you are running. A line follows the actual route your run and you yourself are the pencil creating the artwork.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The sport is about challenging each other to make more creative runs every time you go out and play. Master the art of creative running and overcome obstacles that stand in your way (&quot;I have to run through your garden, otherwise my &#39;bunny-ear&#39; will fail!&quot;).</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Your mission to win a PICNIC Festival ticket:</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	1. Put on your running gear.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2. Get a GPS-enabled device (smartphone, GPS watch, or GPS tracker) and an application to track your run (the special FigureRunning app / Nike+ / Runkeeper).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3. Look at the map of your neighborhood and search for a heart in the streets.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	4. Walk to the street that marks the beginning of your drawing, turn on the GPS tracker and start running.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	5. Check the line which you are drawing to see if it works.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	6. Don&rsquo;t forget to have fun, you ARE the pencil!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	7. Finish your drawing, save it to your photo album and/or upload your drawing to FigureRunning/Nike/Runkeeper</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	8. Upload a picture of your FigureRun to your Picnicnetwork.org profile and tag the picture with &ldquo;figurerunning&rdquo;. Don&rsquo;t forget to describe how your run went and if you want, you can illustrate it with more &ldquo;what-I-found-on-the-way&rdquo; photos or a video.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	9. Do this before the <strong>deadline of 5 September 2011</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	10. Win the PICNIC Festival 2011 passe partout!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We have 3 tickets to give away&hellip;So what are you waiting for?! Grab your phone and your running shoes and get drawing!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	All the FigureRuns uploaded to your profile on picnicnetwork.org will be judged by a professional jury: Willempje Vrins, Leonieke Verhoog &amp; Jan Kroon (founders of FigureRunning) and Kitty Leering &amp; Micky van Zeijl from the PICNIC team. For inspiration go to <a href=\"http://www.figurerunning.com\">www.figurerunning.com</a>.</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Remember to upload your FigureRun to your PICNIC profile by 5 September for your chance to win a free ticket to PICNIC Festival.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	FigureRunning will also be present during PICNIC Festival 2011 for more fun with creative fitness!</p>\r\n','2011-08-23 13:18:04','2011-08-23 13:46:29','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-08-23 13:18:04',1,315,0,'',0),(202,4,'Interactive Activities & Exhibitions',NULL,'<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Glimpses, ARCAM exhibition</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Audio Map from Shoudio</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	FigureRunning</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Socrative</p>\r\n','2011-08-24 14:23:24','2011-08-25 14:17:01','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-08-24 14:23:00',1,NULL,0,'Interactive Activities & Exhibitions',1),(203,53,'Neo Tribes in Tokyo','','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	<a href=\"http://home.medewerker.uva.nl/a.b.f.beerkens/\" target=\"_blank\">Anneke Beerkens</a>, steps into the world of the underground Tokyo fashion tribes and shares a highly unusual insight into the lives of these and their charismatic leaders.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Young people in Japan seem to be turning away from the strict cultural boundaries of their parents. Especially from the fathers who struggle through life as &#39;sarariiman&rsquo; (office men). The Japanese youth tries to stay a way from this solitary existence.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It&#39;s a commonly heard gripe that globalization and the information age now have all of us worldwide sporting pretty much the same looks. It&#39;s reassuring then to step out onto the streets of Tokyo and be confronted with styles seemingly unique to Japanese shores.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	But how to make sense of this abundance of innovation? How to distinguish the emergent trend from the simple one-off? Anthropologist <a href=\"http://home.medewerker.uva.nl/a.b.f.beerkens/\" target=\"_blank\">Anneke Beerkens</a>, originally from Holland and now a researcher at Tokyo&#39;s Bunka Fashion College, helps sort the wheat from the chaff with her just-published tome &#39;Fashion Gods - Neo Tribes In The Streets Of Tokyo&#39;.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In the book Beerkens gives deep insight into the city&#39;s nascent fashion tribes and identifies their prime movers. Available from Amsterdam&#39;s &#39;denim-inspired boutique&#39; <a href=\"http://www.tenuedenimes.com\" target=\"_blank\">Tenue de N&icirc;mes </a>with international distribution set to follow. For now, get a taste for the quality of Beerken&#39;s writing with this superb article on Japan&#39;s longstanding love affair with Americana, which you can read for free <a href=\"http://issuu.com/nimes/docs/journal_no07\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sources:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tenuedenimes.com/journal/blog/2011/6/1/neo-tribes-in-tokyo-by-anneke-beerkens\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.tenuedenimes.com/journal/blog/2011/6/1/neo-tribes-in-tokyo-by-anneke-beerkens</a>, <a href=\"http://www.theragtrader.com/news/403/neo-tribes-in-tokyo\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.theragtrader.com/news/403/neo-tribes-in-tokyo</a></p>\r\n','2011-08-25 11:35:29','2011-08-25 11:37:01','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-08-25 11:35:00',1,321,0,'',1),(204,53,'Permanent Error','','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	For the past year Hugo has been photographing the people and landscape of an expansive dump of obsolete technology in Ghana. The area, on the outskirts of a slum known as Agbogbloshie, is referred to by local inhabitants as Sodom and Gomorrah, a vivid acknowledgment of the profound inhumanity of the place. When Hugo asked the inhabitants what they called the pit where the burning takes place, they repeatedly responded: &lsquo;For this place, we have no name&rsquo;.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Their response is a reminder of the alien circumstances that are imposed on marginal communities of the world by the West&rsquo;s obsession with consumption and obsolesce. This wasteland, where people and cattle live on mountains of motherboards, monitors and discarded hard drives, is far removed from the benefits accorded by the unrelenting advances of technology.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The UN Environment Program has stated that Western countries produce around 50 million tons of digital waste every year. In Europe, only 25 percent of this type of waste is collected and effectively recycled. Much of the rest is piled in containers and shipped to developing countries, supposedly to reduce the digital divide, to create jobs and help people. In reality, the inhabitants of dumps like Agbogbloshie survive largely by burning the electronic devices to extract copper and other metals out of the plastic used in their manufacture. The electronic waste contaminates rivers and lagoons with consequences that are easily imaginable. In 2008 Green Peace took samples of the burnt soil in Agbogbloshie and found high concentrations of lead, mercury, thallium, hydrogen cyanide and PVC.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Notions of time and progress are collapsed in these photographs. There are elements in the images that fast-forward us to an apocalyptic end of the world as we know it, yet the alchemy on this site and the strolling cows recall a pastoral existence that rewinds our minds to a medieval setting. The cycles of history and the lifespan of our technology are both clearly apparent in this cemetery of artifacts from the industrialized world. We are also reminded of the fragility of the information and stories that were stored in the computers which are now just black smoke and melted plastic.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Source: Pieter Hugo <a href=\"http://www.pieterhugo.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.pieterhugo.com</a></p>\r\n','2011-08-25 11:38:52','2011-08-25 12:33:51','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-08-25 11:37:00',1,NULL,0,'',1),(205,53,'Alone in New York',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	The Big Apple seen in from an emotional point of view.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Source: Guiseppe Vetrano <a href=\"http://www.giuseppevetrano.it/ \" target=\"_blank\">http://www.giuseppevetrano.it</a></p>\r\n','2011-08-25 12:02:29','2011-08-25 12:04:31','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-08-25 12:00:00',1,NULL,0,'',1),(206,53,'The Future of Hope','','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Over the past 20 years we have seen a growing realization that the current model for society and culture is unsustainable. We have been living beyond our means...</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Future of Hope is a documentary film following individuals that strive to change the world of consumerism, a system of credit and debt that the Icelandic economy was built upon for the past 10 years or more. Focusing on sustainable developments in organic farming, business, innovation, renewable energy and the environment - filled with positivity and emotion as we are taken on a story of struggle, determination and most importantly... hope. From the midnight sun, to dark winters lit only by the snow, from geysers to volcanoes, this movie truly explores the magnificent country of Iceland. Future of Hope takes you on a journey from the history to the present and even into the future of a new and sustainable Iceland.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Source:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://futureofhope.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">http://futureofhope.co.uk</a></p>\r\n','2011-08-25 12:08:59','2011-08-25 12:10:13','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-08-25 12:06:00',1,NULL,0,'',1);
