nAdsBlue-. We donate 5 euro cents for every liter we use.\nWe are by no means the perfect solution! We have an impact on the environment, we do use fossil fuels to power our equipment. But we believe we are a better alternative to traditional out of home advertising posters and billboards; We do not use paper - paper which is often not from controlled sources (billboards are printed on PVC even worse), we do not use inks - inks that are either petroleum based (printed double sided to work with back-lighting) in the case of paper posters or aggressive solvent based inks in the case of billboards.  Our ads are not back lit or front lit including the 5 or 6 hours a night very people are even outside to see them and we generate very little waste. Posters are generally up for one week and Billboards two to four after which time they are thrown away. (hopefully recycled). \nWe also donate a lot of work to local communities and do cleaning projects in playgrounds for instance as part of trying to be a socially responsible company. And I think this is what is the future. It is not our techniques that are innovative - reverse graffiti has been around for many decades - it is our approach to business. Using GreenGraffiti® the business as a tool for social and environmental improvement. Working with the idea of earning profits of course as we are a business and need to pay the rent but earning profits with principles.\nPeople like yourself are very important to our company. Our water awareness and thus water foundation are the direct result of comments we got about our water consumption and you know, they were right! Water is precious. We can\'t eliminate it from our processes but we can take steps to reduce our water usage, to use gray water sources (health issues here) and to perhaps use it here but provide it there. \nWe learn a lot from people outside our company and would welcome your thoughts as to what we are doing wrong and where we could do better. You have some concerns about what we are doing and we would hope you would share them with us and perhaps provide some solutions that would help people with the same issues you have, understand or even tolerate better what we are doing on the streets. Please, feel free to critique us, we need to know where we can do better and what things are rubbing people the wrong way.\n\nThanks for raising the question!\nJIm','2011-08-12 06:35:31','2011-08-12 06:35:31',NULL,NULL,1),(178,247,257,'Hi Jim,\n\n\nYour contribution to the future urban cities (in 2030) goal is to replace all bilboards/current advertisement  on the streets with water spray art to make 2030 a better world?!?\n\ncheck this out  www.aurasma.com   this is the future for advertising on the streets\n\n ','2011-08-12 07:22:18','2011-08-12 07:22:18',NULL,NULL,1),(179,108,260,'It so should ... but not at the expense of reality !','2011-08-12 08:37:04','2011-08-12 08:37:04',NULL,NULL,1),(180,863,255,'thanks to the PICNIC team and the great people being on stage and attending it\'s highly addictive to come again and again','2011-08-12 10:00:48','2011-08-12 10:00:48',NULL,NULL,1),(181,139,257,'Michiel!\nLove to really talk. Big fan of ar in fact we see this as ggx10 but its one step at a time. \nWe are not looking to replace traditional outdoor by any means as it plays an important role. We do see ourselves becoming a standard part of the media mix. One that matches the ambitions of brands, consumers and goverments. \nAn alternative is the key word. Currently there are very few if ant really sustainable forms of outdoor media! We have great hope in new technologies such as AR. Love to hear your thoughts and learn from you. \nJim','2011-08-12 10:59:46','2011-08-12 10:59:46',NULL,NULL,1),(182,510,260,'True - it should be value added not value distraction.','2011-08-12 11:57:44','2011-08-12 11:57:44',NULL,NULL,1),(183,108,261,'It is indeed ... one of the joys of coming to PICNIC is that I get to meet, talk to and learn from the new Tribe ... they are normally also involved the high impact, hands on stuff that happens at PICNIC . You should also check out the Kaos Pilots http://www.kaospilot.dk out of which the Knowmads were born.','2011-08-12 13:17:40','2011-08-12 13:17:40',NULL,NULL,1),(184,510,261,'i shall!','2011-08-12 14:27:35','2011-08-12 14:27:35',NULL,NULL,1),(185,247,257,'looking forward to have you on my blanket','2011-08-12 14:57:35','2011-08-12 14:57:35',NULL,NULL,1),(186,139,257,'So Michiel,\nCan I ask you why you think that what we are doing is \"not so green-graffiti advertisement\"? Is this just a general statement, is it in comparison to other forms of out door advertising, can \"evil\" advertising ever play a positive role? \nI am sure you are not the only person who has a negative view on this young, fast growing and emerging new industry. We would like to learn what those issues are so that we can address, modify, change, improve them and improve our company to better communicate our ambitions and our accomplishments. \nAs you know sustainability is not just green. It is also about people and in order for anything to be sustainable, it also needs to be profitable. So come on man, blast away at GreenGraffiti® - it would be a great help.\nWe know there are better ways in the future but it might be helpful to limit the conversation to what is available to advertisers today. Can technology play a big role? Oh yes it can... in the future but what about right now today?\nLook forward to hearing your insights and vision.\nJim','2011-08-13 07:45:10','2011-08-13 07:45:10',NULL,NULL,1),(187,809,247,'Great Sidney!  \ncheck out the photos of the first BIG BANG NIGHT 1\nhttp://alturl.com/qif2o\n','2011-08-13 15:21:41','2011-08-13 15:21:41',NULL,NULL,1),(188,247,257,'not so green is your emotional appeal:using petrol going in a car to a spot, splash water on the street/template with all \"muddy mess\" around it, not usable in cold freezing weather, perhaps...in the USA you fear a lawsuit of old ladies falling on their bottom due to slippery roads from your water/muddy mess  oooops:)\n\nexample\ngreen graffiti  is: use some people e.g. of my platform IBM student legend app world wide(students) ride their bikes to your client/street area, place template on street use \"elbow grease\" and metal polish brush for same result... usable in freezing street, no water, cost reduction of my students on a bike ,versus your people with a car /pertol and water trouble and that work only for not frozen street surfaces...\n\n\nGreat you \"buy water back\"by spending money to refund the water you used, however it\'s better to give this to students to develop more options for green graffiti with a better apeal:\n-e.g. we can make an app for you tailor made that is for AR\n-e.g. the students can develop new methods on grass/street surface for prints and ads \n\nsoon we talk and brainstorm to make the emotional appeal of your graffiti really green!','2011-08-14 18:00:40','2011-08-14 18:00:40',NULL,NULL,1),(189,108,263,'Glad you are not the only one confused ! Maybe we should just go for a run instead ! ','2011-08-14 20:43:54','2011-08-14 20:43:54',NULL,NULL,1),(190,856,263,'Great idea! Lets run a question mark! ?','2011-08-14 20:56:17','2011-08-14 20:56:17',NULL,NULL,1),(191,139,257,'Crowd sourcing is ideal and fits our business perfectly. It is certainly something we are interested in. We also like the idea of using the \"hard to employ\" which we have done (Pantar)  as reverse grafiti is something that once the right location has been found, does not require a high level of training or skill. Currently we use students in our operations and pay them a very good wage. Love to support them. Better work then the horeca and I was once one myself. \nBrushes and scrubbing by hand would take quite a long time and that would translate to higher costs I believe. GG has always been open to collaboration, to people adding their ideas and criticism. We know the best new ideas will come from people outside the company. GreenADsBlue our water foundation is one such idea that came about by looking at concerns of the general public most who viewed our water use as wasting a natural resource even though we actually use 1/30 the amount of water it takes to create a piece of paper ot the same size.\nAnother thing to consider is that (unfortunately as I am a big believer in sustainable development/duurzaamheid) few of our clients has used GreenGraffiti® because of it\'s sustainable benefits. This is seen mostly as a \"bonus\" - a feel good factor but not a position that drives sales. Even companies such as Triodos, Essent, Unilever, even Amsterdam Duurzaam dag and a long list of companies claiming to be sustainably focuses who we have met with prefer to use Abris and Billboards as it is just \"easier\", \"safer\" and \"known\". They like the concept, support us as a young ambitious company with an innovative approach but end of day they are still business as usual businesses often using sustainability as a marketing tool rather than practicing what they preach. Emotion though heart warming and the reason for the shear volume of world wide media attention we have received, does not sell services. We have learned we have to focus on the business benefits to sell our services not our sustainable proposition which is quite frankly a pretty sad insight into how businesses are really approaching their sustainable ambitions in the Netherlands.\n\nDo you develop AR Apps? I see you are involved in connecting business opportunities and international expansion. What else do you do?\n\nI look forward to getting together to brainstorm. Thanks for the feedback and comments. If you have a network of students that would like to be involved, could add ideas and value, we would of course welcome them with open arms. \nWe are not perfect nor do we claim to be. We are a step in the right direction. We would prefer to be a leap in the right direction.\n\nTalk soon,','2011-